global-definitions.name: OAM
global-definitions.comment: This FDD/TDD common OAM release is based on FDD PDDB version "LTE BTS LN7.0_1401_001 0.1" and TDD PDDB version "LTE BTS LNT5.0_1401_002 0.0" .

typedef.name: TOaMActAlsoForUeBasedANR
typedef.comment: Activates the profile for UE-based intra- and/or inter-frequency ANR (LTE556, LTE782) too. If set to "true" the profile applies for any kind of ANR, that is UE-based and not UE-based. If set to "false" the profile is not applied for UE-based ANR but still applied for not UE-based ANR features (for example LTE492).

typedef.name: TOaMAnrprwEnableAnrProfile
typedef.comment: The parameter enables ANR learning for the carrier frequency of the profile.

typedef.name: TOaMAlDcVoltageEnabled
typedef.comment: Defines if antenna line DC power is enabled/disabled for an antenna line. The DC power is enabled by default (when the file or parameter is not available for an AL). This parameter is the most relevant for AL DC power Note! In RF sharing case this parameter value shall be set to "false" if BTS is set to the Radio slave mode (SMOD - linkList - radioMaster parameter value is set to "false").

typedef.name: TOaMCommunication3gppEnabled
typedef.comment: Defines if the device scan functionality is enabled/disabled for a capable 3GPP antenna line. The scan is enabled by default (when the file or parameter is not available for an AL). Note: In RF sharing case this parameter value shall be set to the "false" if BTS is set to the Radio slave mode (SMOD - linkList - radioMaster parameter value is set to "false").

typedef.name: TOaMExt1ppsClkOutOn
typedef.comment: Controls if in holdover mode the external 1pps output is switched on (parameter = true) or switched off (parameter = false). In case the BTS has lost all supported reference sources for generating 1pps pulse, the BTS starts running in hold-over mode. This parameter controls if in holdover mode the external 1pps output is switched on or off.

typedef.name: TOaMExt2M048ClkInUse
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the usage of the external 2.048MHz synchronization reference.
TDD specific comment: Defines the usage of the external 2.048MHz synchronisation reference.

typedef.name: TOaMExt2M048ClkOutOn
typedef.comment: Controls if in holdover mode the external 2.048 MHz output is switched on (parameter = true) or switched off (parameter = false). In case the BTS lost all supported reference sources for providing the external 2.048 MHz output, the BTS starts running in hold-over mode. This parameter controls if in holdover mode the external 2.048 MHz output is switched on or off.

typedef.name: TOaMGpsCtrlBlockForCoLocatedBts
typedef.comment: Parameter gpsCtrlBlockForCoLocatedBts controls the mode of operation of the GPS/1pps synchronization input interface. Setting gpsCtrlBlockForCoLocatedBts to value: - "false": Synchronization from external GPS receiver, the BTS is directly connected to an external GPS receiver. It controls the external GPS receiver via TSIP commands and receives TSIP response messages from the receiver. - "true": Synchronization from another BTS, the BTS is not directly connected to an external GPS receiver and is synchronized by a Synchronization Hub BTS. It does not send any TSIP commands for controlling a GPS receiver, but it receives TSIP response messages forwarded by the previous BTS in a 1pps synchronization chain.

typedef.name: TOaMGpsInUse
typedef.comment: Defines the usage of the GPS. GPS is connected to the system module

typedef.name: TOaMHoldOverModeUsed
typedef.comment: This parameter determines whether System Module fan speed is optimized by oscillator temperature or noise level.

typedef.name: TOaMRfSharingEnabled
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter enables the RF sharing with GSM or UTRAN in LTE BTS. Parameter is used only for automatic licence activation and in addition this parameter is used for shared RF modules IP address configuration. This means that the Multi Carrier Power Amplifiers (MCPA) transmitting both GSM/EDGE RF, WCDMA and LTE RF carrier signals at the same 3GPP frequency band. When operating in RF sharing mode, a single RF Module is connected to 2 System Modules simultaneously. Flexi EDGE System Module is operating in GSM/EDGE SW or WCDMA mode and Flexi Multimode System Module in LTE or WCDMA SW mode. Both are connected to the one and same Flexi Multiradio RF Module. Super cell configurations are not released in conjunction with RF-Sharing. Note: Shared RF cannot chained. Note: LTE 3G RF sharing can be configured into use only if the shared BTS does or will contain a 3G System Module. If the 3G System Module does not exist and the LTE-3G RF sharing has been configured into use, LTE BTS will stay in the initializing state because the 3G System Module is always the synchronization master in case of LTE-3G RF sharing. Initializing state in the LTE BTS SW prevents reconfiguration commissioning of the LTE BTS by the BTS Site Manager.
TDD specific comment: This parameter enables the RF sharing with GSM in LTE BTS. Parameter is used only for automatic licence activation and in addition this parameter is used for shared RF modules IP address configuration. This means that the Multi Carrier Power Amplifiers (MCPA) transmitting both GSM/EDGE RF and LTE RF carrier signals at the same 3GPP frequency band. When operating in RF sharing mode, a single RF Module is connected to 2 System Modules simultaneously. Flexi EDGE System Module is operating in GSM/EDGE SW mode and Flexi Multimode System Module in LTE SW mode. Both are connected to the one and same Flexi Multiradio RF Module. Note: LTE 3G RF sharing can be configured only if the shared BTS does or will contain a 3G System Module. If the 3G System Module does not exist and the LTE-3G RF sharing has been configured, LTE BTS will stay in the initializing state because the 3G System Module is always the synchronization master in case of LTE-3G RF sharing. Initializing state in the LTE BTS SW prevents reconfiguration commissioning of the LTE BTS by the BTS Site Manager.

typedef.name: TOaMSyncPropagationEnabled
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter enables the feature "Synchronisation Hub". If the feature activation flag is set to True, it is possible to use both the 2MHz output signal and the PDH output signal for synchronization.
TDD specific comment: This parameter enables the feature "Synchronisation Hub" If the feature activation flag is set to True, it shall be possible to use the 1pps output signal for synchronization.

typedef.name: TOaMTdmSyncInUse
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the usage of the TDM synchronization reference.
TDD specific comment: Defines the usage of the TDM synchronisation reference.

typedef.name: TOaMDisableSCellPDCCHOlLa
typedef.comment: The parameter controls if PDCCH outer loop link adaptation is disabled in SCell for a UE with an activated SCell. If disableSCellPDCCHOlLa is set to True, PDCCH OLLA will be disabled for a UE with an active SCell in its SCell (other UEs in this cell which do not have SCell activated/configured can use PDCCH OLLA depending on the setting of actOlLaPdcch in this cell). If actOlLaPdcch in PCell and SCell is 'true' and disableSCellPDCCHOlLa is set to false, PDCCH OlLa in the SCell will be used for the UE with an active SCell and it will reuse the calculations of the PDCCH OlLa in the PCell of this UE. If actOlLaPdcch in PCell or SCell is configured to 'false', PDCCH OlLa in SCell is never used and the configured value of disableSCellPDCCHOlLa is not considered by BTS SW. The parameter shall be set to 'false' when it is expected that there is some correlation between pdcchCqiShift(t) in the pair of cells that are aggregated and it shall be set to 'true' otherwise.

typedef.name: TOaMUeActiveTrcSessFlag
typedef.comment: This indicates if there are any active UE trace sessions running within eNB. This parameter indicates if there are any active UE trace sessions currently running within eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMIrfimInterPresAntP
typedef.comment: The IE PresenceAntennaPort1 is used to indicate whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

typedef.name: TOaMDtm
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates whether the GERAN target cell is DTM-capable. This information is evaluated during SRVCC to GERAN when deciding whether the UE is available for PS service

typedef.name: TOaMAct1xCsfb
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature LTE1441 enhanced CSFB to CDMA2000 1xRTT.

typedef.name: TOaMAct8EpsBearers
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support of up to 8 EPS bearers.

typedef.name: TOaMActAutoLteNeighRemoval
typedef.comment: Activates autonomous removal of unused LTE neighbour relation and neighbour information

typedef.name: TOaMActCMAS
typedef.comment: Activates CMAS support If CMAS support is set to "true", CMAS warning messages are broadcasted (SIB12) in case of Write-Replace Warning Request incl. CMAS data is received from MME

typedef.name: TOaMActCellTrace
typedef.comment: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Cell Trace feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActCellTraceWithIMSI
typedef.comment: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Cell Trace with IMSI feature. It will be only utilized when cell trace is activated, i.e. actCellTrace is 'true'

typedef.name: TOaMActCiphering
typedef.comment: This parameter enables/disables optional ciphering algorithms.

typedef.name: TOaMActCompChecks
typedef.comment: The parameter activates Complete Consistency Checks in Validator tool. This parameter can be used to disable the checks that could block eNB reconfiguration after SW upgrade. Only particular checks in Validator tool are disabled by this parameter. When, after SW upgrade, configuration validation fails in BTS Site Manager or in NetAct, it is possible to set this parameter to "false" and proceed with eNB reconfiguration. During SW upgrade the configured parameter value will not be changed.

typedef.name: TOaMActConvVoice
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support of the conversational voice bearer. The change becomes active for a cell after the next cell locking/cell unlocking sequence.

typedef.name: TOaMActCplaneOvlHandling
typedef.comment: Feature enabling flag for LTE1047: C-plane overload handling feature. The feature detects overload and triggers counter measures.

typedef.name: TOaMActCsfbPsHoToUtra
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the feature 'Circuit Switched Fallback with Packet Switched Handover to UTRA'.

typedef.name: TOaMActDLCAggr
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter activates the LTE1089: Downlink carrier aggregation and LTE1332:Downlink carrier aggregation - 40 MHz feature. The feature allows higher UE downlink peak data rates by aggregation of two cells.
TDD specific comment: The parameter activates the feature LTE1558 'Downlink carrier aggregation' and feature LTE1830 'TDD downlink carrier aggregation enhancement'. The feature allows higher UE downlink peak data rates by aggregation of two cells.

typedef.name: TOaMActDistributedSite
typedef.comment: The parameter actDistributedSite allows usage of Distributed Site. That is, a RF unit may lie up to 20 km distance from the system module.

typedef.name: TOaMActDualBand
typedef.comment: The eNB supports up to 6 cells dual band configurations with one system module.

typedef.name: TOaMActDualCarrier
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The eNB will support two carriers within the same RF band for same sector (that is for one antenna line) when the value is configured to "true". The carriers in a band must have same bandwidth. Bandwidths 5MHz, 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz are supported.
TDD specific comment: Activation of Dual Carrier usage. This parameter need to be set to 'true' to configure 2 cells for one antenna line.

typedef.name: TOaMActDualRx1xCsfb
typedef.comment: Activates the feature CS fallback to CDMA 1xRTT for dual Rx UEs

typedef.name: TOaMActERabModify
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the E-RAB Modification by the S1AP message E-RAB MODIFY REQUEST.

typedef.name: TOaMActETWS
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Activates ETWS support If ETWS support is set to "true", ETWS primary and secondary notification are broadcasted (SIB10 and SIB11) in case of Write-Replace Warning Request incl. ETWS, data is received from MME.
TDD specific comment: Activates ETWS support If ETWS support is set to true, ETWS primary and secondary notification are broadcasted (SIB10 and SIB11) in case of Write-Replace Warning Request incl. ETWS data is received from MME

typedef.name: TOaMActEnhAcAndGbrServices
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter activates support of the following features LTE534: ARP based Admission Control LTE497: Smart Admission Control, comprising RAC and TAC LTE496: EPS bearers with QCI 2, 3 and 4 Feature LTE496 introduces support of QCI 2, 3, and 4 along with higher guaranteed bit rates and related congestion detection and handling mechanisms. Admission control functionality (LTE497) is extended at the same time from a counter based solution to become load based and offer in addition congestion handling functionality to better address the needs being imposed by higher guaranteed bit rates. Finally the ARP based admission control (LTE534) allows to consider the ARP priority in load-based admission and admission related pre-emption as well as in congestion handling as an additional more service-related dimension for differentiated treatment of bearers with guaranteed resources. As those features are closely inter-related, they are activated via a common activation parameter.
TDD specific comment: This parameter activates support of the following features: ARP based Admission Control (LTE534), Smart Admission Control, comprising RAC and TAC (LTE497) and EPS bearers with QCI 2, 3 and 4 (LTE496). Feature LTE496 introduces support of QCI 2, 3, and 4 along with higher guaranteed bit rates and related congestion detection and handling mechanisms. Admission control functionality (LTE497) is extended at the same time from a counter based solution to become load based and offer in addition congestion handling functionality to better address the needs being imposed by higher guaranteed bit rates. Finally the ARP based admission control (LTE534) allows to consider the ARP priority in load-based admission and admission related pre-emption as well as in congestion handling as an additional more service-related dimension for differentiated treatment of bearers with guaranteed resources. As those features are closely inter-related, they are activated via a common activation parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMActFlexBbUsage
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Activation of more flexible base band usage by allowing more enhanced recovery in case of HW failure. If the parameter is set to 'true', the size of PUCCH PRB may be limited on 10 MHz system bandwidth or lower. The parameter need to be set to 'true' to configure more than 2 cells with FSMD, more than 3 cells with FSME or FSMF without extension Baseband module, more than 6 cells with FSMF with extension Baseband module or more than 12 cells with FSMF + FBBA + FBBC. When parameter is set to 'true', range of parameters maxNumActUE and maxNumRrc will be limited. FSMD: value 'false' => up to 2 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 3 cells can be configured. FSME: value 'false' => up to 3 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 6 cells can be configured. FSMF: value 'false' => up to 3 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 6 cells can be configured. FSMF + 1 x Extension Baseband Module: value 'false' => up to 6 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 12 cells can be configured. FSMF + FBBA + FBBC: value 'true' => up to 18 cells can be configured.
TDD specific comment: Activation of more flexible base band usage by allowing more enhanced recovery in case of HW failure. If the parameter is set to 'true', the size of PUCCH PRB may be limited on 10 MHz system bandwidth or lower. This parameter needs to be set to 'true' to configure more than 2 cells with FSMD or more than 3 cells with FSME. If the parameter is set to 'true', range of parameters maxNumActUE and maxNumRrc will be limited.

typedef.name: TOaMActGsmRedirWithSI
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the feature "GSM redirect with system information".

typedef.name: TOaMActHOtoHrpd
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the feature Handover from LTE to eHRPD.

typedef.name: TOaMActHOtoWcdma
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the Handover from LTE to WCDMA feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActHeNBMobility
typedef.comment: Activates open access home eNB mobility.

typedef.name: TOaMActHighPrioServices
typedef.comment: This parameter enables/disables the feature "Multimedia priority services" (LTE1074)

typedef.name: TOaMActHighRrc
typedef.comment: Activation to configure more than 840 RRC connected UE. With this parameter it is possible to support higher amount of Active UE on cell. The amount of Active UE cannot exceed maximum number of RRC_connected. The parameter can be configured to "true" for cell bandwidths of "15 MHz" or "20 MHz" using System module that supports over 840 RRC connected UE.

typedef.name: TOaMActHoFromUtran
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature Handover from UTRAN.

typedef.name: TOaMActIMSEmerSessFWAUEs
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the support of IMS Emergency sessions for Fixed Wireless Access UEs (3GPP Release 8 based).

typedef.name: TOaMActIMSEmerSessR9
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support IMS Emergency sessions for Release 9 UEs.

typedef.name: TOaMActIdleLB
typedef.comment: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing This flag activates the following functionalities: -inter-RAT IdleLB targets -Load balancing for redirection (requires also the UE context release with redirect feature "actRedirect" and CS Fallback via Redirection feature "actCSFBRedir") -IdleLB targets in Mobility profiles (requires also the "Selective Mobility Profiles" feature "actSelMobPrf") -Support of special SPID values (requires also the "Selective Mobility Profiles" feature "actSelMobPrf")

typedef.name: TOaMActImmHRPD
typedef.comment: Activates "Idle mode mobility from LTE to CDMA/eHRPD".

typedef.name: TOaMActImmXrtt
typedef.comment: Activates idle mode mobility from LTE to CDMA/1xRTT.

typedef.name: TOaMActInterFreqLB
typedef.comment: The parameter activates Inter- frequency load balancing (iF-LB) feature. If the feature iF-LB is activated ("true"), inter-frequency load measurements are performed per cell. Dependent on the actual load situation UEs might be handovered to low loaded neighbor cells (different frequency layer).

typedef.name: TOaMActIntraFreqLoadBal
typedef.comment: If activated, the intra-frequency load balancing algorithm continuously estimates the cell load, triggering a handover threshold negotiation with the neighbors when the cell load is above a predefined value. The handover threshold negotiation procedure is done over the X2 interface to align the handover thresholds between neighbor cells. Hint: The LTE1140: Load Balancing and LTE533: Mobility Robustness features both modify the Cell Individual Offset (CIO) values of LTE neighbor relations. Therefore the LTE533: Mobility Robustness NetAct feature must not be activated respectively deployed in parallel because this might lead to not optimal CIO values. If the feature is deactivated, the "cellIndOffNeighDelta" parameter is implicitly set to 0 in all LNREL objects.

typedef.name: TOaMActLPPaOtdoa
typedef.comment: Activates support of the LPPa OTDOA information request procedure via S1AP

typedef.name: TOaMActLTES1Ho
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature Intra LTE Inter eNodeB Handover via S1

typedef.name: TOaMActLocRep
typedef.comment: Activation/deactivation of Location Reporting (feature 'Support of cell based location service')

typedef.name: TOaMActMDTCellTrace
typedef.comment: This is a feature flag to enable or disable LTE953: MDT Trace feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActMFBI
typedef.comment: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature "Multiple Frequency Band Indicator" (LTE1534)

typedef.name: TOaMActMultBearers
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support of multiple EPS Bearers.

typedef.name: TOaMActMultGbrBearers
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support of multiple GBR EPS Bearers.

typedef.name: TOaMActNonGbrServiceDiff
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the Service Differentiation for non-GBR Bearers.

typedef.name: TOaMActOTNRecovery
typedef.comment: Activate OTN Link Loss Self-Recovery flag This parameter specifies the behavior of Optical Network (OTN) recovery actions. When this parameter is set to true, a 1956 fault (critical BER detected on the optical connection to Radio Module) will not trigger the BTS to reset the impacted RF modules immediately. Instead, the BTS will stay in service and attempt to re-adjust the delays within the time limit as specified in OTN Recovery Period. The radios will self-reset if readjustments failed within the time period. When this parameter is set to false, adjustments will not occur and the BTS will reset the impacted RF modules when fault 1956 is detected.

typedef.name: TOaMActOperatorQCI
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support the establishment of EPS bearers with QCI in the range of 128…254.

typedef.name: TOaMActOperatorQCIGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the support of establishment of GBR EPS bearers with QCI in the range of 128…254.

typedef.name: TOaMActOptMmeSelection
typedef.comment: Activates the optimized MME selection algorithm If this parameter is set to “true”, the MME selection function distinguishes native and mapped GUMMEIs according to TS 23.401. If UE provides its (old) GUMMEI, the MME selection function based on GUMMEI is restricted to the corresponding RATs. If this parameter is set to “false”, the MME selection function does not distinguish native and mapped GUMMEIs. If UE provides its (old) GUMMEI, the MME selection function based on GUMMEI will consider all RATs.

typedef.name: TOaMActPdcpRohc
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the usage of PDCP Robust Header Compression.

typedef.name: TOaMActRIMforGSM
typedef.comment: The parameter activates the LTE498: RAN Information Management (RIM) for GSM feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActRLFbasedRCR
typedef.comment: Activates the feature 'Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC connection reestablishment (RCR)'

typedef.name: TOaMActRfChaining
typedef.comment: The parameter actRfChaining allows RF units chaining. That is, an optical fiber from the system module is chained via a RF unit to another RF unit.

typedef.name: TOaMActS1OlHandling
typedef.comment: This parameter activates the S1 Overload Handling feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActSelMobPrf
typedef.comment: The parameter activates the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles'.

typedef.name: TOaMActSrvccToGsm
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature "SRVCC from LTE to GSM".

typedef.name: TOaMActSrvccToWcdma
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the SRVCC from LTE to WCDMA feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActSubscriberTrace
typedef.comment: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Subscriber & Equipment Trace feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates if the 'Intra-LTE Inter-Frequency UE-based ANR' feature is activated by the operator.

typedef.name: TOaMActUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates if the 'Intra-LTE Intra-Frequency UE-based ANR' feature is activated by the operator.

typedef.name: TOaMActUeBasedAnrUtran
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates if the feature ''UE-based ANR for Inter-RAT UTRAN" neighbour cells is activated by the operator.

typedef.name: TOaMActUlCoMp
typedef.comment: Uplink coordinated multipoint (CoMP) reception activation for the eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMActZUC
typedef.comment: Controls optional ZUC ciphering and integrity protection algorithms. This parameter enables/disables optional ZUC ciphering algorithms.

typedef.name: TOaMActeNACCtoGSM
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature LTE442 Network Assisted Cell Change from LTE to GSM

typedef.name: TOaMAnrOmExtEnable
typedef.comment: Optional feature flag for feature LTE492 ANR support for LTE with O&M extension

typedef.name: TOaMDlSynchBoost
typedef.comment: Enables/Disables a fixed transmission power boost (factor 72/62) of the primary and secondary synchronization signal (PSS and SSS).

typedef.name: TOaMEnaDrxRepGra
typedef.comment: Enable/Disable the usage of the 'UE buffer status & aperiodic CQI reporting' grant.

typedef.name: TOaMEnaDrxWactDl
typedef.comment: Switch to enable/disable prioritization of UEs in DL scheduling depending on remaining DRX active time.

typedef.name: TOaMEnaDrxWactUl
typedef.comment: Enable/Disable of weighting factor for data radio bearer

typedef.name: TOaMEnaDrxWcqiDl
typedef.comment: Switch to enable/disable prioritization of UEs in DL scheduling depending on available channel quality feedback information during DRX.

typedef.name: TOaMEnablePhichCtrlUl
typedef.comment: The parameter enables/disables the improved PHICH control algorithm. If the parameter is 'False', the first uplink demodulation reference symbol which does not overlap with the contention-based Random Access Msg3 is selected. If the parameter is 'True', the uplink demodulation reference symbol is selected with the aim of an equal distribution among PHICH groups as well as the individual PHICH index for each UE per TTI. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMNullFallback
typedef.comment: This parameter determines whether a fallback to null ciphering caused by eNB limitations should be accepted (True) or not (False).

typedef.name: TOaMProhibitPsHOtoWcdma
typedef.comment: This parameter can be used to generally prohibit the execution of PS-handover towards WCDMA. If this parameter is set to "true", all UE will be send to WCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover. This parameter must be configured if handover to WCDMA is activated. Otherwise it is not needed.

member.name: pwsWithEmAreaId
member.comment: Indicates if the Public Warning Systems (ETWS and/or CMAS) make use of Emergency Area IDs. If ETWS or CMAS service is activated, then provision of this parameter is mandatory. If 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is true, then for each eNB cell provision of at least one 'Emergency Area ID' in the 'emAreaIdList' must be specified. If a warning message including 'Emergency Area IDs' is received by eNB and 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is 'false' then this warning message shall not be broadcasted by eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMRohcHdDecomOmodeEnable
typedef.comment: dis-/enable O-mode for header decompressor

typedef.name: TOaMTtiBundlingDuringHoMeas
typedef.comment: This parameter determines whether TTI bundling can be started via intra-cell handover while inter-frequency or inter-RAT measurements are ongoing.

typedef.name: TOaMUlSeqHop
typedef.comment: Defines if sequence hopping is enabled or disabled. Part of SIB2. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcAccuEnable
typedef.comment: Enables/disables the accumulation of PUSCH TPC commands. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMActBbuHotelling
typedef.comment: Defines usage of BBU hotelling feature.

typedef.name: TOaMActHOtoTdscdma
typedef.comment: This parameter enables the feature Handover from LTE to TD-SCDMA.

member.name: calibrationEnabled
member.comment: This flag Indicates whether to start or stop calibration.

typedef.name: TOaMProhibitPsHOtoTdscdma
typedef.comment: This parameter can be used to generally prohibit the execution of PS-handover towards TD-SCDMA. If this parameter is set to true all UE will be send to TD-SCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover. This parameter must be configured if handover to TD-SCDMA is activated. It is not needed otherwise.

typedef.name: TOaMSrsMaxUpPts
typedef.comment: Activation/deactivation of use of maximum srs bandwidth on UpPts. In TDD-LTE, only PRACH format 4 and srs is transmitted in upPTS. The parameter defines wether the srs bandwidth in upPTS is re-configured to fully utilize the bandwidth left by PRACH format 4. - if false, the bandwidth is defined by O&M parameter srsBwConf and srsBandwidthNonBf or srsBandwidthBf. - if true, the SRS bandwidth in upPTS is set to largest bandwidth defined in 3GPP TS36.211, table 5.5.3.2-1 to 5.5.3.2-4 in relation to chosen system bandwith (chBw).

typedef.name: TOaMActCellCapacityRes
typedef.comment: The parameter activates the feature LTE535: "Dedicated cell capacity per operator". The feature allows pre-reservation of cell resources in admission control per PLMN group.

typedef.name: TOaMActDlsOldtc
typedef.comment: Switch to activate/deactivate Outer Loop Delay Target Control (OLDTC) for voice in downlink time domain scheduling. OLDTC algorithm measures an actual scheduling delay of voice bearer in DL and compares it to a targeted delay. Then, if the measured delay is more than the target, UE priority is increased and in case the measured delay is below the target, the priority is decreased.

typedef.name: TOaMActDlsVoicePacketAgg
typedef.comment: Switch to activate/deactivate voice packet aggregation in downlink scheduler.

typedef.name: TOaMActDrx
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Parameter to activate or deactivate the DRX feature in a cell. Note for the case where periodic subband CQI reporting (periodicCqiFeedbackType) is enabled together with DRX functionality: It may not be possible to synchronize DRX start offset such that the wideband CQI report is received during the DRX OnDuration (due to periodicities) and that may cause small performance degradation in DL whenever fresh wideband channel quality information cannot be get in time. It is up to an operator whether to prevent activation of periodic subband CQI reporting and DRX in parallel because of this restriction. It is highly recommended to stay with DRX default values if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.
TDD specific comment: Parameter to activate or deactivate the DRX feature in a cell.

typedef.name: TOaMActFastMimoSwitch
typedef.comment: Enables "Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching" for Closed Loop MIMO modes based on PMI/RI reports sent by UEs if actFastMimoSwitch is set to TRUE. Enables "Dynamic MIMO Switching" if actFastMimoSwitch is set to FALSE. actFastMimoSwitch is set to TRUE: Activation of "Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching" "Fast adaptive MIMO Switching" supports fast rank selection and fast codebook based precoding of data transmission using closed loop feedback of precoding matrix indicator (PMI) in combination with rank indicator (RI). PMI and RI reporting delays shall be minimized by periodic and aperiodic reports sent by UEs in order to optimize PMI closed loop gains in combination with optimized rank selection. actFastMimoSwitch is set to FALSE: Activation of "Dynamic MIMO Switching" "Dynamic MIMO Switching" supports RI and CQI based rank selection after filtering of CQI and RI reports sent by the UE. "Dynamic MIMO Switching" is using RI and CQI thresholds for rank selection by comparison with filtered values. The threshold parameters "mimoClCqiThD", "mimoClCqiThU", "mimoClRiThD", "mimoClRiThU" are activated and used for rank switching.

typedef.name: TOaMActLdPdcch
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Activate or deactivate the load adaptive number of PDCCH symbols in a cell The actual OFDM symbol amount used for PDCCH in a TTI is selected from values between the minimum reasonable amount of symbols for the selected DL bandwidth and maximum allowed number of PDCCH symbols (maxNrSymPdcch). If dlChBw equals '3 MHz' it is recommended to set the parameter to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: Activate or deactivate the load adaptive number of PDCCH symbols in a cell The actual OFDM symbol amount used for PDCCH in a TTI is selected from values between the minimum reasonable amount of symbols for the selected DL bandwidth and maximum allowed number of PDCCH symbols (maxNrSymPdcch). For LTE TDD not every sub-frame need adaptive PDCCH symbol adjustment because not every sub-frame has PDSCH.

typedef.name: TOaMActNoIntraBandIFMeasurements
typedef.comment: For interfrequency load balancing neighbour frequencies within the same frequency band as the frequency of the own cell shall be excluded

typedef.name: TOaMActOlLaPdcch
typedef.comment: Activate / Deactivate Outer loop Link Adaptation for PDCCH O&M switch for activating / deactivating an additional Outer Loop Link Adaptation for PDCCH. This additional PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation controls the PDCCH link adaptation CQI shift such that the PDCCH and HARQ Response Target BLER is achieved when the OLQC Target BLER is achieved. If PDCCH OLLA is additionally based on PUSCH TX/DTX detection, PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation controls the PDCCH link adaptation CQI shift such that the PDCCH target BLER and PUSCH missed detection is achieved.

typedef.name: TOaMActOtdoa
typedef.comment: Activates the transmission of PRS signals according to the PRS configuration.

typedef.name: TOaMActPrsTxDiv
typedef.comment: If Tx Diversity is enabled for PRS transmission, then precoding vector switching will be used and therefore all configured Tx antennas will be used for the transmission of the PRS signal. If Tx diversity is disabled then the PRS signal will just be transmitted on a single antenna (the physical antenna corresponding to antenna port {0}).

typedef.name: TOaMActPuschMask
typedef.comment: Activates PUSCH masking

typedef.name: TOaMActQci1eVTT
typedef.comment: Activates the feature 'Extended VoLTE talk time'

typedef.name: TOaMActSixIfMeasurements
typedef.comment: The parameter allow to extend the number of interfrequency measurements from 3 to 6

typedef.name: TOaMActSmartDrx
typedef.comment: Parameter to activate/deactivate the Smart DRX feature in a cell.

typedef.name: TOaMActSuperCell
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Activates the transmission of duplicated data streams via different RRHs in downlink, and the combination of uplink signals received from different RRHs. The super cell configurations can just be applied in 10 MHz cell bandwidth configurations, that is LNCEL "dlChBw" and "ulChBw" parameters are configured to 10 MHz. Super cell configurations are not released in conjunction with RF sharing and Repeater Interface Units.
TDD specific comment: Activates the transmission of duplicated data streams via different RRHs in downlink, and the combination of uplink signals received from different RRHs. All cell instances in the eNB shall be configured with same for actSuperCell value.

typedef.name: TOaMActTtiBundling
typedef.comment: Parameter to activate or deactivate the TTI Bundling feature in a cell.

typedef.name: TOaMActUlGrpHop
typedef.comment: Activates uplink group hopping in PUSCH and PUCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMCqiAperEnable
typedef.comment: O&M switch for enabling / disabling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI reporting on PUSCH.

typedef.name: TOaMCqiPerSimulAck
typedef.comment: O&M switch for enabling / disabling simultaneous transmission of periodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback and HARQ ACK/NACK on PUCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMDeltaTfEnabled
typedef.comment: Enabling/disabling of the transport format dependent offset on a per UE basis. If this parameter is "true", PUSCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1) takes the Transport Block size in account during the power calculation.

typedef.name: TOaMDl64QamEnable
typedef.comment: Enables/disables downlink 64 QAM modulation for link adaptation use in PDSCH.

typedef.name: TOaMDlInterferenceEnable
typedef.comment: The parameter dlInterferenceEnable is used for enabling and disabling interference generation in downlink.

typedef.name: TOaMDlOlqcEnable
typedef.comment: O&M switch for enabling / disabling downlink Outer loop Link Quality Control which is acting based on the 1st transmission HARQ result, that is, 1st transmission BLER.

typedef.name: TOaMDlamcEnable
typedef.comment: O&M switch for enabling / disabling downlink Adaptive Modulation and Coding.

typedef.name: TOaMDrxApplyDeviceType
typedef.comment: This parameter determines whether the device type "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt" of the UE shall be considered for DRX configuration. Such an UE does not foresee to particularly benefit from NW-based battery consumption optimisation. If drxApplyDeviceType is set to "APPLY" and the device type is "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt", DRX will not be activated for this UE.

typedef.name: TOaMEnableAmcPdcch
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the switch for enable/disable Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) based Adaptive Modulation and Coding (AMC) for PDCCH link adaptation. If the parameter is disabled, default aggregation is used implicitly.

typedef.name: TOaMEnableBetterCellHo
typedef.comment: Flag if better cell HO is enabled.

typedef.name: TOaMEnableCovHo
typedef.comment: Flag if coverage HO is enabled.

typedef.name: TOaMEnableDl16Qam
typedef.comment: The parameter defines if downlink Link Adaptation is allowed to select the 16QAM modulation for PDSCH.

typedef.name: TOaMEnableLowAgg
typedef.comment: The parameter determines the enabling/disabling switch for automatic selection of lower aggregation during PDCCH scheduling. This means that a required aggregation level which is defined from UE's Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) reports may be downgraded by one step without any other particular reason (e.g. blocking due to UE hash function or overall space). Assigning of lower aggregation decreases number of blocked UEs in case of PDCCH resource deficiency, and gives possibility for greater number of PDCCH messages per TTI. A corresponding increase in PDCCH power compensates caused degradation in PDCCH code robustness. There are some restrictions for utilitizing the automatic lower aggregation for an UE: - the required aggregation shall be at least 4, - enableAmcPdcch and enablePcPdcch shall be enabled, and - used PDCCH capacity for all uplink and downlink allocations shall exceed a limit defined by the threshold pdcchLowAggTh of total PDCCH capacity for allocated number of PDCCH symbols in TTI The parameter will be ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

typedef.name: TOaMEnablePcPdcch
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the switch for enabling / disabling power control on PDCCH. If the parameter is disabled, a flat downlink Power Spectral Density (PSD) is used.

typedef.name: TOaMIntraPresAntP
typedef.comment: Indicates whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

typedef.name: TOaMPrachHsFlag
typedef.comment: High speed flag for PRACH preamble generation determines whether an unrestricted or a restricted set has to be used by the UE. false = Unrestricted; true = Restricted

typedef.name: TOaMRcEnableDl
typedef.comment: The parameter switches the rate capping functionality on/off in downlink direction. Rate capping functionality in downlink restricts non-GBR (non-Guaranteed Bit Rate) radio bearers bitrate to AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate).

typedef.name: TOaMRcEnableUl
typedef.comment: Enabling/disabling of rate capping in uplink.

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwEnDl
typedef.comment: The parameter switches Restricted RB Assignment functionality on/off in the downlink direction. When the functionality is enabled, the UE-specific PRB assignment is restricted to a limit defined in the redBwMaxRbDl parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwRpaEnUl
typedef.comment: Enabling/disabling the restricted PRB assignment functionality in uplink.

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwSgbEnUl
typedef.comment: Enables/disables a pre-provisioned set of soft guard bands for uplink bandwidth reduction. Parameter modification requires object (cell) locking.

typedef.name: TOaMRiEnable
typedef.comment: Determines whether RI reporting is enabled (true) or not (false).

typedef.name: TOaMSrsSimAckNack
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Determines if SRS and ACK/NACK are allowed (enabled) to be transfered simultaneously.
TDD specific comment: Activates/Deactivates SRS and Ack/Nack simultaneous transmission. If this parameter is set to true, in uplink the transmission of srs and ack/nack is allowed in the same TTI.

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcAllTbEn
typedef.comment: O&M switch for enabling/disabling the counting of all Transport Blocks instead of the 1st transmission Transport Blocks for defining uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inner loop factor (UEs in non-TTI bundling mode), BLER measurements (UEs in TTI bundling mode).

typedef.name: TOaMAct1TxIn2Tx
typedef.comment: This is to activate RRH path scalability when one 2pipe RRH used as 2 1pipe virtual RRHs

typedef.name: TOaMActBfFallback
typedef.comment: Active/deactive the functionality of beamforming fallbacking If actBfFallback is set to true, fallback functionality from beamforming to TxDiv is activated based on the thresholds defined in mimoBfslCqiThD and mimoBfslCqiThU.

typedef.name: TOaMActCsiRsSubFNonTM9Sch
typedef.comment: Activate non-TM9 UEs to be scheduled in CSI-RSI sub-frames. Limit by current simulation result: - Non-TM9 UEs will only use single stream to transmit in CSI-RS sub-frames. - TM7 UEs can not be scheduled in CSI-RS sub-frames if csiRsSubfrConf is not TDD specific rsc20, rsc21 nor rsc22.

typedef.name: TOaMActPdcchLoadGen
typedef.comment: This parameter controls the activation or deactivation of "Inter cell load generation for PDCCH".

typedef.name: TOaMActReduceWimaxInterference
typedef.comment: Activates reduced WiMax interference.

typedef.name: TOaMActTm8MuMimo
typedef.comment: Parameter to activate or deactivate TM8 MU-MIMO in a cell

typedef.name: TOaMActTmSwitch
typedef.comment: Activate or deactivate the dynamic transmission mode switch function

typedef.name: TOaMActUlMuMimo
typedef.comment: This parameter activates feature LTE1545 "UL MU MIMO 8RX".

typedef.name: TOaMActUpPtsBlanking
typedef.comment: Activates UpPTS blanking.

typedef.name: TOaMSrsActivation
typedef.comment: Activates/Deactivates srs (sounding reference symbol) feature in Cell.

typedef.name: TOaMSrsOnTwoSymUpPts
typedef.comment: Active/deactive srs transmission on 2 symbols of UpPts. If srsOnTwoSymUpPts is set to true, then srs transmission on 2 symbols of UpPTS is allowed. If srsOnTwoSymUpPts is set to false, then the transmission of srs in two symbols of upPTS is not allowed. This parameter is only used in case srs periodicity of Ue is set to 2ms.

typedef.name: TOaMLnhohHrpdPreRegAllowed
typedef.comment: Defines whether the eNodeB and MME support preregistration and handover procedures to an evolved High Rate Packet Data (eHRPD) RAN. This parameter is used in Measurement Configuration of eHRPD neighbors in RRC CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMLnhoifInterPresAntP
typedef.comment: The IE PresenceAntennaPort1 is used to indicate whether all the neighbouring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighbouring cells.

typedef.name: TOaMRemoveAllowed
typedef.comment: Inhibits autonomous removal of the neighbor relation by eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMMhaActive
typedef.comment: Defines is MHA AISG MHA or Non-AISG MHA. Selectable values is 0 (false)= Non-AISG MHA and 1 (true )= AISG MHA .

typedef.name: TOaMMhaAlarmDetection
typedef.comment: Determines whether alarm detection is used or not. The options are 0 (false) and 1 (true). Default values for Non-AISG MHAs and AISG MHAs in passive mode: 1 Default values for AISG and third party MHAs:0 Note: Configurable MHA alarms are allowed only for passive MHAs

typedef.name: TOaMAutoAdapt
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter offers the possibility to use existing LNCEL configuration as default mobility profile. autoAdapt parameter is considered when MODPR applies. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to true then MODPR applies only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID or when no SPID is assigned to the UE. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to false then MODPR applies for all UEs. If autoAdapt is set to 'true' (value of LNBTS-actSelMobPrf does not matter): - the HO frequency lists defined in LNADJL, LNADJW and LNADJG objects are used instead of MODPR configuration. Frequency layers of newly created LNADJL, LNADJW and LNADJG objects are automatically included in the default profile. - REDRT configuration of the corresponding cell is used instead of MODRED configuration. MODRED , if present, is not considered - IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration and serving carrier of the corresponding cell are used instead of MODIMP. - MODIMP, if present, is not considered Note: Measurements are done only for adjacent objects (LNADJx) that are referred by a relationship object (LNRELx) with a frequency configured in the corresponding handover object (LNHOx). If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to true and autoAdapt is set to 'false' : - MODPR, MODRED and MODIMP configuration is used for HO mobility, redirection and Idle Mobility reconfiguration. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to false and autoAdapt is set to 'false' : - MODPR configuration is used for HO mobility - MODRED and MODIMP configurations are never used. REDRT, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration are always used instead.
TDD specific comment: This parameter offers the possibility to use existing LNCEL configuration as default mobility profile. autoAdapt parameter is considered when MODPR applies. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to true then MODPR applies only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID or when no SPID is assigned to the UE. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to false then MODPR applies for all UEs. If autoAdapt is set to 'true' (value of LNBTS-actSelMobPrf does not matter): - the HO frequency lists defined in LNADJL, LNADJW, LNADJT and LNADJG objects are used instead of MODPR configuration. Frequency layers of newly created LNADJL, LNADJW, LNADJT and LNADJG objects are automatically included in the default profile. - REDRT configuration of the corresponding cell is used instead of MODRED configuration. MODRED , if present, is not considered - IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration and serving carrier of the corresponding cell are used instead of MODIMP. - MODIMP, if present, is not considered Note: Measurements are done only for adjacent objects (LNADJx) that are referred by a relationship object (LNRELx) with a frequency configured in the corresponding handover object (LNHOx). If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to true and autoAdapt is set to 'false' : - MODPR, MODRED and MODIMP configuration is used for HO mobility, redirection and Idle Mobility reconfiguration. If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to false and autoAdapt is set to 'false' : - MODPR configuration is used for HO mobility - MODRED and MODIMP configurations are never used. REDRT, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration are always used instead.

typedef.name: TOaMActEthernetSec
typedef.comment: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature "Security for Ethernet" Note for FSMr3 hardware: The reconfiguration of the parameter may lead to a temporary loss of the connection.

typedef.name: TOaMAutoConfBlocked
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates if Auto Configuration is allowed or blocked by a local installer working at the site.

typedef.name: TOaMCommissioningRequired
typedef.comment: Multiradio Flexi BTS creates this parameter with value True when it is ready for Auto Configuration. This parameter is relevant only when Multiradio Flexi BTS is not commissioned.

typedef.name: TOaMResetToTestDedicated
typedef.comment: This parameter indicates if Multiradio Flexi BTS should automatically go to the "Test Dedicated" state in start-up.

typedef.name: TOaMCellTrcMode
typedef.comment: This indicates the status of the cell trace session i.e. whether the cell trace session is enabled or disabled. Note: This parameter currently should only be set to enabled (i.e. TRUE).

typedef.name: TOaMRetActive
typedef.comment: Defines is RET AISG RET or Non-AISG RET. Selectable values is 0 (false)= Siemens AISG1.1, TMARET RET, Siemens proprietary AISG1.1 RET and 1 (true )= 3GPP RET. Note: A modification might lead in loosing control over the RET device when the AISG support is different.

typedef.name: TOaMCalibrate
typedef.comment: Exercise the antenna drive unit over its entire range of travel to ensure fault-free operation, and synchronize the measured and actual beam tilt of the antenna. Calibration of a RET device might take up-to 4 minutes according to 3GPP stardards. A typical time for the calibration is approximately 1-2 minutes. According to 3GPP standards, calibration of several devices connected onto one antenna line is done as a series of consecutive operations by the system. In addition, calibration and set tilt (for more details of set tilt, see set tilt parameter documentation) are done as consecutive operations. When such situation occurs, accumulative time for the operations may be increased long enough as to not be feasible to be activated in one plan. Thus, in such case, time consuming operations should be devided into 2 or more plans. Note: The maximum calibration time is 30minutes.

typedef.name: TOaMCalibrationDone
typedef.comment: This parameter defines if Calibration has been done

typedef.name: TOaMConfigFileDlNeeded
typedef.comment: Defines if a Configuration File DL is needed.

typedef.name: TOaMConfigurationDone
typedef.comment: This parameter defines if the Configuration has been done.

typedef.name: TOaMRModGpsInUse
typedef.comment: Defines that synchronization signal from GPS connected to radio module is delivered via RP3-01 interface to the system module.

typedef.name: TOaMSyncMaster
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: A module which oscillator is used for source of the BTS site system clock. Other module(s) in a BTS are synch slave(s). The synchronization master depends on the RF sharing technologies. In 2G-LTE concurrent mode, EUTRA (LTE) is supported as synchronization master, where in 3G-LTE concurrent mode UTRAN (WCDMA) is the synchronization master.
TDD specific comment: A module which oscillator is used for source of the BTS site system clock. Other module(s) in a BTS are synch slave(s). Only EUTRA (LTE) is supported as synchronization master in 2G-LTE concurrent mode.

typedef.name: TOaMExtDualModeSyncMaster
typedef.comment: Defines whether external Dual Mode synchronization master exists. In Dual Mode configuration synchronization is delivered to NSN EUTRA from UTRA (any vendor) through Ir router via CPRI interface. If this parameter is set 'true' then EUTRA works as a synchronization slave and synchronization comes via CPRI. If it is set 'false' then either another parameter defines the synchronization role (e.g. syncMaster) or synchronization master may be found during RP3 autodetection. This parameter is required because autodetection of the synchronization role (master or slave) is either not possible in CPRI or synchronization master is a third party system module. Hence the synchronization role shall be set explicitly by an operator.

typedef.name: TOaMAuthIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines the authentication mode included indicator. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMDayLt
typedef.comment: Defines the Daylight Savings Time (DST) indicator. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in the RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the dayLtIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.

typedef.name: TOaMDayLtIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines whether the Daylight Savings Time (DST) indicator is included. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in the RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMHomeRegIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines whether the homeReg parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMImsiTSupported
typedef.comment: Defines whether 15-digit IMSI_T addressing is supported. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMLeapSecondIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines whether the lpSec parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMLocaltimeOffIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines whether the ltmOff parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMPilotIncIncluded
typedef.comment: Defines whether the pilotInc parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrprtEnableAnrProfile
typedef.comment: The parameter enables ANR learning for the carrier frequency of the profile.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrPrLId
typedef.comment: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRL object. An Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (ANRPRL) defines carrier-frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of LTE intra-frequency and inter-frequency neighbor cells.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrThresRSRPNbCell
typedef.comment: If RSRP of a neighbor cell included in ANR measurement "reportStrongestCells" is greater than anrThresRSRPNbCell, then a cell is accepted by eNB as a neighbor cell for which CGI is needed. The parameter is relevant only if at least one of the features; LTE782 or LTE556, is activated, that is if actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte and/or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to "true".

typedef.name: TOaMAnrThresRSRPNbCellMobEv
typedef.comment: Threshold to control detection of neighbour cells via passive ANR. If a measurement report for the mobility events A3, A4 or A5 is received, then the cell corresponding to an included PCI can be accepted as 'candidate cell for ANR' only if the PCI fulfills the condition: RSRP(PCI) > anrThres RSRPNbCellMobEv. The parameter is only relevant if at least one of the features LTE492, LTE782 or LTE556 is activated, i.e. if anrOmExtEnable or actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to 'true'. Passive ANR can be switched off by setting the threshold to a very high value.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrThresRSRQNbCell
typedef.comment:
The eNB will request to resolve the CGI of unknown cells only if the respective RSRQ level measured by the UE is at least equal to anrThresRSRQNbCell. The parameter is relevant only if at least one of the features; LTE782 or LTE556, is activated, that is if actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte and/or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to "true".
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMNrLimitInterFreq
typedef.comment: Once the number of LTE inter-frequency neighbor relations of the eNB cell reaches "nrLimitInterFreq", the eNB stops autonomous learning of new neighbor cells via ANR. Note: The number of inter-frequency neighbor relations can exceed this limit since new neighbor cells/new neighbor relations still can be configured via O&M and autonomous creation of neighbor relations for already available neighbor cells might occur.

typedef.name: TOaMNrLimitIntraFreq
typedef.comment: Once the number of LTE intra-frequency neighbor relations of the eNB cell reaches "nrLimitIntraFreq", the eNB stops autonomous learning of new neighbor cells via ANR. Note: The number of intra-frequency neighbor relations can exceed this limit since new neighbor cells/new neighbor relations still can be configured via O&M and autonomous creation of neighbor relations for already available neighbor cells might occur.

member.name: targetCarrierFreq
member.comment: The parameter identifies the EUTRA target carrier frequency for which this ANR profile applies. The profile applies for intra- and or inter-frequency ANR dependent on the carrier frequency of the cell. If no target carrier is defined, the profile applies for any frequency which is measured by a UE. This profile is considered as default profile and must exist in any case. If an ANRPRL instance with a dedicated carrier frequency exists, this has higher priority than the default profile. Note that ANR measurements will be only activated in a cell if an LNHOIF object is created for each relevant target carrier frequency.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrPrWId
typedef.comment: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRW object. An Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (ANRPRW) defines carrier-frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of WCDMA neighbor cells.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrUtraEcNoThres
typedef.comment: It defines the minimum EcNo level measured by the UE from a UTRAcell required for ordering its CGI decoding. (Mapping between the UE measured EcNo and the SFS values is according to 3GPP TS 25.133/25.123).

member.name: anrUtraRscpThres
member.comment: It defines the minimum power level that a UE should report from a measured UTRA cell for considering the corresponding PCI, respectively PSC, as a possible UTRA neighbor cell candidate. (Mapping between the UE measured RSCP and the SFS values is according to 3GPP TS 25.133/25.123) The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133: * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

member.name: cellsToApplyList
member.comment: The parameter allows to restrict the ANR profile to certain LTE cells that are identified by their lncelId. If the parameter is omitted or the list is empty the profile is considered as default profile, which applies to all cells with no dedicated profile.

typedef.name: TOaMLnRelWLimitForAnr
typedef.comment: The parameter allows limiting the number of WCDMA neighbor relations (LNRELW instances) per UTRAN carrier frequency and LTE cell. This limit applies only for ANR created LNRELW instances but does not apply for LNRELW instances, which are manually created via plan file. If the limit is already reached or even exceeded by manually created LNRELW instances, no additional LNRELW instances referring to WCDMA neighbor cells with the profile carrier frequency will be added by ANR. If the number of neighbor relations (LNRELW instances) exceeds the maximum number of WCDMA neighbor cells which might be used by eNB in measurement configurations (limit in 3GPP 36.331) but the limit which ich configured with lnRelWLimitForAnr is not yet reached, then eNB will create new LNLRELW instances with handoverAllowed set to 'forbidden'. This is to ease further manual optimization of neighbour cell blacklisting.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrprwUtraCarrierFreq
typedef.comment: The parameter identifies the UTRA carrier frequency for which this ANR profile applies.

member.name: additionalRxGain
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional Rx gain in decibels, is used in gain calculation to compensate an Rx gain produced by an external device e.g. the base station when two radio modules are cross-connected together via Rx diversity outputs sharing the antenna line. User will know the gain produced by the external device to apply proper value here. Note: an MHA/TMA gain will not be included in this parameter. The MHA/TMA gain is commissioned together with the MHA/TMA device commissioning and taken into account as default by the system.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: Additional Rx gain in decibels, is used in Gain calculation to compensate a Rx gain produced by an external device e.g. the base station when two radio modules are cross-connected together via RX diversity outputs sharing the antenna line. User shall know the gain produced by the external device to apply proper value here. Note: an MHA/TMA gain shall not be included in this parameter. The MHA/TMA gain is commissioned together with the MHA/TMA device commissioning and taken into account as default by the system.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMAntennaRoundTripDelay
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The total delay of all the passive units of an antenna line can be entered into this parameter, which is then used as the RTT value in delay compensation in BTS.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The total delay of all the passive units of an antenna line can be entered into this parameter, which is then used as the RTT value instead of calculating the value using the BTS Site Manager.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMAntennaTotalLoss
typedef.comment:

member.name: ulDelay
member.comment: Antenna Line Uplink Delay in nanoseconds, is used to compensate the antenna line UL delay difference between main and diversity Rx branches of the cell. This is needed to avoid gain (i.e. performance) loss due to the time difference between Rx branches data. For example, offset of 1/2 chip period (130ns) introduces diversity gain degradation of about 1dB. Different delays are met e.g. when two radio modules are cross-connected together via RX diversity outputs. User may provide absolute UL delay values for all Rx branches of the cell, or optionally only the positive difference referred to the smallest delay branch and leave smallest delay branch value to zero. It's not required to apply the UL delay when the delay for Rx branches of the cell are about equal. Note: Multiradio Combiner (MRC) delay shall not be included in this parameter. The MRC delays are taken into account as default by the system when the Multiradio Combiner is commissioned into use.

member.name: gpsTotalAntennaLineDelay
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter will be specified when NSN official cable (30m, 100m or 300m) is replaced with an own proprietary cable between GPS receiver and eNB. The maximum length of cable will be less than 400 meters. In this case an operator is obliged to measure the delay of cable. If this parameter is set, the value for gpsCableLength will not be set.
TDD specific comment: Specifies the time delay between the GPS receiver and the 1pps sync input at the eNB (used for delay compensation at the eNB). Alternative usage is in BBU hotelling feature to compensate 1pps signal total delay between synchronization bus master 1pps output to slave sync input. This parameter shall be specified when either NSN official cable (30m, 100m or 200) is replaced with an own proprietary cable between GPS receiver and eNB. The maximum length of cable between GPS receiver and eNB shall be less than 400 meters. In this case an operator has obliged to measure the delay of cable. If this parameter is set then value for gpsCableLength shall not be set.

typedef.name: TOaMPpsTimingOffset

Different systems could have difference in the frame synchronization to GPS PPS timing pulse. This parameter gives possiblity to adjust freely an air interface timing as for 1PPS synchronization pulse.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMCaRelId
typedef.comment: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CAREL. It uniquely identifies a CAREL instance. CAREL creation activates Carrier Aggregation in the related cells. CAREL is created in the LNCEL that will be P-LNCEL (primary cell for Carrier Aggregation). LNCEL contains lcrId of the S-LNCEL (secondary cell for Carrier Aggregation). Depending on enableAutoLock and enableGrflShdn settings, LNCEL is automatically locked during plan activation for CAREL creation/deletion.

typedef.name: TOaMCaSchedFairFact
typedef.comment:
This parameter controls scheduling fairness between UEs with and without activated SCell (S-LNCEL). This parameter controls scheduling fairness in DL time and frequency domain scheduling between UEs with and without an active SCell. Value 0 means that no fairness is provided; that is UEs with an SCell activated get maximal benefits; and value 1 means that full fairness is provided that is UEs with and without an active SCell will be treated similarly. The pair of cells that are aggregated should have the same setting for this parameter.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMCarelLcrId
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter is the Local Cell Resource ID of cell to be aggregated. Aggregate cells considering the following: - NSN does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is an NSN supported band combination but not supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 - NSN does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is an NSN supported band combination and supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 but the channel bandwidths of the cells are not supported by 3GPP in this band combination (section 5.6A.1 in TS 36.101).
TDD specific comment: This parameter is the Local Cell Resource ID of cell to be aggregated. Aggregate cells considering the following: - NSN does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is an NSN supported band combination but not supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 - NSN does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is an NSN supported band combination and supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 but the channel bandwidths of the cells are not supported by 3GPP in this band combination (section 5.6A.1 in TS 36.101).

member.name: idleLBGeranCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of GERAN carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnAdjId values if an LNADJ instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features. typedef.name: TOaMLnadjwUTargetCid
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: UTRAN Cell-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC and is required (together with the RNC ID) for the Source RNC To Target RNC Transparent Container IE in the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN. The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).
TDD specific comment: UTRAN Cell-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC and is required (together with the RNC ID) for the Source RNC To Target RNC Transparent Container IE in the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN.

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjwUTargetFreq
typedef.comment: Target Frequency Target Frequency provides the DL Carrier Frequency of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the primary scrambling code identifies a neighboring UTRAN cell

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjwUTargetLac

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjwUTargetRac
typedef.comment: Target Routing Area Code UtranTarget_RAC provides the Routing Area Code identifying the Routing Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjwUTargetRncId
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. Values in the range of 4096 .. 65535 are considered as Extended RNC-ID. It uniqely identifies a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN and is required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN. The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).
TDD specific comment: UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniqely identifies a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN and is required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrUtraInactivityTimer
typedef.comment: It defines the minimum UE inactivity time period before triggering UE-based UTRAN ANR measurements. This timer applies to UE-capable of UTRAN ANR measurements when the respective feature (LTE908) is enabled. When LTE908 is enabled, "tInactiveUtraAn" preceeds any other inactivity timer (for example "drxDedInactivityT" or "tInactive").

typedef.name: TOaMB1SupervisionOffset
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the offset value for calculation of the maximum waiting time for "CSFB with PS-HO" related B1 measurement reports. If the supervision timer expires eNB will trigger CS Fallback with redirection to GERAN or UTRAN depending on configuration. The value 0ms is not recommended as then B1 supervision timer might always expire. The B1 supervision time is calculated by adding the offset value to the frequency specific time to trigger value of the related LNHOW/LNHOT object: B1 supervision time = b1TimeToTriggerCSFBUtraMeas + b1SupervisionOffset IMPORTANT: The value range has been extended from max 1000ms to 10000ms due to I&V purposes only. In the customer release the default value shall be less than 1001ms

typedef.name: TOaMCaMinDlAmbr
typedef.comment: This parameter excludes those UEs from carrier aggregation, whose UE-AMBR Downlink is below the caMinDlAmbr threshold .

typedef.name: TOaMConsecHoFailThres
typedef.comment: If for a LTE Neighbour Relation (NR) 'consecHoFailThres' consecutive handover execution failures are observed, then the eNB triggers a re-validation for this NR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed). If 'consecHoFailThres=0', then no re-validation is triggered. Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same NR has expired.

typedef.name: TOaMCqiAperPollT

typedef.name: TOaMCqiCompSmRi1Cl

CQI compensation for DL AMC in case of Closed Loop MIMO SM mode is used and RI with value 1 is received The parameter defines the CQI compensation value for DL AMC when Spatial Multiplexing transmission mode is used but Rank Indication of 1 is received from the UE. Applicable when the Closed Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing has been configured to use i.e. when dlMimoMode parameter is 'Closed Loop Mimo'. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

Applicable in the case when Closed Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing has been configured to use i.e. when the dlMimoMode parameter is 'Closed Loop Mimo'. This parameter is vendor-specific.
