The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMDlOlqcDeltaCqiStepUp
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the increase in CQI offset for a HARQ ACK response in Outer Loop Link Quality Control (OLQC) for downlink. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMDlamcTHistCqi
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time in TTIs for which historical CQI is remembered in the downlink Adaptive Modulation and Coding algorithms. The default CQI (dlamcCqiDef) is used after the timer expiry. This is a vendor-specific parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMDlsFdPfSchAvgC
typedef.comment: Averaging constant for calculation of the scheduled rate for the PFsch frequency domain scheduler. Parameter is not applicable with other frequency domain scheduling algorithms.

typedef.name: TOaMDlsOldtcStepUp
typedef.comment:
Adaptation step up for Outer Loop Delay Target Control. In case voice bearer scheduling is performed within a targeted delay, the delay correction factor is increased by this step size up. The parameter is not applicable if dlsOldtcEnable is set to false.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMDlsTputAvgT
typedef.comment: This is a time averaging constant for the equal throughput criterion in downlink. The mean throughput of the data radio bearer is defined over this time constant.

typedef.name: TOaMDrbIdThreshold
typedef.comment: DRB Identity Threshold If the number of unused DRB identities is less than this threshold, eNB will trigger an intra-cell handover to refresh security keys.

typedef.name: TOaMEmergencyArp
typedef.comment: The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. The ARP priority levels 1-8 should only be assigned to resources for services that are authorized to receive prioritized treatment within an operator domain (i.e. that are authorized by the serving network). The ARP priority levels 9-15 may be assigned to resources that are authorized by the home network and thus applicable when a UE is roaming. (taken from 3GPP TS23.203)

member.name: etwsPrimNotifBcDur
member.comment: Duration during which an ETWS primary Notification is broadcasted. As the broadcast parameter delivered with Write-Replace Warning Request are not to be used for ETWS primary notification (SIB10), the broadcast duration has to be administered.

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsHopBwPusch
typedef.comment: This is the number of PRBs used for PUSCH hopping. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMHysteresisLoadDlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the hysteresis when measuring DL GBR resource load unbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available DL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMHysteresisLoadPDCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the hysteresis when measuring PDCCH load unbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMHysteresisLoadPUCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the hysteresis when measuring PUCCH load unbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available PUCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMHysteresisLoadUlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the hysteresis when measuring UL GBR resource load unbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available UL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMIFLBA4ActLim
typedef.comment: Maximum number of UEs per cell that have iF-LB A4 measurements activated at a time.

typedef.name: TOaMIFLBLoadFilCoeff
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the filter coefficient for the all inter-frequency load balancing load measurements (exponential filter). Value 0 equals filter smoothing factor 1. Value 1 -> 0.84. Value 2 -> 0.707. ... Value 19 -> 0.037

typedef.name: TOaMIlMinDatvolUl
typedef.comment: This is the minimum data volume transferred by a dummy grant.

typedef.name: TOaMKeyRefrMarg
typedef.comment: Defines a threshold for PDCP COUNT supervision. If the remaining COUNT space becomes less than this threshold, the eNB key hierarchy should be refreshed.

typedef.name: TOaMLnBtsId
typedef.comment: Instance identifier of object Macro eNB and used also as telecom parameter of the 3GPP 'Macro eNB ID', which is part of Global eNB ID. In addition it appears as distinguished name (DN) in the planning data at the Element Manager.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxMRnoPciToResolve
typedef.comment: It defines the number of consecutive measurement reports without LTE (intra-frequency or inter-frequency) PCIs to resolve that the eNB cell must receive before disabling Active ANR.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxMRnoUtraPciToResolve
typedef.comment: This parameter configures the maximum number of consecutive ReportStrongestCellsForSon measurements without unknown UTRA PCI, respectively PSCs, received on a given UTRAN carrier frequency before entering the Slow Search state.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumOfLnadjLimit
typedef.comment: Configures the overall number of LNADJ instances (enbControlled + oamControlled) to be supported. Note: For FSMr2 HW and for FZM the value shall not exceed 128. For FSMr3 HW there is no hardware specific limitation. The parameter shall never be configured to a value higher than the system informs in parameter supportedNumOfLnadj.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumPrbSr
typedef.comment: Maximum number of PRBs on request by SR Defines a) the maximum number of PRBs in case of RR scheduler in FD b) the number of PRBs in case of the exhaustive FD scheduler which shall be assigned to a UE without QCI=1 bearer on request of a Scheduling Request

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumPreEmptions
typedef.comment: This parameter limits the number of pre-emptions which the admission of a set of E-RABs (for example at initial context setup, E-RAB setup, handover request) might cause. If this number gets exceeded for an E-RAB set, the admission of this set set will partly or completely fail. Because each pre-emption takes at least 5ms (but might take more, depending on eNB load), the pre-emption number limitation should be considered carefully to avoid timeouts of procedures which depend on E-RAB admission (in particular handover preperations).

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumX2LinksIn
typedef.comment: If the number of eNB-controlled X2-links reaches 'maxNumX2LinksIn', then the eNB shall stop accepting establishment requests for new eNB-controlled X2-links from neighbour eNBs

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumX2LinksOut
typedef.comment: If the number of eNB-controlled X2-links reaches 'maxNumX2LinksOut', then the eNB shall stop the automatic establishment of new eNB-controlled X2-links

typedef.name: TOaMMaxS1ResetRetries
typedef.comment: The maximum number of times that the eNB shall repeat the attempt to reset the S1 interface in case earlier attempts were unsuccessful.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxS1SetRetry
typedef.comment: The maximum number of times that the eNB should attempt to set up the S1 interface without success. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxX2ResRetry
typedef.comment: The maximum number of times that the eNB should attempt to reset the X2 interface without success. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxX2SetRetry
typedef.comment: The maximum number of times that the eNB should attempt to setup the X2 interface without success. The parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMMcc
typedef.comment: Primary Mobile Country Code of eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMMimoClCqiAvg
typedef.comment:
Averaging filter constant for closed loop CQI measurements (not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true') This parameter is vendor specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMimoClCqiComp
typedef.comment:
CQI Compensation applied to closed loop CQI Measurements when reported RI=2 (in CQI). The reported CQI in the closed loop dual codeword transmission case is smaller than for a single codeword transmission. With this compensation, a normalization towards a single codeword case is obtained. This parameter is vendor specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMimoClRiAvg
typedef.comment:
Averaging filter constant for closed loop Rank measurements (not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true') This parameter is vendor specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMimoOlCqiAvg
typedef.comment:
Averaging filter constant for Open Loop CQI measurements.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMimoOlCqiComp
typedef.comment:
CQI compensation applied to CQI measurements when reported RI=2 (in CQI). The reported CQI in Open Loop Spatial Multiplexing case is smaller than for the diversity transmission. With this compensation a normalization towards diversity is obtained.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMimoOlRiAvg
typedef.comment:
Averaging filter constant for Open Loop Rank measurements.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMinNotActivatedUtraRSCFS
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the minimum time interval that should elapse since the last search of possible unknown PCIs, respectively PSCs, on a UTRAN carrier frequency, before re-intiating a new search on that carrier. Via this parameter, it is possible to control the minimum frequency according which a UTRAN carrier frequency in slow search mode is scanned for potential new neighbor cell detection. If value "0" is selected, the respective UTRAN carrier frequency will always be in fast Active search.

typedef.name: TOaMMnc
typedef.comment: This is the primary Mobile Network Code of the eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMMncLength
typedef.comment: This parameter determines the range of the primary MNC of the eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMNCqiDtx
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the number of consecutive CQI DTX detections causing radio link failure indication. Special value 0 means that the feature is disabled. The parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMNCqiRec
typedef.comment: The parameter defines number of consecutive CQI non-DTX detections causing radio link failure recovery indication. The parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMNHO
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the number of HO events over which to average the number of successful HOs from an eNB cell towards its intra-frequency neighbors, when a HO event to any of these neighbors happens. Such average function provides one criterium to select the most suitable neighbor cell for traffic offloading

typedef.name: TOaMNRimRirG
typedef.comment: The maximum number of attempted (re-)transmissions for a specific RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU without success.

typedef.name: TOaMNumOfUEforIntraLB
typedef.comment: Defines the maximum number of UEs to be requested for load balancing by adaptation of cell individual offsets. Cell-Boundaries between an overloaded cell served by source-eNB and an underloaded cell served by target-eNB is shifted so that UEs in the hysteresis region between the two cells will be handed over earlier to the closer underloaded target-cell. The above is achieved by adapting the cell individual offset (CIO) of the target cells PCI in the source-eNB with a positive value and of the source cells PCI in the target-eNB (after HO) by a negative value to avoid ping-pong effects. The changed CIOs are valid for all UEs in both cells (whenever they are newly configured, the new CIOs are used). The numOfUEfarIntraLB UEs causing the most GBR traffic are reconfigured with the new CIOs immediately to speed up the load balancing.

typedef.name: TOaMOffLoadDlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the DL GBR resource load offset with reference to its target load when measuring DL GBR resource load imbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available DL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMOffLoadPDCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the PDCCH load offset with reference to its target load when measuring PDCCH load imbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMOffLoadPUCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the PUCCH load offset with reference to its target load when measuring PUCCH load imbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available PUCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMOffLoadUlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the UL GBR resource load offset with reference to its target load when measuring UL GBR resource load imbalance. The value represents a percentage of the available UL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMOtnRecoveryPeriod
typedef.comment: OTN Link Loss Recoverable period without RF Unit Reset This parameter specifies the time period when an Optical Network (OTN) can be recovered after a link loss without incurring a restart.

typedef.name: TOaMOvlIpcPoolUsageL2
typedef.comment: When the consumption (filling level) of the IPC pool reaches the rate defined in this parameter, overload level 2 is detected.

typedef.name: TOaMOvlOccurrences
typedef.comment: Number of subsequent messages per port that must have delay bigger than the threshold in order to trigger overload

typedef.name: TOaMOvlThrOvl1
typedef.comment: If queuing time exceeds this threshold, overload level 1 applies. Note: ovlThrOvl1 < ovlThrOvl2

typedef.name: TOaMOvlThrOvl2
typedef.comment: If queuing time exceeds this threshold, overload level 2 applies. Note: ovlThrOvl1 < ovlThrOvl2

typedef.name: TOaMOvlTimer
typedef.comment: Duration of overload state after overload detection

typedef.name: TOaMP0UePucch
typedef.comment: This is a UE-specific power offset to be used for PUCCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P2). This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMP0UePusch
typedef.comment: This is a UE-specific power offset to be used for PUSCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1), which controls the mean received SNR for user data during a (re)transmission corresponding to a received PDCCH with the DCI format 0 associated with a new packet transmission. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchClComp
typedef.comment:
The parameter determines the compensation constant for diversity normalization for Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) used in PDCCH link adaptation in case Closed Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing has been applied and Rank Indicator (RI) is 2. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchCqiAvg
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines an averaging constant for Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) measurement filter, and it is applied only for CQI to be used PDCCH link adaptation. Basically the constant defines a weight for new received CQI value and 1 - pdcchCqiAvg is then a weight for a previous CQI. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchCqiHist
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time for which Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) used in PDCCH link adaptation is valid until fallback to a default aggregation (pdcchAggDefUe) is made. In other words the parameter determines the time which old CQI is remembered. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchLowAggTh
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines Common Channel Element (CCE) utilization threshold for activation of automatic lower aggregation selection in PDCCH link adaptation. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchOlComp
typedef.comment:
The parameter determines the compensation constant for diversity normalization for Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) used in PDCCH link adaptation in case dynamic Open Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing has been applied and Rank Indicator (RI) is 2. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchPcBoost
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the PDCCH power control maximum limit for power boost per Common Channel Element (CCE). This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchPcRed
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the PDCCH power control power maximum limit for reduction per Common Channel Element (CCE). This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchPcReloc
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the PDCCH power control maximum limit on the equal power relocation per Common Channel Element (CCE). This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPrioHarqDl
typedef.comment: The scheduling priority of a HARQ retransmission in DL, a higher number means a higher priority. This is a vendor-specifc parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMPrioHarqUl
typedef.comment: The scheduling priority of the HARQ retransmissions in UL, a higher number means a higher priority. This is a vendor-specifc parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMPrioSrUl
typedef.comment: The scheduling priority of the scheduling request procedure, a higher number means a higher priority. This is a vendor-specifc parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMPrioSrbDl
typedef.comment: The scheduling priority of the Signaling Radio Bearer in DL; a higher number means a higher priority. This is a vendor-specifc parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMPrioSrbUl
typedef.comment: The scheduling priority of the Signaling Radio Bearer in UL; a higher number means a higher priority. This is a vendor-specifc parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMLNBTSpuschHopOffset
typedef.comment: The PUSCH hopping offset parameter defines the offset used for PUSCH frequency hopping, expressed in a number of resource blocks.

typedef.name: TOaMQciWeightAlignDl
typedef.comment: Scaling factor for balancing of delay term and QCI weights in DL time domain scheduling criterion.

typedef.name: TOaMQciWeightAlignUl
typedef.comment: Scaling factor for the alignment of delay term and QCI terms Scaling factor for the balancing of the delay term and the QCI-specific relative weight terms

typedef.name: TOaMRaCrntiReuseT
typedef.comment: On receiving information that a UE has gone to RRC_IDLE, the eNB is not able to re-allocate the C-RNTI of a UE to another UE until this time has elapsed. This is a vendor-specific parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMRaLargeVolUl
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the data volume to be used for large size random access message 3 in case of an initial access or handover. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMRcAvCstDl
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the averaging constant for scheduled non-GBR (non-guaranteed bit rate) radio bearers AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate) determination in downlink. The latest scheduled AMBR is taken into account by 1/rcAvCstDl weight factor and the previous calculated AMBR by 1 - 1/rcAvCstDl weight factor. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMRcAvCstUl
typedef.comment: Averaging constant for scheduled AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate) determination for non-Guaranteed Bit Rate radio bearers in uplink. The latest scheduled AMBR is weighted by 1/rcAvCstUl and the previous calculated AMBR by 1 - 1/rcAvCstUl.

typedef.name: TOaMRecoveryResetDelay
typedef.comment: Defines the minimal number of seconds after which a recovery reset can be triggered. Note: When setting the parameter value to 10000 (unlimited delay), the recovery reset will be performed after all snapshot information is collected. This setting must be used with care.

typedef.name: TOaMRlpDetEndNUl
typedef.comment: Defines the number of consecutive uplink data receptions on PUSCH without DTX detection before the radio link problems are assumed to be over and an indication about radio link recovery is sent to higher layers. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMRlpDetEndNoDl
typedef.comment: Determines the number DL PDSCH transmission with correct HARQ feedback until detected radio link problems are assumed to be over. This parameter determines the number DL PDSCH transmission with correct HARQ feedback until detected radio link problems are assumed to be over. This parameter is vendor-specific. Note: due to ambiguous HARQ feedback the detection that there are no longer radio link problems for a UE with an active SCell might be later compared to a single cell UE since some NACKs might be excluded from the detection.

typedef.name: TOaMRlpDetMaxNUl
typedef.comment: Defines the number of uplink DTX detections on PUSCH before an indication about radio link problems is sent to higher layers. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMRlpDetMaxNoDl
typedef.comment: Determines the maximum number of failed DL PDSCH transmission attempts until radio link problems are detected. This parameter determines the maximum number of failed DL PDSCH transmission attempts until radio link problems are detected. This parameter is vendor-specific. Note: due to ambiguous HARQ feedback the detection of radio link problem for a UE with an active SCell might be more likely or earlier compared to a single cell UE since some NACKs might be falsely interpreted as DTX. Also, the parameter is reused for SCell scheduling stopping based on HARQ feedback in downlink scheduling on SCell.

typedef.name: TOaMRlpDetMaxTimeDl
typedef.comment: Determines the timeframe for failed DL PDSCH transmission attempts until radio link problems are detected. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMRohcFullContextCount
typedef.comment: Defines the number of successfully decompressed headers which are needed to transit directly into the full-context state.

typedef.name: TOaMRohcFullHdCount
typedef.comment: number of full headers to be transmitted in IR state

typedef.name: TOaMRohcHdRefreshPeriod
typedef.comment: periodicity for transmitting of full header in IR state

typedef.name: TOaMRohcK1
typedef.comment: full context state and K1 is for the number of failed decompressed headers

typedef.name: TOaMRohcK2
typedef.comment: static context state and K2 is for the number of failed updated headers

typedef.name: TOaMRohcN1
typedef.comment: full context state and N1 is for the number of decompressed headers

typedef.name: TOaMRohcN2
typedef.comment: static context state and N2 is for the number of updated headers

typedef.name: TOaMRrcGuardTimer
typedef.comment:
This timer is started when an RRC message for setup, modification or release of a radio bearer is sent to the UE. When the timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the MULTIPLICAND in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMRsrInitWaitTmr
typedef.comment: This time defines how long the eNB waits for the result of an earlier issued Resource Status Request: * If the Resource Status Request is sent to initiate a Resource Status Reporting, the eNB will repeat the Resource Status Request after this timer expires if the Resource Status Reporting is still needed by the eNB. * If the Resource Status Request is sent to stop an ongoing Resource Status Reporting, on timer expiry the eNB will consider the stop request as failed and will locally release the Resource Status Reporting.

typedef.name: TOaMRsrResTmrFirst
typedef.comment: This defines the maximum time the eNB waits for further cell load measurements before collected cell load measurements are indicated to the requesting cell for the first time.

typedef.name: TOaMS1InducedCellDeactDelayTime
typedef.comment: If for an eNB cell all configured PLMN IDs are unavailable on S1 interface for the duration given by "s1InducedCellDeactDelayTime", the eNB cell is deactivated.

typedef.name: TOaMS1ResetRspTmr
typedef.comment:
This is a timer that specifies the amount of time an eNB should wait for an S1AP:RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message before assuming that the procedure has failed. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMS1SetupRspTmr
typedef.comment:
This is a timer that specifies the amount of time that an eNB should wait for an S1AP: SETUP RESPONSE message before assuming the procedure has failed. Recommended values are: 1s, 2s, 5s, 10s,15s, 20s, 25s, 30s, 40s, 50s, 60s, 90s, 120s, 180s, 240s and 300s
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMShutdownStepAmount
typedef.comment: Number of Steps for Graceful Cell Shutdown

typedef.name: TOaMShutdownWindow
typedef.comment: Time Interval for Stepwise Output Power Reduction for Graceful Cell Shutdown

typedef.name: TOaMSysTimeCorrectValue
typedef.comment: Defines the system time correction value for IP packets received by Target eNB transferred over S1/X2 interface.

typedef.name: TOaMTDataFwdEpc
typedef.comment: This timer is normally started in the target eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER NOTIFY message was issued. When the timer expires the eNB closes its user data forwarding tunnels. Note: This timer should usually be greater than TDATAfwdS1, see note at MM.1768. A semantic check may be useful, but it is not required.

typedef.name: TOaMTDataFwdS1
typedef.comment: This timer is started in the source eNB when the X2AP: RELEASE RESOURCE message is received. When the timer expires, the eNB closes its S1-U connection. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTDataFwdX2
typedef.comment: This timer is normally started in the target eNB when the S1AP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message is received. When the timer expires, the eNB closes its user data tunnels at X2. Note: The value of this timer should usually be greater than TDATAfwdS1, see note at MM.605. A semantic check may be useful, but is not required. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTEstS1Con
typedef.comment: This timer is used to supervise the establishment of a UE-associated logical S1 connection. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTHalfRrcCon
typedef.comment: The minimal time period during which the internal state and the resources associated with an half-open RRC connection (i.e. one for which no RRC connection setup complete message has yet been received) must not be deleted in the eNB. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTHoOverallD
typedef.comment: Covers the estimated time taken to send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message to the UE (no RLC Ack needed) - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE THOoverall = T304 + T311 + T301 + THOoverallDelta This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTL2AckRrcRel
typedef.comment: The minimal time period indicates the time after which the RRC L3 releases the RRC connection, if no positive ack is received from L2 to the RRC:RRC connection release message. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTRimKaG
typedef.comment: This timer is started when eNB receives a valid RAN-INFORMATION/Initial Multiple Report PDU. This timer is restarted when eNB receives subsequent RAN-INFORMATION/Multiple Report PDU. When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU. Refer to [RIM.359].

typedef.name: TOaMTRimPollG
typedef.comment: This timer is started when RIM procedure for a GERAN neighbor cell fails or ends. When the timer expires the eNB re-starts RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report procedure for the GERAN neighbor cell. Note: If this timer’s length is set to a short value (e.g. 5 minutes), the re-sending RIM PDUs may visibly increase the S1 link traffic.

typedef.name: TOaMTRimRirG
typedef.comment: This timer is started when eNB sends out a RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Mutiple Report message. When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RIM message up to nRimRirG(see [CCPM.9031]) times.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelCanG
typedef.comment: TS1RELOCcancel guards the respond to an S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE The "TS1RELOCcancel_UTRAN" parameter provides the duration of the "TS1RELOCcancel" timer, which is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond to an S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE during eNB-initiated cancellation of a nS1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. "TS1RELOCcancel" is started in the source eNB when it sends the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message to the MME and is stopped when an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the eNB initiates failure procedures to ensure integrity of the S1 and the UE state. The value of "TS1RELOCcancel_UTRAN" should be set to an estimate of the an upper bound of the time taken for the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message reach the MME, for the EPC and the UTRAN to perform any cancellation procedures required and for the eNB to receive the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message during normal network conditions. Parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelCanL
typedef.comment: TS1RELOCcancel guards the respond to a S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with a S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE Parameter TS1RELOCcancel_LTE provides the duration of the timer TS1RELOCcancel, which is used to guard against a failure of the MME to respond to an S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE during an eNB-initiated cancellation of a S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCcancel is started in the source eNB when it sends the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message to the MME, and is stopped when an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires, the eNB initiates failure procedures to ensure integrity of the S1 and the UE state. The value of TS1RELOCcancel_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of the upper bound of the time necessary for the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message to reach the MME, for the EPC and the UTRAN to perform any cancellation procedures required and for the eNB to receive the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message during normal network conditions. This parameter is vendor specific

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelCanU
typedef.comment: TS1RELOCcancel guards the response to an S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message. Parameter TS1RELOCcancel_UTRAN provides the duration of the timer TS1RELOCcancel, which is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond to an S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE during an eNB-initiated cancellation of an S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCcancel is started in the source eNB when it sends the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message to the MME, and is stopped when an S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires, the eNB initiates failure procedures to ensure integrity of the S1 and the UE state. The value of TS1RELOCcancel_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of the an upper bound of the time necessary for the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message yo reach the MME, for the EPC and the UTRAN to perform any cancellation procedures required, and for the eNB to receive the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message during normal network conditions. This parameter is vendor specific

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelExecDeltL
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer for the Handover Execution Phase of intra LTE S1 handover at the Target eNodeB

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelExecDeltU
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer for the Handover Execution Phase of handover from UTRAN at the Target eNodeB.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelOvDeltG
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to GSM TS1RELOCoverallDelta_GSM is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_GSM to that of T304_InterRAT. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the RNC to communicate via the MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelOvDeltL
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer For the intra LTE S1 handover at the Source eNodeB tS1RelOvDeltL (TS1RELOCoverallDelta_LTE) is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during intra LTE S1 handover. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: RRC CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released.The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_LTE to that of T304 and T311.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelOvDeltU
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to UTRAN TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN to that of T304_InterRAT. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the RNC to communicate via the MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelPrepG
typedef.comment: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to GSM Timer TS1RELOCprep_InterRAT is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelPrepL
typedef.comment: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of intra LTE S1 handover Timer TS1RELOCprep_LTE is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of intra LTE S1 handover. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelPrepU
typedef.comment: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT Timer tS1relprepIrat is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

typedef.name: TOaMTX2RelocComp
typedef.comment: This timer is started in the target eNB when the S1AP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST message is sent to the MME and is typically stopped when the S1AP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message is received in return. When the timer expires, the eNB-initiated context release procedure is started. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTX2RelocExcD
typedef.comment: Covers the estimated time taken to - send an X2AP:HANDOVER REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message to the source eNB - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message to the UE (no RLC Ack needed) - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE TX2RELOCexec = TDRX + T304 + T311 + TX2RELOCexecDelta This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTX2RelocHold
typedef.comment: This timer is started in the source eNB when the X2AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message is sent to the target eNB and is typically stopped when the X2AP: HANDOVER REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE or X2AP: HANDOVER PREPARATION FAILURE message is received. When the timer expires, the X2 signaling connections at the source eNB are closed. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTX2RelocPrep
typedef.comment: This timer is started in the source eNB when the X2AP: HANDOVER REQUEST message is sent to the target eNB and is typically stopped when the X2AP: HANDOVER REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message is received in return. When the timer expires, the X2AP: HANDOVER CANCEL procedure is started. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTaCmdMaxRetry
typedef.comment: The number of times the timing advance command is retried before the LTE MAC assumes that the UE has gone out-of-synch. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTaOffScheMarg
typedef.comment:
Determines the time alignment offset limit for the uplink scheduler to stop considering the UE for scheduling. This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTagMarginAM
typedef.comment: The margin for end tag timer calculation valid for RLC-AM DRBs.

typedef.name: TOaMTagMarginUM
typedef.comment: The margin for end tag timer calculation valid for RLC-UM DRBs.

typedef.name: TOaMTagMaxAM
typedef.comment: The maximum bound for tag timer calculation valid for RLC-AM DRBs.

typedef.name: TOaMTagMaxUM
typedef.comment: The maximum bound for tag timer calculation valid for RLC-UM DRBs.

typedef.name: TOaMTargetLoadDlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the target load for the DL GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of the available DL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMTargetLoadPDCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the target load for the PDCCH. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMTargetLoadPUCCH
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the target load for the PUCCH. The value represents a percentage of the available PUCCH resources in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMTargetLoadUlGBR
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the target load for the UL GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of the available UL PRBs in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMTeNACCDelta
typedef.comment: Parameter TeNACCoverallDelta is used to calculate the duration of the timer TeNACCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to perform eNACC to GSM. TeNACCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the eNodeB assumes that the Core network connected to the GERAN is Pre-Rel’8 so that it will not trigger a UE Context Release. So Source eNodeB initiates UE Context Release towards MME. The duration of TeNACCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TeNACCoverallDelta to that of T304_CCO. The value of TeNACCoverallDelta_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time required by the UE to initiate RRC Connection Re-Establishment procedure (after failing to establish RRC Connection in GERAN)

typedef.name: TOaMTimDelACContPreempt
typedef.comment: This timer delays the continuation of the admission control for pre-empted bearers. If eNB sends the S1AP message E-RAB RELEASE INDICATION for pre-empted bearers to MME, the MME needs time to release the indicated bearers in the EPC. Until the release of a bearer S-GW might still send downlink data packets for this bearer to eNB. The expected avarage time is covered by this timer that delays the continuation of the admisison control by the given timer value.

typedef.name: TOaMTimSuppGtpuErrIndPreempt
typedef.comment: This timer suppresses the GTP-U Error Indications that eNB might send for pre-empted bearers. If eNB sends the S1AP message E-RAB RELEASE INDICATION for pre-empted bearers to MME, MME needs time to release the indicated bearers in the EPC. Until the release of a bearer S-GW may still send downlink data packets for this bearer to eNB. This period is covered by the timer “Timer Suppress GTP-U Error Indication at Pre-emptions” that suppresses the GTP-U Error Indications for the given time interval.

typedef.name: TOaMTtiBundlingCStepUp
typedef.comment:
UL OLLA compensation stepsize up while in TTI Bundling mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTtiBundlingDeltaCini
typedef.comment:
UL OLLA initial value for compensation while in TTI Bundling mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTtiBundlingDeltaCmax
typedef.comment:
UL OLLA maximum limit for compensation while in TTI Bundling mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTtiBundlingDeltaCmin
typedef.comment:
UL OLLA minimum limit for compensation while in TTI Bundling mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTx2RelODelta
typedef.comment: Covers at a minimum the estimated time taken to: - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message to the UE (no RLC Ack needed) - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:CONNECTION REESTABLISHMENT REQUEST message from the UE - send an S1AP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST message from the target eNB Note that this value can be extended to also include the estimated time for the target eNB to complete the full handover completion phase. TX2RELOCoverall = T304max + T311 + T301 + TX2RELOCoverallDelta This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcCStepUp
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the stepsize up value for the uplink Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C. Stepsize down value for delta C can be calculated by using this parameter and UL target BLER (ulTargetBler, SFS ULAMC_TARGET_BLER (ulamcTargetBler)). This parameter is vendor-specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcDeltaCini
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the initial value for uplink Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcDeltaCmax
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the maximum limit for the uplink Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C. If the value delta C reaches the maximum limit, UL MCS is increased by one.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcDeltaCmin
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the minimum limit for uplink Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C. If delta C value reaches the minimum limit, UL MCS is decreased by one.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcHistMcsT
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time in TTIs for remembering the selected Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) for the uplink when UL AMC has been enabled.

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcInactT
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time in TTIs for starting the uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inactivity actions.

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcUpdowngrF
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the factor for the calculation of BLER thresholds for the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) downgrade and upgrade. The upgrade threshold is ulTargetBler / ulamcUpdowngrF and the downgrade threshold is ulTargetBler * ulamcUpdowngrF. ulTargetBler: SFS ULAMC_TARGET_BLER (ulamcTargetBler)
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlatbPhrAvgF
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the forgetting factor for UE Power Headroom Reports (PHRs) which is used for time averaging PHR reports. PHR averaging functionality is part of uplink Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth (ATB).
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCchavgtcont

Filter coefficient for the PUCCH component in closed loop uplink power control for averaging of UL measured RSSI and SINR values if UL user data is available. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCumpucchmax

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCumpucchmin
typedef.comment: Minimum value of accumulated Delta_PUCCH values in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCumpuschmax
typedef.comment: Maximum value of accumulated Delta_PUSCH values in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCumpuschmin
typedef.comment: Minimum value of accumulated Delta_PUSCH values in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcRssiMax
typedef.comment: Upper limit of the RSSI value used for further processing and final calculation of DELTA_PUSCH and DELTA_PUCCH in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

member.name: ulpcRssiMaxIAw
member.comment: Sets an upper limit for RSSI received from a UE. If exceeded, the next power command indicates -1 dB UL power change even if the current UL power is insufficient for reaching Target SINR.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcRssiMin
typedef.comment: Lower limit of the RSSI value used for further processing and final calculation of DELTA_PUSCH and DELTA_PUCCH in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcSchavgtcont
typedef.comment:
Filter coefficient for the PUSCH/SRS component in closed loop uplink power control for averaging of UL measured RSSI and SINR values in case of availability of UL user data. Parameter is vendor specific.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcSchavgtdisc

Filter coefficient for the PUSCH/SRS component in closed loop uplink power control for averaging of UL measured RSSI and SINR values in case of non-availability of UL user data. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcSinrMax
typedef.comment: Upper limit of the SINR value used for further processing and final calculation of DELTA_PUSCH and DELTA_PUCCH in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcSinrMin
typedef.comment: Lower limit of the SINR value used for further processing and final calculation of DELTA_PUSCH and DELTA_PUCCH in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfPucchUe
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from PUCCH for measurements on UE scope in closed loop uplink power control.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfPucchcell
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from PUCCH for measurements on cell scope in closed loop uplink power control.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfPuschUe
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from PUSCH for measurements on UE scope in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfPuschcell
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from PUSCH for measurements on cell scope in closed loop uplink power control. Parameter is vendor specific.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfSrsUe
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from SRS for measurements on UE scope in closed loop uplink power control.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcWfSrscell
typedef.comment: Weighting factor for measurements from SRS for measurements on cell scope in closed loop uplink power control.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsInterferenceCst
typedef.comment: Averaging Constant which is required for the calculation of the PRB-specific interference and noise power in the time domain.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsNumConsecutivePhr
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the number of consecutively received PHRs after that the change of the SRS class is requested in case the corresponding power conditions of the SRS resources are fulfilled. Two SRS classes are specified with different number of PRBs on that the sounding signal is transferred in the subframe the UE is selected. Huge SRS resources are assigned with class 1 and the basic configuration is represented by class 2. The SRS class which is selected depends beyond other conditions on the power the UE can spend for the SRS signal.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsNumSchedAreaUl
typedef.comment: Defines the number of scheduling areas supported by the PUSCH.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsSidVolRohcComp
typedef.comment: SID packet size for RoHC transmission mode Defines the data volume of the SID packet which shall be considered for the silent period of the QCI=1 bearer - the parameter defines the packet size with compressed RTP/UDP/IP header (RoHC)

typedef.name: TOaMUlsSidVolUncomp
typedef.comment: SID packet size for uncompressed transmission mode Defines the data volume of the SID packet which is considered for the silent period of the QCI=1 bearer - the parameter defines the packet size with full RTP/UDP/IP header

typedef.name: TOaMUlsTputAvgT
typedef.comment: Time averaging constant for equal throughput criterion in uplink. The mean throughput of Data Radio Bearer is defined over this time constant.

Running averaging factor for the calculation of the scheduling criterion of the interference aware UL scheduler.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlsVoipOverhead
typedef.comment: Overhead size of VoIP packets on MAC level Defines the MAC overhead which shall be added to the VoIP packet for the MAC SDU and the additional MAC-C elements like PHR and BSR

Timeout duration while waiting for an eNB Configuration Update Acknowledge on X2-i/f Vendor-Configurable Timer that specifies the amount of time an eNB waits for X2AP:ENB CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE message before assuming the X2 Configuration Update procedure has failed.

This timer specifies the amount of time an eNB should wait for X2AP: RESET RESPONSE before assuming that the procedure has failed. This parameter is vendor-specific.

This timer specifies the amount of time an eNB should wait for X2AP: SETUP RESPONSE before assuming that the procedure has failed. This parameter is vendor-specific.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelCanTd
typedef.comment: TS1RELOCcancel guards the respond to a S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with a S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE Parameter TS1RELOCcancel_TDSCDMA provides the duration of the timer TS1RELOCcancel which is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond to a S1AP:HANDOVER CANCEL with a S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE during eNB initiated cancellation of a S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCcancel is started in the source eNB when it sends the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message to the MME and is stopped when a S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the eNB initiates failure procedures to ensure integrity of the S1 and the UE state. The value of TS1RELOCcancel_TDSCDMA should be set to an estimate of the an upper bound of the time taken for the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL message reach the MME, for the EPC and the UTRAN to perform any cancellation procedures required and for the eNB to receive the S1AP: HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE message during normal network conditions. Parameter is vendor specific

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelOvDeltTd
typedef.comment: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to TD-SCDMA TS1RELOCoverallDelta_TDSCDMA is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_TDSCDMA to that of T304_InterRatTD. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_TDSCDMA should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the RNC to communicate via the MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

typedef.name: TOaMTS1RelPrepTd
typedef.comment: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT Timer TS1RELOCprep_TDSCDMA is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsSrelFilterCst
typedef.comment: Filtering constant for the relative signal strength parameters required for the channel aware UL scheduler. The filtering constant shall be determined depending on the SRS settings. ulsSrelFilterCst = (mSRS,0/mSRS,B_SRS)*TSRS mSRS,0, mSRS,B_SRS see 36.211 chapter 5.5.3.2 TSRS see 36.313 chapter 8.2

typedef.name: TOaMA3Offset
typedef.comment:
Handover margin for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMAddAUeRrHo
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: “Reduce load in serving cell” but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is bigger than 0. If CAC in the Cell is zero, the HO for “Reduce load in serving cell” are always rejected. This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUe. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 860 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1030 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 2 3 MHz bandwidth 15 5 MHz bandwidth 15 10 MHz bandwidth 15 15 MHz bandwidth 30 20 MHz bandwidth 45 Dependencies: maxNumActUE + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (40,120,480,860,1030,1200)) (1) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod (2) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '2' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (2) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '1' - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth 20 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 30 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 20

typedef.name: TOaMAddAUeTcHo
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUe. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 860 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1030 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 4 3 MHz bandwidth 20 5 MHz bandwidth 20 10 MHz bandwidth 20 15 MHz bandwidth 40 20 MHz bandwidth 50 Dependencies: maxNumActUE + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (480,860,1030,1200)) (1) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod (2) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '2' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (2) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '1' - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth 30 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 45 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 30

typedef.name: TOaMAddEmergencySessions
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional margin for Emergency Sessions. This margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell. Please note that active QCI1-DRBs thresholds are not considered when actEnhAcAndGbrServices is true. The parameter is only relevant if actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. Emergency traffic shall have high preference against normal traffic in the cell. The addEmergencySession value is used to increase several thresholds and it has to be considered, that the system limits are never exceeded for all resources. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 5 MHz bandwidth 50 10 MHz bandwidth 70 15 MHz bandwidth 70 20 MHz bandwidth 90 Dependencies: In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal handover traffic addEmergencySessions should be greater than max( addNumUeRadioReasHo, addNumUeTimeCriticalHo, addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo, addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo).
TDD specific comment: Additional margin for Emergency Sessions; this margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs with a factor and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell Emergency traffic shall have high preference against normal traffic in the cell. The addEmergencySession value is used to increase several thresholds and it has to be considered, that the system limits are never exceeded for all resources. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth, 20 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 30 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 20

typedef.name: TOaMAddGbrTrafficRrHo
typedef.comment: Additional margin on the threshold "maxGbrTrafficLimit" in case of handover for radio reasons. The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system. For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*, for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*, for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*, for 20 Mhz system 100 PRBs* are available. * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs and so on, which can consume some PRBs (for example three PRBs) in average. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to True and ignored otherwise. The "addGbrTrafficRrHo" parameter should be configured significantly lower than the "maxGbrTrafficLimit" parameter to reduce admitting handover traffic and preempting other low prior traffic immediately with next cell local admission requests.

typedef.name: TOaMAddGbrTrafficTcHo
typedef.comment: Additional margin on the threshold "maxGbrTrafficLimit " in case of handover for time critical reasons. The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system. For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*, for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*, for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*, for 20 Mhz system 100 PRBs* are available. * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs and so on, which can consume some PRBs (for example three PRBs) in average. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to True and ignored otherwise. The "addGbrTrafficTcHo" parameter should be configured significantly lower than the parameter maxGbrTrafficLimit to reduce admitting handover traffic and preempting other low prior traffic immediately with next cell local admission requests.

typedef.name: TOaMAddNumDrbRadioReasHo
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb. This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: “Reduce load in serving cell” but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is bigger than 0. If CAC in the Cell is zero, the HOs due to “Reduce load in serving cell” are always rejected. Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1440 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1800 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3090 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3600 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 6 3 MHz bandwidth 35 5 MHz bandwidth 35 10 MHz bandwidth 35 15 MHz bandwidth 90 20 MHz bandwidth 135 Dependencies: maxNumActDrb + max( addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above)
TDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb. Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 1800 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth 60 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 90 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 60

typedef.name: TOaMAddNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Additional margin for the maximum number of active GBRs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: “Reduce load in serving cell” but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is bigger than 0. If CAC in the Cell is zero, the HOs due to “Reduce load in serving cell” are always rejected. This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb. Hand over traffic has some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 5 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 200 10 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 400 15 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 500 20 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 600 Note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 5 MHz bandwidth 15 10 MHz bandwidth 15 15 MHz bandwidth 30 20 MHz bandwidth 40 Dependencies: maxNumQci1Drb + max( addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (200, 400, 500, 600)) The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise.

This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb. Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell. The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed: (1) tddFrameConf is set to 'sa1' Max value: 120 for 10 MHz and 144 for 20 MHz Default value: 16 for both 10 MHz and 20 MHz (2) tddFrameConf is set to 'sa2' Max value: 60 for 10 MHz and 72 for 20 MHz Default value: 12 for both 10 MHz and 20 MHz

typedef.name: TOaMBlankedPucch
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the pointer to PRB from where the CQI-allocation starts to leave some PRBs free and therefore avoid interference with neighbor bands. When set to 0 the Flexible UL Bandwidth feature is deactivated. The physical allocation policy on the RF of the PRB defined by blankedPucch follows that typical of PUCCH PRB resources, which are symmetrically distributed at the edges of the given system BW. In other terms blankedPucch resources are distributed at the BW edges the very same way as the resources defined by nCqiRb (of which they are a subset) When set to values different from 0 all the PRBs from 0 up to "blankedPucch" value are not used by the PUCCH allocation algorithm for allocating the periodic CQI. In other words all those PRBs up to blankedPucch are skipped by the periodic CQI allocation algorithm. Example: blankedPucch = 6 would mean that CQI-allocation will start from the seventh PRB, the PRB #6. All the PRB up to the PRB#6 excluded (three at each BW edge accordingly to PUCCH physical allocation policy) are left free, to avoid interferences with neighbor bands supported by other radio technologies. The configuration of the blanked PRBs region in one operators network shall be the same for all the cells having same E-UTRA Operating Band, same channel bandwidth and same center carrier frequency (that is same Transmission bandwidth configuration according to 3GPP-36.104). In case of contemporary activation of the LTE46: Channel-aware Scheduler (UL) feature one must take care of the correct choice of the SRS configuration to avoid that SRS signal is sent within the blanked RF area.
TDD specific comment: Defines the pointer to RB from where the CQI allocation shall start in order to left some RBs free and therefore avoid interference with neighbour bands. Example: blankedPucch = 6 would mean that CQI-allocation will start from the seventh PRB, the RB #6 is the lower part and therefore avoid interferences with neighbour bands supported by other radio technologies. When periodic CQI reporting shall be possible the number of blanked Pucch PRB ressources needs to be less than the number of CQI PRBs

The shift is the cyclic shift difference between two adjacent ACK/NACK/Scheduling Request resources using the same orthogonal cover sequence and can be decided considering multipath delay spreads for the given cell deployment.

typedef.name: TOaMDlCellPwrRed
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Sets the power reduction from the antenna maximum TX power.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: Sets the power reduction from the antenna maximum TX power. Cell locking is not required if dlCellPwrRed is changed by 0.2 dB or less. If the feature ‘Automatic Locking (LTE830)’ is activated, eNB will not perform cell locking in this case. The user can define a lower cell output power with the cell power reduction parameter. Reduction is deducted from the antenna maximum TX power. Hint: If dlCellPwrRed is modified by 0.2 dB or less, more often than 32 times within 3 hours, a valueTag overflow occurs. As consequence the changed System Information (SIB2 ff.) might sporadically not be read by UEs which come back to the cell and have stored valid system information from 3h validity rule viewpoint.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: dlpcMimoComp
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: Sets the compensation in 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 2x2 MIMO SM and 4x2 MIMO SM case into the DL power control. Compensation of MIMO Coverage effects for MIMO Spatial Multiplexing and MIMO Diversity The parameter determines the power compensation factor for antenna-specific maximum power in case of a downlink transmission using at least two TX antennas. This means that every single subcarrier power determined for multiple TX antenna transmission is reduced by this factor. The parameter does not apply in case of a single TX (TM1) transmission, and thus neither affects the power of cell-specific reference signal transmission. Note that only the limited set of dlpcMimoComp values (0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) can be communicated to the UE due to p-a signaling restrictions and the extended range has been determined only for finetuning purposes. Please be informed that Nokia Solutions and Networks does not guarantee a successful DL transmission using amplitude dependent modulations, especially 64QAM, if other values than the values presented in the limited set (0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) are used. Please note, that if the Cell-Specific Reference Symbol Power Boost is activated by setting the dlRsBoost parameter, only the values 0dB and 3dB are allowed for dlpcMimoComp. The parameter will be ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: Sets the compensation in 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 2x2 MIMO SM and 4x2 MIMO SM case into the DL power control. Compensation of MIMO Coverage effects for MIMO Spatial Multiplexing and MIMO Diversity The parameter determines the power compensation factor for antenna-specific maximum power in case of a downlink transmission using at least two TX antennas. This means that every single subcarrier power determined for multiple TX antenna transmission is reduced by this factor. The parameter does not apply in case of a single TX (TM1) transmission, and thus neither affects the power of cell-specific reference signal transmission. Note that only the limited set of dlpcMimoComp values (0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) can be communicated to the UE due to p-a signaling restrictions and the extended range has been determined only for finetuning purposes. Please be informed that Nokia Solutions and Networks does not guarantee a successful DL transmission using amplitude dependent modulations, especially 64QAM, if other values than the values presented in the limited set (0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) are used. Please note, that if the Cell-Specific Reference Symbol Power Boost is activated by setting the dlRsBoost parameter, only the values 0dB and 3dB are allowed for dlpcmimocomp.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMEarfcnDLTdd
typedef.comment: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number. Supported Bands and related EARFCNs are the following: Band 38 (2570-2619.9 MHz): 37750-38249 Band 39 (1880-1919.9 MHz): 38250-38649 Band 40 (2300-2399.9 MHz): 38650-39649 Band 41 (2496-2689.9 MHz): 39650-41589 Please note following limitations for the hardware variants: FZHA working on E-UTRA band 38 supports frequency range 37800...38199 (2575-2614.9 MHz) FZFA working on E-UTRA band 39 supports frequency range 38250…38549 (1880-1909.9 MHz) FZFD, FZFE and FZFF working on E-UTRA band 39 support frequency range 38250…38599 (1880-1914.9 MHz) FZND, FZNK, FZNL, FZNN and FSNI working on E-UTRA band 40 support frequency range 38850...39349 (2320-2369.9 MHz) FZHE and FZHJ working on E-UTRA band 41 support frequency range 39650...41589 (2496-2689.9) FZHN working on E-UTRA band 41 supports frequency range 40640...41139 (2595MHz-2644.9MHz) FZHG working on E-UTRA band 41 supports frequency range 41040...41439 (2635MHz-2674.9MHz) FZHO working on E-UTRA band 41 supports frequency range 40040...40439 (2535MHz-2574.9MHz) Note that for intra-band contiguous CA, the spacing between the central frequencies of the two carriers must be equal or less than 198 EARFCN (19.8 MHz) for 20 MHz +20 MHz bandwidth combination, and 144 EARFCN (14.4 MHz) for 20 MHz + 10 MHz bandwidth combination.

member.name: emAreaIdList
member.comment: An element of the emAreaIdList identifies an Emergency Area ID (emAreaId) of the eNB cell. Multiple emAreaId's may be configured for the eNB cell. An 'emAreaId' ID may be used in signalling messages received via S1-i/f to indicate the set of cells with emergency impact (e.g. which have to broadcast the warning message). If e.g. a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with 'emAreaId' is received, the warning message shall be broadcasted by an eNB cell if 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is true and the 'emAreaId' received in the request message matches with the 'emAreaId' assigned to the eNB cell.

typedef.name: TOaMEutraCelId

The leftmost 20 bits of the value correspond to the value of the eNB ID (parameter lnBtsId) and the 8 rightmost bits correspond to the value of the local cell resource ID (lcrId). This parameter cannot be set by operator, it is calculated system internally and is only readable.

member.name: filterCenterTx
