member.name: idleLBCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

typedef.name: TOaMLncelIdleLBPercentageOfUes
typedef.comment: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.

typedef.name: TOaMIlReacTimerUl
typedef.comment: Improved latency reaction timer in uplink defines the time in which the UE has to send useful data after either the initial dummy grant or a previous reception of useful data. If the timer expires the, UE will not get dummy grant anymore.

typedef.name: TOaMInactivityTimer
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity in both DL and UL directions.

typedef.name: TOaMIniMcsDl
typedef.comment: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH for other use than BCCH, PCH or random access messages. iniMcsDl is applicable for PDSCH LA only if both dlOlqcEnable and dlamcEnable are set to 'false' where it determines the static target code rate for PDSCH user data transmissions. Otherwise, UE reported CQI or default CQI (dlamcCqiDef) with or without OLQC correction determines the target code rate.

typedef.name: TOaMIniMcsUl
typedef.comment: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH for other use than random access message 3.

typedef.name: TOaMIniPrbsUl
typedef.comment: Defines the initial amount of maximum PRBs in uplink.

typedef.name: TOaMLncelLcrId
typedef.comment: ID of the Local Cell Resource. The value for each cell shall be unique in the eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMLnCelId
typedef.comment: Instance identifier of the object LNCEL. This parameter is used only for O&M purposes. Important Note: If the lnCelId shall be modified it is recommended to use BTSSM. The BTSSM will automatically perform a full commissioning instead of a delta commissioning. Otherwise 2 plan file operations are required because LNCEL as well as the related LCELL object must be deleted and recreated. Those two objects are strongly coupled and must be created and deleted in common.

member.name: lowerMarginCIO
member.comment: This parameter defines the minimum value that a CIO can assume, when changed autonomously by the eNB during for example the intra-frequency load balancing function.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxBitrateDl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Maximum Bit Rate that shall not be exceeded in DL (configured value is limitation on TTI base, i.e. a calculation on maximum bitrate per TTI is done) This parameter is not used any longer for UEs having carrier aggregation activated. In case CA-UEs are treated the limitations are taken from the 3 GPP-standard TS 36.306 considering the UE's category. That's why the range of this parameter must not be adapted to higher transmission rates defined with Rel10!
TDD specific comment: Maximum Bit Rate that shall not be exceeded in DL (configured value is limitation on TTI base, i.e. a calculation on maximum bitrate per TTI is done) This parameter is not used any longer for UEs having carrier aggregation activated. In case CA-UEs are treated the limitations are taken from the 3 GPP-standard TS 36.306 considering the UE's category.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxBitrateUl
typedef.comment: Maximum bit rate that shall not be exceeded in UL TTI.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxCrPgDl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for paging. This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling. Note: The amount of paging records being transmitted per paging occasion is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single paging record is transmitted in any case.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for paging. This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMaxCrRa4Dl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for random access procedure messages 4 (SRB0 message). This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling. Note: For small bandwidth system a sufficient number of HARQ retransmission or according segmentation is applied in order to reach to the configured code rate.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for random access procedure messages 4 (SRB0 message). This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMaxCrRaDl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for random access procedure messages 2 (RA response). This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling. Note: For small bandwidth system the number of RAR records per RAR message is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single RAR record is transmitted in any case.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for random access procedure messages 2 (RA response). This maximum coderate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMaxCrSibDl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for System Information Broadcast. This maximum coderate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling. Recommendation: For cells with a bandwidth of 1.4 MHz the code rate should be >= 0.12 as lower code rates may not be reached.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for System Information Broadcast. This maximum coderate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMaxGbrTrafficLimit
typedef.comment: Maximum radio resource consumption (PRBs) for GBR traffic in UL and DL The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system. For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs* for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs* for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs* for 20 Mhz system 100 PRBs* are available * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs etc. which can consume some PRBs (e.g. 3 PRBs) in average. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNrSymPdcch
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines how many OFDM symbols can be used for PDCCH channel transmission. eNB selects based on usage the actual value for each TTI, which and value is signaled to the UEs in PCFICH. If dlChBw equals '3 MHz' it is recommended to set the parameter to '3'.
TDD specific comment: The parameter defines how many OFDM symbols can be used for PDCCH channel transmission. eNB selects based on usage the actual value for each TTI, which and value is signaled to the UEs in PCFICH.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumActDrb
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of established DRBs in the cell. The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1440 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1800 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3090 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3600 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 60 3 MHz bandwidth 200 5 MHz bandwidth 480 10 MHz bandwidth 600 15 MHz bandwidth 1200 20 MHz bandwidth 1200 Dependencies: maxNumActDrb + max( addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above)
TDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of established DRBs in the cell. The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1500 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 2000 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth 300 20 MHz bandwidth 600

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumActUE
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell. Active UEs are UEs with at least one DRB. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1030 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 20 3 MHz bandwidth 80 5 MHz bandwidth 300 10 MHz bandwidth 300 15 MHz bandwidth 600 20 MHz bandwidth 600 Dependencies: maxNumActUE + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (480,860,1030,1200))
TDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell with established DRB. The maximum number of UEs in the cell with established DRB. The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth 200 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 300 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 200

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumCaConfUeDc
typedef.comment: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a cell PCell (P-LNCEL); Dc (Double carrier) indicates that these UEs have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and only 1 SCell (S-LNCEL). Carrier aggregated UEs with 1 SCell need double amount of UL resources compared with single carrier UEs as long as UL signalling is done only via PCell. That's why the information Dc is relevant.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumQci1Drb
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of established QCI1-GBR-DRBs in the cell. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise. QCI1-DRBs are additional data radio bearers in the cell and are also checked against the threshold maxNumActDrb. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 500 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 5 MHz bandwidth 75 10 MHz bandwidth 100 15 MHz bandwidth 100 20 MHz bandwidth 100 Dependencies: maxNumQci1Drb + max( addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (200, 400, 500, 600))
TDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of established QCI1-GBR-DRBs in the cell QCI1-DRBs are additional data radio bearers in the cell and are also checked against the threshold maxNumActDrb. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise. The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed: (1) tddFrameConf is set to 'sa1' Max value: 120 for 10 MHz and 144 for 20 MHz Default value: 24 for 10 MHz and 20MHz, TDD conf.2, 36 for 20 MHz, TDD conf.1. (2) tddFrameConf is set to 'sa2' Max value: 60 for 10 MHz and 72 for 20 MHz Default value: 24 for 10 MHz and 20MHz, TDD conf.2, 36 for 20 MHz, TDD conf.1.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumRrc
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection. This threshold includes resource usage of UEs using this cell as SCell in case of Carrier Aggregation. The maximum value depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1030 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 20 3 MHz bandwidth 80 5 MHz bandwidth 300 10 MHz bandwidth 300 15 MHz bandwidth 600 20 MHz bandwidth 600 Dependencies: maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (480,860,1030,1200)) In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: (1) if riEnable is set to 'true' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod (2) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '2' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (3) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '1' - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection The maximum value depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth, 200 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 300 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 200

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumRrcEmergency
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection, used to admit RRC connections for emergency calls. In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal traffic maxNumRrcEmergency should be greater than maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) The parameter is only relevant if actEmerCallRedir is set to 'true' OR actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The emergency call is only recognized when the UE was in idle state before initiating the connection. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40 3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120 5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600 15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1030 20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1200 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 35 3 MHz bandwidth 100 5 MHz bandwidth 440 10 MHz bandwidth 560 15 MHz bandwidth 800 20 MHz bandwidth 800 Dependencies: In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal traffic maxNumRrcEmergency should be greater than maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) The parameter is only relevant if actEmerCallRedir is set to 'true' OR actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: (1) if riEnable is set to 'true' maxNumRrcEmergency <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod (2) if riEnable is set to 'true' AND riPerM is set to '2' maxNumRrcEmergency <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (3) if riEnable is set to 'true' AND riPerM is set to '1' maxNumRrcEmergency <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection for an emergency call The emercency call is only recognized when the UE was in idle state before initiating the connection. The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed: 10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 0 .. 600 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 0 .. 400 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: 10 MHz bandwidth, 300 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.1, 400 20 MHz bandwidth, TDD conf.2, 300

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumUeDl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This is the maximum number of simultaneous users scheduled in a TTI in downlink. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 1.. 7 3 MHz bandwidth: 1..7 5 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 7 10 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 14 15 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 17 20 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 20 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths.
TDD specific comment: Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in each TTI Range depends on chBw value as follows: chBw = '10.0 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...10 chBw = '20.0 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...12 Default value depends on Channel Bandwidth parameter as follows: 10.0 MHz => 10 20.0 MHz => 12

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumUeUl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This is the maximum number of simultaneous users scheduled in a TTI in uplink. The following values are allowed: 1.4 MHz bandwidth 1.. 7 3 MHz bandwidth: 1..7 5 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 7 10 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 14 15 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 17 20 MHz bandwidth 1 .. 20 Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths.
TDD specific comment: Maximum Number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI Range depends on chBw value as follows: chBw = '10.0 MHz', value range is restricted to 1…10 chBw = '20.0 MHz', value range is restricted to 1…12 Default value depends on Channel Bandwidth parameter as follows: 10.0 MHz => 10 20.0 MHz => 12

typedef.name: TOaMMinBitrateDl
typedef.comment: Minimum bit rate that shall be granted in DL TTI.

typedef.name: TOaMMinBitrateUl
typedef.comment: Minimum bit rate that shall be granted in UL TTI.

typedef.name: TOaMMobStateParamNCelChgHgh
typedef.comment: The number of cell changes to enter the high mobility state. Corresponds to NCR_H in TS 36.304.

typedef.name: TOaMMobStateParamNCelChgMed
typedef.comment: The number of cell changes to enter the medium mobility state. Corresponds to NCR_M in TS 36.304.

typedef.name: TOaMN1PucchAn
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Offset used to calculate ACK/NACK resource from PDCCH CCE. This is the AckNack index offset relative to the lowest CCE index of the associated DL scheduling PDCCH. In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: if riEnable is set to 'true' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is false.
TDD specific comment: This is the AckNack index offset relative to the lowest CCE index of the associated DL scheduling PDCCH. Parameter is one parameter in a set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called as MaxPucchResourceSize.

typedef.name: TOaMNCqiRb
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter nCqiRb is the number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b. It is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula: MaxPucchResourceSize = nCqiRb + roundup{[((rounddown (((maxNrSymPdcch * 12 - X) * dlChBw - roundup (phichRes * (dlChBw / 8)) * 12 - 16) / 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * 3 / deltaPucchShift ) * deltaPucchShift] / (3*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8)-blankedPucch, where X=4; when maxNrSymPdcch = 1 or dlMimoMode set to 'SingleTX', 'TXDiv', 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' or 'Closed Loop Mimo' X=8 when maxNrSymPdcch > 1 and dlMimoMode set to '4-way TXDiv' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' All parameters in this formula are configuration parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded. Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resouces per BW is not overcome. In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: (1) If riEnable set to 'true' AND riPerM set to '2' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (2) If riEnable set to 'true' AND riPerM set to '1' - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: This parameter is the number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b. This parameter is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula: MaxPucchResourceSize = nCqiRb + roundup{[ (max((M-i-1)* Np +i*Np1 + rounddown (((12 * (maxNrSymPdcch-Yi) - X) * chBw – mi*roundup(phichRes * (chBw / 8)) * 12 – 16 )/ 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * c / deltaPucchShift) * deltaPucchShift] / (c*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8), All other parameters in this formula are O&M parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resouces per BW is not overcome.

typedef.name: TOaMP0NomPucch
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the cell specific nominal power to be used for PUCCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P2), for controlling mean received SNR for control data.

typedef.name: TOaMP0NomPusch
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the cell specific nominal power for the PUSCH. Used for P0_PUSCH calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1) for controlling the mean received SNR for user data during (re)transmission corresponding to a received PDCCH with DCI format 0 associated with a new packet transmission. This parameter is used to control mean received SNR for user data.

typedef.name: TOaMPMax
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter defines the maximum output power of the cell per antenna carrier in dBm. The maximum output power is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all downlink physical channels that is allowed to be used in a cell. The reference point is the antenna connector. The most common configurable dBm values correspond to following Watt: 10.0 dBm = 10 mW 37.0 dBm = 5 W 39.0 dBm = 8 W 40.0 dBm = 10 W 41.8 dBm = 15 W 43.0 dBm = 20 W 44.3 dBm = 27 W 44.8 dBm = 30 W 46.0 dBm = 40 W 46.5 dBm = 45 W 47.8 dBm = 60 W 49.0 dBm = 80 W For low power RRH the carrier power value is used for repeater(s) connected to low power RRH, where the carrier power value in RRH is fixed. For example FHCB output power is fixed to 10 mW (10 dBm) and FHEC output power is fixed to 1 mW (0 dBm). Note for LTE-GSM sharing configurations: 45W and 80W power level is only supported in LTE dedicated configuration. Note: The allowed cell power value which are allowed to be configured depend on the used hardware variant. During online commissioning the BTS Site Manager will based on the hardware variant support only the allowed values. Please refer to the documentation where per variant the supported power values are specified.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: This parameter defines the maximum output power of the cell. The maximum output power is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all downlink physical channels that is allowed to be used in a cell. The reference point is the antenna connector. The most common configurable dBm values correspond to following Watt: 10.0 dBm = 10 mW 37.0 dBm = 5 W 38.8 dBm = 7.5W 39.0 dBm = 8 W 40.0 dBm = 10 W 40.8 dBm = 12 W 41.8 dBm = 15 W 42.0 dBm = 16 W 43.0 dBm = 20 W 44.8 dBm = 30 W 46.0 dBm = 40 W 47.0 dBm = 50 W 49.0 dBm = 80 W Note: In case of FYRN is used, only 40 dBm are supported. Note: The allowed cell power value which are allowed to be configured depend on the used hardware variant. During online commissioning the BTS Site Manager will based on the hardware variant support only the allowed values. Please refer to the documentation where per variant the supported power values are specified.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: pMaxIntraF
member.comment: Pmax to be used for the intra-frequency neighboring EUTRA cells. If pmax is absent, the maximum power according to the UE capability is used.

member.name: pMaxOwnCell
member.comment: The IE P-Max is used to limit the UE's uplink transmission power on a carrier frequency; it is also used to calculate the parameter P-compensation defined in TS 36.304 . Corresponds to parameter PEMAX in TS 36.101. The UE transmit power should not exceed the minimum of this value (in dBm), if provided, and the maximum UE power for the UE power class, PUMAX, as specified in TS 36.101.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAggMsg4
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the reserved number of Control Channel Elements (CCEs) for dedicated Random Access Message 4 assignment on PDCCH.
TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the reserved number of Control Channel Elements (CCEs) for dedicated Random Access Message 4 assingment on PDCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAggPaging
typedef.comment: PDCCH aggregation for paging defines how many CCEs shall be used for one PDCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAggPreamb
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the aggregation level by means of control channel elements (CCEs) for preamble assignments on PDCCH. The preamble assignment is message 0 sent during the non-contention based Random Access procedure if DL data arrives during UL out-of-sync.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAggRaresp
typedef.comment: PDCCH aggregation for Random Access response message defines how many CCEs are used for one PDCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAggSib
typedef.comment: PDCCH aggregation for secondary system information defines how many CCEs should be used for one PDCCH.

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchAlpha
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter defines the limit for PDCCH allocations. PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is multiplied by this factor. The parameter will be ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'. If dlChBw equals '3 MHz' it is recommended to set the parameter to '1.0'.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the limit for PDCCH allocations. PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is multiplied by this factor.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: pdcchCqiShift
member.comment:
The fine-tuning parameter for adjustment of measured and averaged CQI towards lower or higher aggregation in PDCCH Link Adaptation. The parameter gives the initial starting point for PDCCH shift dynamic control in case actOlLaPdcch is true. The configured PDCCH CQI shift value is automatically adjusted for control channels boosting in need basis.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: pdcchHarqTargetBler
member.comment:
BLER target for PDCCH outer loop link adaptation in percent. Defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of PDCCH and UL HARQ response for initial downlink transmissions for PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percents. If PDCCH OLLA is additionally based on PUSCH TX/DTX detection, the parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of PDCCH and PUSCH missed detection for initial uplink transmissions for PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percents.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPdcchUlDlBal
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: PDCCH allocation balance initial between UL and DL for load adaptive PDCCH The parameter determines initial value the PDCCH allocation balance constant between uplink and downlink. The Load Adaptive PDCCH algorithm optimizes the value depending on the actual load distribution between DL and UL In fact, the PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is divided into uplink and downlink based on the parameter before dynamic schedulings. The parameter pdcchUlDlBal (PDCCH LA UL DL allocation balance constant) has been originally introduced as fixed factor of split of UL and DL PDCCH resources. When Usage Based PDCCH is activated by means of parameter actLdPdcch, the pdcchUlDlBal parameter is used as an initial value of the split and as a sort of target value of the algorithm adapting the split. Please note that the parameter is ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code! TDD specific comment: PDCCH allocation balance initial between UL and DL for load adaptive PDCCH The parameter determines initial value the PDCCH allocation balance constant between uplink and downlink. The Load Adaptive PDCCH algorithm optimizes the value depending on the actual load distribution between DL and UL In fact, the PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is divided into uplink and downlink based on the parameter before dynamic schedulings. The parameter pdcchUlDlBal (PDCCH LA UL DL allocation balance constant) has been originally introduced as fixed factor of split of UL and DL PDCCH resources. When Usage Based PDCCH is activated by means of parameter actLdPdcch, the pdcchUlDlBal parameter is used as an initial value of the split and as a sort of target value of the algorithm adapting the split.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMLncelPhyCellId
typedef.comment: Physical layer cell identity defines a cell uniquely. It consists of two parts; physical layer cell identity group and physical layer identity, and is calculated with the following formula: physical layer cell identity = 3 x physical layer cell identity group + physical layer identity. Guidance for configuration: Neighbor cells should have different values, and in a three cell eNB all cells should have phyCellId which belongs to same physical layer cell identity group. For example, in a three cell eNB, good PhyCellIds values are 0, 1, 2

typedef.name: TOaMPrachCS
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Preamble cyclic shift defines the configuration which is used for preamble generation. The configuration determines how many cyclic shifts are needed to generate preamble. Unrestricted set is supported. Configuration also defines the zero correlation zone and respective maximum cell range.
TDD specific comment: Preamble cyclic shift defines the configuration which is used for preamble generation. The configuration determines how many cyclic shifts are needed to generate preamble. Configuration also defines the zero correlation zone and respective maximum cell range.

typedef.name: TOaMPrachConfIndex
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines allowed system frame and subframe numbers for random access attempts, and the preamble format. For a cell with bandwidth 1.4 MHz the following prachConfIndex values are recommended dependent on the physical cell id (PCI): - PCI modulo 3 = 0 => prachConfIndex = 3 (PRACH format 0) or 19 (PRACH format 1) i.e. PRACH occasion is within TTI 1 - PCI modulo 3 = 1 => prachConfIndex = 4 (PRACH format 0) or 20 (PRACH format 1) i.e. PRACH occasion is within TTI 4 - PCI modulo 3 = 2 => prachConfIndex = 5 (PRACH format 0) or 21 (PRACH format 1) i.e. PRACH occasion is within TTI 7
TDD specific comment: Defines allowed system frame and subframe numbers for random access attempts, and the preamble format.

typedef.name: TOaMPrachFreqOff
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the location in frequency for the PRACH transmissions. For UL scheduling its recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocation for UE consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs effectively. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH. It is recommended to set the value such that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH RBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH; thus recommended parameter alternatives are: 1) roundup((MaxPucchResourceSize+blankedPucch)/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or 2) ulChBw(in PRBs)-6-roundup((MaxPucchResourceSize+blankedPucch)/2 ) if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area The MaxPucchResourceSize in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH RBs, and it defined in nCqiRb parameter.
TDD specific comment: Defines the location in frequency for the PRACH transmissions.For UL scheduling its recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocation for UE consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs effectively. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH. Defines the first physical resource block allocated for PRACH In case of preamble format 4 for special subframe, prachFreqOff must be set to 0. In case of preamble format 0, 1 and 2 for normal subframe, recommendation is to set value so that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH RBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH, and thus recommended parameter alternatives are: 1) roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or 2) ulChBw-6-roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize/2 if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area The MaxPucchResourceSize in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH RBs, and it defined in nCqiRb parameter.

member.name: prsNumDlFrames
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: Number of DL Frames that are used for PRS per PRS occasion for FDD. With this PRS transmission can be repeated within a PRS occasion in order to increase the hearability of PRS
TDD specific comment: Number of DL Frames that are used for PRS per PRS occasion for TDD. With this PRS transmission can be repeated within a PRS occasion in order to increase the hearability of PRS

member.name: prsPowerBoost
member.comment:
Power Boosting for PRS increases hearability and allows for a more flexible use of the DL Tx power. With de-boosting it is possible to lower PRS power in interference sensitive areas. PRS power is related to DL RS power, and when prsPowerBoost is set to value 0dB, and dlRsBoost is set to same 0dB value, PRS and DL RS has same power in each TX Antenna. Note also the case when actPrsTxDiv is TRUE. Power is same in each TX Antenna, but as PRS is transmitted at the same time from each used TX Antenna, sum of PRS power over all TX Antennas are higher. To compensate power in TxDiv case, prsPowerBoost can be set to proper value. See examples below: Example 1: dlMimoMode is set to TxDiv, value -3 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power. Example 2: dlMimoMode is set to 4-way TxDiv, value -6 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power. Example 3: dlMimoMode is set to Closed Loop MIMO (4x2), value -3 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMPucchNAnCs
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Number of cyclic shifts for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b in a resource block used for a mix of formats 1/1a/b and 2/2a/2b.
TDD specific comment: This is the number of cyclic shifts for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b in a resource block used for a mix of formats 1/1a/b and 2/2a/2b. This parameter is one of the parameters in a set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called as MaxPucchResourceSize.

typedef.name: TOaMPuschCqiOffI

typedef.name: TOaMPuschRiOffI
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the delta offset index for the decoding of the Rank Indicator information on the PUSCH channel.

member.name: qRxLevMinOffset
member.comment: Affects the minimum required RX level in the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMRaLargeMcsUl
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used for large size random access message 3 in case of initial access or handover. The size of the large size Random Access Msg3 may be restricted depending on the setting of raLargeMcsUl. ulChBw = '1.4 Mhz', if raLargeMcsUl is equal to the default, the TBS of Msg3 is 328 bit ulChBw = '3 Mhz', if raLargeMcsUl is equal to the default, the TBS of Msg3 is 504 bit
TDD specific comment: Defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used for large size random access message 3 in case of initial access or handover.

member.name: rand
member.comment: Defines the random challenge value. This parameter is sent in the RRC CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 messages during CDMA2000 1xRTT pre-registration procedure; and it is also sent in the RRC HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest and S1AP UPLINK S1 CDMA2000 TUNNELING during the 1x Circuit Switched Fallback (1xCSFB) procedure.

member.name: rcAmbrMgnDl
member.comment:
The parameter determines the multiplier for non-GBR (non-Guaranteed Bit Rate) radio bearers AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate) in order to consider overhead caused by PDCP and RLC layers.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: rcAmbrMgnUl

member.name: redBwMaxRbDl
member.comment: This parameter defines the maximum UE-specific PRB assingment per TTI in downlink. Note that this value will be rounded up in the RRM algorithm to fit the system bandwidth dependent RGB granularity.

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwSgbGroup
typedef.comment: Group index which together with set index (redBwSgbSet) defines the pre-provisioned set of soft guard band. Parameter modification requires object (cell) locking.

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwSgbSet
typedef.comment: Set index which together with group index (redBwSgbGroup) defines the pre-provisioned set of soft guard band. Parameter modification requires object (cell) locking.

typedef.name: TOaMRiPerOffset
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the offset for periodic Rank Indicator reporting instance. The offset tells the time shift for the periodic CQI/PMI reporting instance. The range of the offset depends on the periodicity (cqiPerNp) of periodic CQI/PMI reporting.

typedef.name: TOaMRootSeqIndex
typedef.comment: The premable generation is started from the Root Sequence which is pointed by the logical root sequence number. 64 preambles can be transmitted in the PRACH frame. If one root is not enough to generate all the 64 preambles, then the consecutive number is selected until the full set is generated. RACH root sequence is cell specific information and neighbouring cells should have a different value. RACH root sequence is transmitted in system information.

member.name: rttCellIdInfo
member.comment: This parameter indicates whether 1x cell Identifier shall be used by this cell to build IE “CDMA2000 1xRTT Pilot List” when sending UPLINK S1 CDMA2000 TUNNELING message to the MME during e1xCSFB preparation procedure. Value 0 means "000": A Cell Identifier field is not included for this pilot. The pilot is an actual 1x pilot. Value 1 means "001": A 1x Cell Identifier field is included for this pilot. The pilot is an actual 1x pilot.

member.name: sIntrasearch
member.comment: The Sintrasearch parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for intra-frequency measurements. The UE can omit measurements of intra-frequency neighbor cells if the serving cell is above a certain threshold.

member.name: sNonIntrsearch
member.comment: The sNonintrsearch parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for inter-RAT and inter-frequency measurements.

typedef.name: TOaMSrbSchedWeightDl
typedef.comment: Downlink scheduling weight for Signalling Radio Bearer 1 and 2 for the uplink scheduler in MAC.

typedef.name: TOaMSrbSchedWeightUl
typedef.comment: Uplink scheduling weight for Signalling Radio Bearer 1 and 2 for the uplink scheduler in MAC.

member.name: srsConfiguration

Operator choses a given configuration number for a cell and the system depending on system BW and configuration value define the correct sounding setting. All the odd numbered configurations imply 10ms UE periodicity, while the even-numbered configurations imply UE periodicity set to 5ms. ulChBw =20MHz => Configuration 1: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (16 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 2: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (16 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 3: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=2 (20 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 4: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=2 (20 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) ulChBw =15MHz=> Configuration 1: SRS C1: CSRS=0, BSRS=2 (12 PRBs per UE);SRS C2: CSRS=0, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 2: SRS C1: CSRS=0, BSRS=2 (12 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=0, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 3: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (16 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1 BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 4: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (16 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) ulChBw =10MHz=> Configuration 1: SRS C1: CSRS=0, BSRS=2 (12 PRBs per UE);SRS C2: CSRS=0, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 2: SRS C1: CSRS=0, BSRS=2 (12 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=0, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 3: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (8 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1 BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 4: SRS C1: CSRS=1, BSRS=2 (8 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=1, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 5: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=1 (20PRBs per UE);SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 6: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=1 (20 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 7: SRS C1: CSRS=4, BSRS=2 (8 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=4 BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 8: SRS C1: CSRS=4, BSRS=2 (8 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=4, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) ulChBw =5MHz=> Configuration 1: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=0 (24 PRBs per UE);SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 2: SRS C1: CSRS=2, BSRS=0 (24 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=2, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 3: SRS C1: CSRS=3, BSRS=0 (20 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=3 BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE) Configuration 4: SRS C1: CSRS=3, BSRS=0 (20 PRBs per UE); SRS C2: CSRS=3, BSRS=3 (4 PRBs per UE)

member.name: srsPwrOffset
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: UE specific power offset to be used for Sounding Reference Signal transmission power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P3). Note: The actual power offset depends on value of deltaTfEnabled. For deltaTfEnabled = 'true' (KS = 1.25) the actual parameter value is "srsPwrOffset-3" corresponding to the dB-range of -3 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1 dB. For deltaTfEnabled = 'false' (KS = 0) the actual parameter value is "-10.5 + 1.5 * srsPwrOffset" value corresponding to the dB-range -10.5 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1.5 dB.
TDD specific comment: UE specific power offset to be used for Sounding Reference Signal transmission power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P3). SRS will be implicitly disabled if PUSCH masking is configured. The parameter is therefore not relevant and ignored if PUSCH masking is activated, i.e. if actPuschMask is equal to "true". Note: The actual power offset depends on value of deltaTfEnabled. For deltaTfEnabled = 'true' (KS = 1.25) the actual parameter value is "srsPwrOffset-3" corresponding to the dB-range of -3 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1 dB. For deltaTfEnabled = 'false' (KS = 0) the actual parameter value is "-10.5 + 1.5 * srsPwrOffset" value corresponding to the dB-range -10.5 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1.5 dB.

typedef.name: TOaMStInactFactor
typedef.comment: Factor with which the DRX Inactivity Timer of the DRX profile as applied for a UE is multiplied in order to determine how long to keep a UE UL synchronized following last transmission of new data.

typedef.name: TOaMT302
typedef.comment: eNB sends this parameter to the UE in the message RRC CONNECTION REJECT. The UE will consider access to the cell as barred for the time specified by t302.

typedef.name: TOaMTExtendedWait
typedef.comment: tExtendedWait suppresses the reselection of a cell for a while. eNB sends this parameter to the UE in the message RRC CONNECTION REJECT and RRC CONNECTION RELEASE, and only in case of Delay Tolerant access request. The UE will consider access to the cell as barred for the time specified by teWait.

member.name: tPageCorrInt
member.comment: A RRC connection setup request which is correlated to (i.e. matches by s-TMSI) a S1 paging with priority will be prioritized ("emergency callback"). The timer determines the maximum time between the S1 paging and its correlated RRC connection setup request. When the parameter is set to value "0" any correlation is disabled.

typedef.name: TOaMTPingPong
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the maximum time interval which may elapse from when a UE has left a cell by handover till when it returns to that cell by another handover in order to consider such event as a PingPong

typedef.name: TOaMTReselEutr
typedef.comment: The Treselection parameter defines the cell reselection timer value. It allows averaging of the target cell quality before cell reselection is performed.

typedef.name: TOaMTStoreUeCntxt
typedef.comment: This timer is started when an UE enters a cell by handover or RRC Re-Establishment. The timer controls how long the context needed to send an X2AP: HANDOVER REPORT is stored in the new cell after handover. No special action is triggered on timer expiry

typedef.name: TOaMTaMaxOffset
typedef.comment:
Determines the maximum allowed Time Alignment offset. If the value is exceeded, TA command is sent to the UE to adjust UL timing.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTaTimerMargin

typedef.name: TOaMLncelTac

member.name: threshServingLowQR9

typedef.name: TOaMThreshSrvLow

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold1
typedef.comment: Threshold Th1 for RSRP If RSRP of serving cell is greater than Th1, only the serving cell is measured. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

member.name: threshold2GERAN
member.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of GERAN Measurements Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If the value is below threshold2GERAN (event A2) , GERAN measurements are started. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

member.name: threshold2Hrpd
member.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of CDMA2000-eHRPD measurements Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If value below threshold2Hrpd (event A2) then CDMA2000-eHRPD measurements are started. Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4 The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

member.name: threshold2InterFreq
member.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If the value is below Th2_InterFreq, inter frequency measurements are started. member.name: threshold2Wcdma

If the value is below threshold2Wcdma (event A2) , WCDMA measurements are started. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

member.name: threshold2a
member.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (InterFreq) Measurements Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If Inter-RAT (InterFreq) measurements are active and value exceeds Th2a (event A1) then Inter-RAT measurements are stopped. Th2_XXX <= Th2a for XXX= InterFreq, WCDMA, GSM, CDMA2000-HRPD The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold3
typedef.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving cell is lower than threshold3 and RSRP of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3a, a handover is triggered. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold3a
typedef.comment: Threshold for RSRP of intra-frequency neighbor cell. If RSRP of serving cell is lower than threshold3 and RSRP of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3a, a handover is triggered. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold4

The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

member.name: ttiBundlingBlerTarget
member.comment:
BLER target value for link adaption while in TTI Bundling mode
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: ttiBundlingBlerThreshold

SINR threshold for switching UEs from TTI-Bundling mode into non-TTI-bundling mode

typedef.name: TOaMUlRsCs
typedef.comment: Defines cyclic shift of uplink reference signals.

typedef.name: TOaMUlTargetBler
typedef.comment: Defines target Block Error Ratio for uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding.

typedef.name: TOaMUlamcSwitchPer
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the period in sent Transport Blocks (TBs) when uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inner loop functionalities should be executed. Depending on the parameter ulAmcEnableAllTbs, all TBs or 1st transmission TBs have been calculated for the period. MCS increase/decrease based on the UL AMC inner loop factor can be only done after the period ends.

typedef.name: TOaMUlatbEventPer
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the period in MCS increase/decrease events when uplink Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth (ATB) functionality should be performed. MCS change events are calculated and UL ATB functionality is executed every time the event counter reaches the value defined in the parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcRarespTpc
typedef.comment:
TPC command indicated in the Random Access response related to Random Access message 3 or 1st scheduled uplink transmission.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the MULTIPLICAND in your code!

member.name: ulpcReadPeriod
member.comment: Time interval for sending averaged RSSI and SINR values to the decision matrix to determine power corrections in closed loop uplink power control.

typedef.name: TOaMUlsMaxPacketAgg
typedef.comment: Maximum number of aggregated VoIP packets in UL (with Inter Arrival Time of 20 ms) Defines the maximum number of VoIP packets which may be aggregated for UL transmission based on a IAT of 20 ms. If the IAT of the VoIP packets is 10 ms the maximum packet aggregation is {1,3,5,7}. Note that values of the parameter are {1,2,3,4} regardless of Inter Arrival Time, therefore following mapping is used to configure UL Packet Aggregation for IAT of 10ms – ulsMaxPacketAgg value (aggregation level with IAT of 10ms) -> 1 (1), 2 (3), 3 (5), 4 (7).

typedef.name: TOaMUlsMinRbPerUe
typedef.comment: Defines the minimum PRB allocation for UEs which are power limited. This is used for the UEs for which the maximum number of PRBs due to power limitation is limited to low values (e.g. <= 5).

typedef.name: TOaMUlsMinTbs
typedef.comment: Defines the minimum UL TBS (segment size). The lower limit of the range is defined equal to the minimum transport block size (TBS) in the Table 7.1.7.2.1-1 in 3GPP TS 36.213. The upper limit of the range is defined equal to the TBS belonging to modulation order 2 and 10 PRBs.

member.name: upperMarginCIO
member.comment: This parameter defines the maximum value that a CIO can assume, when changed autonomously by the eNB during for example the intra-frequency load balancing function.

typedef.name: TOaMBfCqiThDown
typedef.comment:
CQI threshold for switching from dual codeword to single codeword in case of TM8 If the current CQI is less than or equal to bfCqiThDown, OR current rank is less than or equal to bfRankThDown, then switching from dual codeword to single codeword for TM8.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMBfCqiThUp
typedef.comment:

member.name: b2Threshold1GERAN

If RSRP of serving value < b2Threshold1Utra and RSCP or EcN of WCDMA neighbour cell > b2Threshold2Utra<EcNo, Rscp> then handover is triggered (B2 event) Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1Utra AND the WCDMA neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2Utra<EcNo, Rscp> (dep. measQuantityUtra). Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMB2Threshold2RssiGERAN

Receive level threshold for GERAN neighbour cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1 AND the GERAN neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2RssiGERAN. Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for GERAN. Note: The mapping for RSRP based GERAN thresholds is different from the one defined in 3GPP TS 36.133 and are defined in TS 45.008 The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 45.008: * -110 dBm means a threshold lower than -110 dBm * values between -109 dBm and -48 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -47 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -48 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMRttStrengthThresh
typedef.comment:
Defines the pilot strength threshold for enhanced CSFB to CDMA2000 1xRTT. In 3GPP TS36.331, pilotStrength's range is [0 .. 63] which is different from current value range of paramter "rttStrengthThresh". The reason is that : in future phase 2 e1xCsfb feature, this parameter may be re-used as AggregatedThreshold which include strengths from multiple PNs and AggregatedThreshold 's value range is [-18 .. 63]. The formula used by the UE to report the pilot strength is [ -2 * 10 * log (measured pilot strength) ]. Therefore 63 maps to -31.5 dB. So [-18..63] maps to [9..-31.5] dB.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniqely identifies of a neighboring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN. Values in the range of 4096 .. 65535 are considered as Extended RNC-ID. The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).
TDD specific comment: This parameter is the UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniqely identifies of a neighboring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN.

member.name: angle
member.comment:
The elevation angle between the direction orthogonal to the antenna element axis and the maximum of its main beam in the elevation plane. A positive electrical tilt angle means that the antenna beam is directed below the direction orthogonal to the antenna axis. The BTS creates the parameter to SCF. The parameter value is read from device. The user sets the parameter value at least once according to the configuration/network plan. Otherwise, the present value (factory or old setting) exists. Setting tilt angle of a RET device might take up to 2 minutes according to 3GPP stardards. A typical time for the calibration is approximately 15-30 seconds. According to 3GPP standards, setting tilt of several devices connected onto one antenna line is done as a series of consecutive operation by the system. In addition, set tilt and calibration (for more details of calibration, see calibrate parameter documentation) are done as consecutive operations. When such a situation occurs, accumulative time for the operations may be increased long enough as to not be feasible to be activated in one plan. Thus, in such case, time consuming operations should be devided into the 2 or more plans.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

This parameter defines the maximum allowed electrical tilt value. Changing the minimum or maximum values may cause incorrect tilt functionality if the values are not in the proper range. It is recommended to enter values only if they are not retrieved from the device after configuration file activation. User defined values are not taken into use if configuration file is updated with the same plan file (i.e. the user-defined values are overwritten). The minimum value should be smaller than the maximum value.

typedef.name: TOaMRetAntUnitNumber
typedef.comment: The RET antenna unit number. For a single-antenna RET device, the RET antenna unit number is always 1. For a multi-antenna RET device, the RET antenna unit number starts at 1 and increases by 1 for each controlled antenna, with no numbering gaps allowed. The RET antenna unit number identifies a specific antenna control (actuator) on a multi-antenna RET device. The RET antenna unit number identifies the antenna controlled by a RET device. A single-antenna RET device controls only 1 antenna. Therefore, the RET antenna unit number is always 1. A multi-antenna RET device controls multiple antennas. For a multi-antenna RET, the RET antenna unit number starts at 1 and increases by 1 for each controlled antenna, with no numbering gaps allowed. Note: for a multi-antenna RET device, the RET antenna unit number identifies a specific antenna control (actuator) and corresponds to the "Antenna Number" parameter on the 3GPP Iuant interface (3GPP 25.463/25.466).

typedef.name: TOaMRetId
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the specific RET (Remote Electrical Tilting), which is vertical tilting for antenna.

typedef.name: TOaMRmodRModId
typedef.comment: This parameter identifies the radio module associated with the antenna line.

typedef.name: TOaMAssocMaxRetrans
typedef.comment: This is the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring the SCTP association failure.

typedef.name: TOaMMaxTimeSctpSetup
typedef.comment: The overall maximum time that the eNB is trying to establish a SCTP association to a newly learned adjacent eNB after the eNB has received the IP address via ANR. The time the eNB is trying to establish mustn’t exceed maxSctpSetupTime. Note: In case of long maxTimeSctpSetup interval it might happen that STCP layer has already finished transmitting SCTP INIT sequence before maxTimeSctpSetup expires. In case of short maxTimeSctpSetup interval, the eNB signalling application will finish SCTP INIT retransmission before SCTP computed time interval expires.

typedef.name: TOaMPathMaxRetrans
typedef.comment: This is the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring SCTP path failure.

typedef.name: TOaMRtoMax
typedef.comment: This parameter specifies the maximum value for retransmission timer T3-rtx when DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. Used for SCTP calculation range.

typedef.name: TOaMRtoMin
typedef.comment: This parameter specifies the minimum value for retransmission timer T3-rtx when DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. Used for the SCTP calculation range.

typedef.name: TOaMSctpHeartbeatInterval
typedef.comment: This parameter defines the interval between two SCTP heartbeat messages, counted in seconds.

typedef.name: TOaMSctpId
typedef.comment: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SCTP.

typedef.name: TOaMSmodSModId
typedef.comment: System Module identification in terms of its distname index. The position of this radio module is defined with respect to this index

typedef.name: TOaMTResUtra

typedef.name: TOaMUffimId
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter uniquely identifies an UFFIM (UTRAN FDD Frequency Idle Mode configuration) managed object.

member.name: ulCoMpCellList

typedef.name: TOaMUlCoMpSinrThreshold
typedef.comment: Signal-Interference-Noise Ratio to be use for uplink CoMP operation. Received uplink signal from a neighbor cell is combined to the serving cell signal if signal level exceeds the set SINR threshold level.

typedef.name: TOaMAuth

typedef.name: TOaMGcsnaL2AckTimer
typedef.comment:
Defines the length of time the Inter Working Solution (IWS) waits for an acknowledgment after it sends the GCSNA1xCircuitService message indicating an acknowledgment is required. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMGcsnaSequenceContextTimer
typedef.comment:
Defines the length of time the UE retains the last received Generic Circuit Services Notification Application (GCSNA) sequence number and IWS_ID. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMImsi11and12
typedef.comment: Defines the 11th and 12th digits of an International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI). - When an IMSI has 12 or more digits, IMSI_11_12 is equal to the 11th and 12th digits of the IMSI. - When an IMSI has fewer than 12 digits, digits with a value equal to zero are added to the most significant side to obtain a total of 12 digits and the IMSI_11_12 is equal to the 11th and 12th digits of the resulting number. This field is sent as a 7-bit binary representation in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode. Set this parameter to the integer obtained by encoding the 12th and 11th digits of the IMSI using the formula 10 x D12 + D11 - 11. Where: D11 is the 11th digit D12 is the 12th digit If the digit is equal to zero, then 10 is used For example, for an IMSI_11_12 of '04', the derived value 93 (= 10 x 10 + 4 - 11) should be set for this parameter. The decimal value 127 corresponds to the escape code of all 1's: '1111111'.

typedef.name: TOaMLeapSecond
typedef.comment: Defines the total number of leap seconds since the start of CDMA System Time (i.e. since Jan 6, 1980 00:00:00 UTC). This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the lpSecIncluded parameter is set to TRUE. The UE uses this parameter to derive UTC time by subtracting the received leap second value from CDMA System Time which the UE receives in SIB8.

typedef.name: TOaMLocalTimeOff
typedef.comment:
Defines the local time offset from CDMA system time. CDMA system time is based on GPS time. CDMA system time differs from local time by the local time offset and the number of leap seconds by which UTC and GPS time differ. The mobile station calculates the local time using the relation: local time = CDMA time - leap seconds + local time offset This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the ltmOffIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMMaxNumAltSo
typedef.comment: Defines the maximum number of alternative service options that the UE is allowed to include in the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) Origination message or in the CDMA2000 1xRTT Page Response message. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMMccXrtt
typedef.comment: Defines the 3-digit MCC (Mobile Country Code) of the PLMN for the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor. A special value 1023 is also defined to correspond to the 3GPP2 escape code. At eNB, the 3-digit MCC will be converted to 10-bit binary code according to MCC encoding rule (Refer to 3GPP2 C.S005-E, Section 2.3.1.3), and the special value is converted to the 3GPP2 escape code of all 1's: '1111111111'. The final 10-bit binary code will be used to populate MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE).

typedef.name: TOaMMinPRev
typedef.comment: Defines the minimum protocol revision level. This field is set to prevent UEs which cannot be supported by the Inter-Working Solution (IWS) from accessing the system. The eNodeB shall set this field to the minimum protocol revision level that the IWS supports. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMPRev
typedef.comment: Defines the Protocol Revision level of the CDMA2000 1xRTT network. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMPilotInc
typedef.comment: Defines the pilot Pseudo-Random Noise (PN) sequence offset index increment. A UE searches for Remaining Set pilots at pilot PN sequence index values that are multiples of this value. Set this field to the pilot PN sequence increment, in units of 64 PN chips, which UEs use for searching the remaining set. Set this field to the largest increment such that the pilot PN sequence offsets of all neighboring CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) base stations are integer multiples of that increment. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the pilotIncIncuded parameter is set to TRUE.

typedef.name: TOaMXparamId
typedef.comment: This parameter is the naming attribute Of MOC XPARAM. It uniquely identifies a XPARAM instance.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrPrTId
typedef.comment: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRT object. An Automatic Neighbour Relationship Profile (ANRPRT) defines carrier frequency specific settings for automatic detection of TD-SCDMA neighbor cells.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrprtAnrUtraRscpThres
typedef.comment: It defines the minimum power level that a UE should report from a measured UTRA cell for considering the corresponding PCI, respectively PSC, as a possible UTRA neighbor cell candidate. The mapping between the UE measured RSCP and the configured value is according to 3GPP TS 25.133/25.123. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133: * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

member.name: cellsToApplyList
member.comment: The parameter allows to restrict the ANR profile to certain LTE cells which are identified by their lncelId. If the parameter is omitted or the list is empty the profile is considered as default profile which applies to all cells with no dedicated profile.

typedef.name: TOaMLnRelTLimitForAnr
typedef.comment: The parameter allows limiting the number of TD-SCDMA neighbor relations (LNRELT instances) per UTRAN carrier frequency and LTE cell. This limit applies only for ANR created LNRELT instances but does not apply for LNRELT instances, which are manually created via plan file. If the limit is already reached or even exceeded by manually created LNRELT instances, no additional LNRELT instances referring to TD-SCDMA neighbor cells with the profile carrier frequency will be added by ANR. If the number of neighbor relations (LNRELT instances) exceeds the maximum number of TD-SCDMA neighbor cells which might be used by eNB in measurement configurations (limit in 3GPP 36.331) but the limit which ich configured with lnRelTLimitForAnr is not yet reached, then eNB will create new LNLRELT instances with handoverAllowed set to 'forbidden'. This is to ease further manual optimization of neighbour cell blacklisting.

typedef.name: TOaMAnrprtUtraCarrierFreq
typedef.comment: The parameter identifies the UTRA DL carrier frequency for which this ANR profile applies.

typedef.name: TOaMLnAdjTId
typedef.comment: Uniquely identifies a UTRAN (TD-SCDMA) neighbour cell within an eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUTargetCId
typedef.comment: Target C-ID Uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC. Required (together with the RNC ID) for the Source RNC To Target RNC Transparent Container IE in the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUTargetFreq
typedef.comment: Target Frequency UtranTarget_FREQ provides the DL Carrier Frequency of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the primary scrambling code identifies a neighbouring UTRAN cell

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUTargetLac
typedef.comment: Target Location Area Code UtranTarget_LAC provides the Location Area Code identifying the Location Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUTargetRac
typedef.comment: Target Routing Area Code UtranTarget_RAC provides the Routing Area Code identifying the Routing Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUTargetRncId
typedef.comment: Target RNC ID Uniquely identifies a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

typedef.name: TOaMLnadjtUtraTddPci
typedef.comment: Physical cell Id of the TD-SCDMA neighbor cel The cell parameter Id (TDD) of the TD-SCDMA neighbor cell which is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell. Received from RRMT-CMC in the TCL, which together with the cell frequency identifies a TD-SCDMA cell.

member.name: b1ThresholdCSFBUtraRscp
member.comment: Threshold for UTRA neighbour cell on the current frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event. PCCPCH-RSCP is defined in TS 25.123 for TDD. Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.123: * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMLnhotB2Threshold1Utra
typedef.comment: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value < b2Threshold1Utra and RSCP of TD-SCDMA neighbour cell > b2Threshold2UtraRscp, then handover is triggered (B2 event) Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1Utra AND the TD-SCDMA neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2UtraRscp. Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133: * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMLnhotB2Threshold2UtraRscp
typedef.comment: Threshold for UTRA neighbour cell on the current frequency, such that ist is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event. PCCPCH-RSCP corresponds to P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD. Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA. The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.123: * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB) * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

typedef.name: TOaMLnhotHysB1ThresholdCSFBUtra
typedef.comment:
Related Hysteresis of Margin for CSFB to TD-SCDMA Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMLnhotHysB2ThresholdUtra
typedef.comment:
Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for HO to TD-SCDMA Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!
