typedef.name: TOaMLnhotOffsetFreqUtra
typedef.comment: Offset value applicable to the UTRA carrier frequency. The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

typedef.name: TOaMLnhotUtraCarrierFreq
typedef.comment: Identifies UTRA carrier frequency for which this configuration is valid The IE ARFCN-ValueUTRA is used to indicate the ARFCN applicable for a downlink (Nd, FDD) or bi-directional (Nt, TDD) UTRA carrier frequency

typedef.name: TOaMLnRelTId
typedef.comment: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNRELT instance. It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnRelTId value within all LNRELT instances subordinate to an LNCEL object. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnRelTId values if an LNRELT instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.

typedef.name: TOaMLnreltUTargetCid
typedef.comment: This parameter is the UTRAN C-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC.

typedef.name: TOaMLnreltUTargetRncId
typedef.comment: This parameter is the UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniqely identifies of a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN.

enum.name: EOaMAnrprwSrvccHoInd
enum.comment: This parameter selects if SRVCC to a WCDMA target cell is performed as a combined PS and CS SRVCC or whether SRVCC is performed for the CS bearer only. The value is used if a new LNADJW object is created by eNB because of ANR measurements and if the profile applies for the detecting LTE cell. The value is only relevant if the feature LTE872 'SRVCC to WCDMA' is deployed. It is highly recommended to set this value properly even if the feature is not yet deployed but shall be deployed in future. Otherwise manual setting in all LNADJW objects becomes necessary later on if the feature LTE872 is activated. It is a capability of the target UTRAN whether 'combined PS and CS SRVCC' or 'CS SRVCC only' are supported.

enum.name: EOaMAntId
enum.comment: Identifies the specific antenna port in Flexi Radio Module for antenna line.

enum.name: EOaMFeederVoltage
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the voltage level supplied to the antenna line. The values entered for this parameter depend on the MHA type. Non-AISG NSN MHAs: WMHA, WMHB: 12 WMHC: BTS1 Automatic value (Manual voltage override is allowed: possible values [0 V / +12 V/ +14.5 V/ +24V/ +28 V (+24 /+28 only for Main branch, the value depends on the radio module type)]), BTS2 12 Non-AISG Other (3rd party) MHA: 0 (The user can change the line voltage to 12V. AISG MHAs: Currently for all AISG MHA Automatic value is used. Note: In RF sharing case this parameter value shall be set to the "Automatic" if BTS is set to the Radio slave mode (SMOD - linkList - radioMaster parameter value is set to "false").
TDD specific comment: Defines the voltage level supplied to the antenna line. The values entered for this parameter depend on the MHA type. Non-AISG NSN MHAs: WMHA, WMHB: 12 WMHC: BTS1 Automatic value (Manual voltage override is allowed: possible values [0 V / +12 V/ +14.5 V/ +24V/ +28 V (+24 /+28 only for Main branch, the value depends on the radio module type)]), BTS2 12 Non-AISG Other (3rd party) MHA: 0 (The user can change the line voltage to 12V. AISG MHAs: Currently for all AISG MHA Automatic value is used.

enum.name: EOaMBtsSyncMode
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: With this parameter the the synchronization mode of the eNB can be selected. LTE systems supporting MBSFN or co-operate with CDMA 2000 system require a tight timing on air interface transmission synchronization. In all those cases phase synchronization should be selected. For LTE systems which do not require such accurate phase synchronization, the 50ppb frequency accuracy is achieved via normal frequency synchronization. For those that value should be set. If phase synchronization is selected, only synchronization reference sources which are capable to accuracy needed by phase synchronization shall be selected. To meet a relative phase accuracy BTS can not come up without GPS connection existence and operation.
TDD specific comment: With this parameter the the synchronization mode of the eNB can be selected. TD-LTE systems require a tight timing on air interface transmission synchronization. In all those cases phase synchronization should be selected. If phase synchronization is selected, only synchronization reference sources which are capable to accuracy needed by phase synchronization shall be selected. To meet a relative phase accuracy BTS can not come up without GPS connection existence and operation.

enum.name: EOaMGpsCableLength
enum.comment: This parameter defines the cable length used between GPS receiver and eNB for official NSN cable with length of 30m, 100m or 300m . If this parameter is set, the gpsTotalAntennaLineDelay shall not be set. If an official NSN cable is replaced by a non-NSN delivered cable the parameter "Total GPS antenna line delay" must be used instead of this parameter. NSN does not assure the validity of delay calculation when using cables not ordered officially.

enum.name: EOaMBbuHotellingMode
enum.comment: Defines the BBU hotelling mode for eNB.

enum.name: EOaMCrgSkipThreshold
enum.comment: The parameter defines a thresholds above which the resource utilization within a subframe is considered efficient, in which case the subframe will be assigned to the cell resource groups in question. Otherwise, the assignment of the subframe to the cell resource group may be skipped. The value '0' means disabling subframe skipping.

enum.name: EOaMBandInd
enum.comment: This is an indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers. For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator is not relevant.

struct.name: SOaMGnflNccperm
struct.comment: This parameter restricts the permitted Network Colour Code (NCC) for idle mode mobility. Using default settings, no network is permitted. A field encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is set to "0" if a BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is not permitted for monitoring, and set to "1" if the BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is permitted for monitoring; N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the leading bit of the bit string.

enum.name: EOaMMeasBdw
enum.comment: The IE AllowedMeasBandwidth is used to indicate the maximum allowed measurement bandwidth common for all neighbouring cells on a carrier frequency. The values mbw6, mbw15, mbw25, mbw50, mbw75, mbw100 indicate 6, 15, 25, 50, 75 and 100 resource blocks respectively.

enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Frequency-specific offset for equal priority E-UTRAN frequencies.
TDD specific comment: Frequency specific offset for equal priority E-UTRAN frequencies.

enum.name: EOaMCPlaneIpAddrCtrl
enum.comment: The parameter determines whether the C-Plane IP address of the neighbor eNB (X2 link) is statically configured or whether eNB is allowed to update the address based on information provided by ANR procedures. oamControlled X2 link: It is the responsibility of the operator to configure the correct cPlaneIpAddr. enbControlled X2 link: The IP address will be maintained by ANR procedures if ANR features are activated. It is the default value for neighbor eNBs which have been learnt via ANR procedures.

enum.name: EOaMX2LinkStatus
enum.comment: The parameter provides information whether the X2 link is successfully established.

enum.name: EOaMLnadjgBandIndicatorGeran
enum.comment: Bandindicator Value of the GERAN neighbour cell (Part of CarrierFrequency) The IE BandIndicatorGERAN indicates how to interpret an associated GERAN carrier ARFCN, see TS 45.005 [20]. More specifically, the IE indicates the GERAN frequency band in case the ARFCN value can concern either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with one of these bands, the indicator is not relevant.

enum.name: EOaMNetworkControlOrder
enum.comment: Network Control Order Value of the GERAN neighbor cell, where the different parameter value mean: NC0: Normal UE control NC1: UE control with measurement reports NC2: Network control RESET: The UE shall return to the broadcast parameters.

enum.name: EOaMRimStatus
enum.comment: Provides the status of the RIM association to serving BSS. Meaning of the values: - disabled: The GERAN neighbor cell is not RIM enabled, that is the feature is not activated or PLMN of the GERAN cell is blacklisted for RIM or no RAC value is configured. - unavailable: The GERAN neighbor cell is RIM enabled but no valid system information from RIM procedure is available. - available: The GERAN neighbor cell is RIM enabled and valid system information from RIM procedure is available.

enum.name: EOaMSystemInfoType
enum.comment: This parameter is set by Operator to indicate which type of GERAN Systeminformation (if any) is included in the RRC MOBILITYFROMEUTRANCOMMAND message. The parameter is meaningless - if feature 'RIM for GSM (LTE498)' is activated and AND - the PLMN of the cell is not blacklisted for RIM and AND - parameter gTargetRac is configured.

enum.name: EOaMCpConfDL
enum.comment: Adjacent cyclic prefix configuration in DL. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.

enum.name: EOaMCpConfUL
enum.comment: Adjacent cyclic prefix configuration in DL. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.

enum.name: EOaMDlTrmBw
enum.comment: Downlink transmission bandwidth of the FDD neighbor cell. The parameter is not applicable for TDD neighbor cells. The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".

enum.name: EOaMLnadjlSourceOfData
enum.comment: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM), X2 information (X2) or UE specific ANR measurements (UE).

enum.name: EOaMSpcSubConfTD
enum.comment: Supported special subframe configuration by neighbor eNB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.

enum.name: EOaMTrmBwTD
enum.comment: Uplink and Downlink Transmission Bandwidth Of Cell Served By Neighbor ENB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells. The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".

enum.name: EOaMUlDlConfTD
enum.comment: UL and DL Configuration of a subframe in a radio frame supported by neighbor eNB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.

enum.name: EOaMUlTrmBw
enum.comment: Uplink transmission bandwidth of the FDD neighbor cell. The parameter is not applicable for TDD neighbor cells. The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".

enum.name: EOaMLnadjwSourceOfData
enum.comment: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM) or UE-specific ANR measurements (UE).

enum.name: EOaMLnadjwSrvccHoInd
enum.comment: This parameter selects if SRVCC to a WCDMA target cell is performed as a combined PS and CS SRVCC or whether SRVCC is performed for the CS bearer only. This parameter must be configured individually for every WCDMA cell that is used as target for SRVCC.

enum.name: EOaMLnadjxBandClass
enum.comment: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) band class of this 1xRTT neighbor cell. The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].

enum.name: EOaMActCSFBRedir
enum.comment: The parameter activates the feature 'Circuit Switched Fallback to UTRAN or GSM via Redirection'. If the feature is activated, mobile originated and mobile terminated CS calls are redirected to targets which are to be configured via REDRT objects.

enum.name: EOaMActCsiDroppingSolution
enum.comment: This parameter enables/disables a solution to dropping of periodic CSI due to DL scheduling on the SCell. This parameter also enables/disables a solution to dropping of periodic CSI in the PCell/single serving cell caused by setting of cqiPerSimulAck of this PCell/single serving cell to 'false' and/or caused by UE indicating in FGI2 value '0'. Please see RRM.5967 for more details. If set to 'enable', DL scheduling avoidance is always used in subframes that collide with periodic CSI. If set to 'disable', DL scheduling avoidance is never used (the same as in RL50). This setting is intended for peak data rate demonstration and is recommended to be used with proactive UL assignment (ilReacTimerUl not set to zero) so that aperiodic CSI of PCell and SCell is ensured even if all periodic CSI is dropped. If set to 'enableIfNeeded', the DL scheduling avoidance is used on demand based on triggers from MIMO-MC (MIMO Mode Control) and the UL TA (Time Alignment) Control.

enum.name: EOaMActEmerCallRedir
enum.comment: The parameter activates the feature 'Emergency Call Via Redirection'. The feature can be only activated if at least one redirection target for UTRAN or GSM has been created before.

enum.name: EOaMActIfHo
enum.comment: This parameter enables the feature Inter Frequency Handover to FDD and TDD neighbor cells.

enum.name: EOaMActRedirect
enum.comment: This parameter enables the feature UE context release with redirect.

enum.name: EOaMActS1Flex
enum.comment: This parameter indicates whether S1 Flex feature is enabled or disabled.

enum.name: EOaMAnrLTEIntraRscReportAmount
enum.comment: It defines the number of periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE

enum.name: EOaMAnrLTEIntraRscReportInterval
enum.comment: It defines the time interval for ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE

enum.name: EOaMAnrLTETReportCGI
enum.comment: It defines the maximum time at the eNB for receiving the RRC Measurement Report message with an LTE (intra- or inter-frequency) ReportCGI measurement results from a UE configured to perfrom such measurement.

enum.name: EOaMAnrRobLevel
enum.comment: Specifies the level of robustness of UE-based ANR functions. For high level of robustness, the eNB attempts for a longer time period to resolve a detected unknown neighbor cell via UE-based ANR before stopping these attempts.

enum.name: EOaMAnrUtraTRCGI
enum.comment: It defines the value of the timer started in the eNB when activating ReportCGI measurement in a UE.

enum.name: EOaMAnrUtraTRSC
enum.comment: It defines the maximum time eNB waits for an activated ReportStrongestCells measurement report on an UTRAN carrier frequency

enum.name: EOaMAnrUtraTRSCFS
enum.comment: It defines the maximum time eNB waits for an activated ReportStrongestCellForSon measurement report on an UTRAN carrier frequency.

enum.name: EOaMCongWeightAlg
enum.comment: The congestion weight algorithm defines in which order bearers are preempted in case of congestion. qciPrio: Bearers are preempted in order of QCI priority. arpPrioPerVul: First bearers with ARP vulnerability "preemptable" are preempted in order of ARP priorirty; then bearers with ARP vulnerability "not preemptable" are preempted in order of ARP priorirty.

enum.name: EOaMCycPrefix
enum.comment: The parameter defines the cyclic prefix configuration/length for the OFDM symbol in downlink and uplink. This parameter is vendor-specific.

enum.name: EOaMDrbAmMxRtxTh
enum.comment: This parameter is used by the transmitting side of each AM RLC entity to count the number of transmissions of an AMD PDU. This parameter is set so that a radio link failure can be detected by the eNB before the maximum number of transmissions has been reached. This parameter is only used in the DRB configuration. This parameter is on a higher level than ARQ and HARQ. This parameter is vendor-specific.

enum.name: EOaMEnableAutoLock
enum.comment: The parameter enables the feature "Automatic locking". If the feature is enabled, objects are automatically locked and unlocked by eNB if a parameter which requires object locking is modified via delta plan file. If graceful shutdown is enabled by setting enableGrflShdn to 'enabled', the less service impacting but slower graceful cell shutdown procedure is performed instead of immediate locking.

enum.name: EOaMEnableGrflShdn
enum.comment: The parameter enables the feature 'Graceful Cell Shutdown'. If the feature is activated an additional administrative state 'shuttingdown' is supported. It allows a less service impacting cell locking. Before entering 'locked' state of the cell the UEs will be motivated to leave the cell by stepwise reduction of the eNodeB cell TX power (DL power).

enum.name: EOaMIFLBLoadExchangePeriod
enum.comment: Load exchange with the other cells of the eNodeB is done with this periodicity.

enum.name: EOaMMoProfileSelect
enum.comment: This parameter is used to configure selection method of Mobility Profile for mobility procedures. If this parameter is set to SPID, then SPID received from MME or incoming handover is used for MOPR selection. If this parameter is set to PLMN value then MOPR selection is based on MNC included in UE Serving PLMN ID. Virtual SPID is used for mapping with value ((MNC+255) mod 256) + 1 Mobility profiles (MOPR and MODPR) are considered only when SPID selective mobility profiles feature is activated (actSelMobPrf is set to true).

enum.name: EOaMLnbtsOperationalState
enum.comment: Operational state of the eNB, the value is set by system.

enum.name: EOaMPbrNonGbr
enum.comment: Prioritized Bit Rate for non-GBR bearers This prioritized bit rate is used by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].

enum.name: EOaMPrioTopoHO
enum.comment: This parameter is used to define priorities between the 3 topology options for intra LTE handover, which are 1) Intra eNB HO 2) HO via X2 3) HO via S1 It's assumed that Intra eNB HO can not have lower priority than any other topology and S1 HO can not have higher priority than any other topology. Four relations are possible: 1) all topologies have the same priority -> "all equal" 2) intra eNB HO is prioritized over inter eNB HO where X2-based HO and S1-based HO are not discriminated -> "intra eNB HO prior inter eNB HO" 3) intra eNB HO is prioritized over inter eNB HO where X2-based HO is prioritized over S1-based HO -> "intra prior X2 prior S1" 4) intra eNB HO and X2-based handover are not discriminated but S1-based HO takes lower priority than the others -> "low prio S1"

enum-member.name: EOaMPrioTopoHO_IntraENBHoPriorInterENBHo
enum-member.pddbText: intra eNB HO prior inter eNB HO

enum.name: EOaMProhibitLBHOTimer
enum.comment: This timer is used for temporary blacklisting of a Target Cell for load-based handover. One Target Cell is blacklisted when a handover is rejected because of lack of resources. The timer is started when the cell is blacklisted. When timer expires the blacklisting is removed. Blacklist affects all UEs in the actual source cell. Blacklist affects only Handovers for Load Balancing. (cause "Reduce Load in Serving Cell" ) Blacklisted cells are managed internally by eNB and not added to black lists visible to operator.

enum.name: EOaMRachAccessForHoFromUtran
enum.comment: This parameter selects whether Target eNodeB shall provide and reserve a dedicated RACH preamble for HO from UTRAN. In case no dedicated RACH preamble is provided UE will perform contention based RACH access. If a dedicated RACH preamble is provided UE will perform non-contention based RACH access as for intra LTE handover. Note that in case eNodeB is configured to reserve a dedicated RACH preamble it may happen that eNodeB runs out of dedicated RACH preambles. In this case contention based RACH access will be used as fallback solution.

enum.name: EOaMReportTimerIFLBA4
enum.comment: Timer to supervise the A4 report. At expiry the A4 event will be deactivated. The parameter is to be vendor-specific and will be started at the time when the A4 event had been configured in the UE.

enum.name: EOaMRfSharingState
enum.comment: BTS detects automatically when the RF sharing is in use and report this in the rfSharingState parameter in the topology. This parameter has important informative value in the user interfaces in NetAct (for example for troubleshooting).

enum.name: EOaMS1PrdRevalWaitTmr
enum.comment: If for a LTE Neighbour Relation (NR) a S1 handover preparation is started and since the last validation of the NR at least the time 's1PrdRevalWaitTmr' has elapsed, then eNB triggers a re-validation for this NR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed). If 's1PrdRevalWaitTmr' is set to '0', then no re-validation is triggered. Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same NR has expired.

enum.name: EOaMSCellActivationCyclePeriod
enum.comment: This parameter defines the period of the SCell Activation cycle. The parameter value is in seconds. This parameter is not used when "sCellActivationMethod" is set to "blind".

enum.name: EOaMSCellActivationMethod
enum.comment: This parameter defines the Method to be used for SCell Activation. "blind" means that SCell is blindly activated and it is never re-activated after "sCellDeactivationTimereNB" expiration. "nonGBRBufferBased" means that SCell activation is triggered depending on the non-GBR data in buffer. Period of the SCell Activation cycle is configured in "sCellActivationCyclePeriod".

enum.name: EOaMSCellDeactivationTimereNB
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: This timer controls the deactivation of Secondary Cell for Carrier Aggregation configured UEs. The timer behaves in the same way as the SCell deactivation timer defined in TS 36.321, but result is explicit SCell deactivation by MAC CE instead of implicit SCell deactivation in order to avoid eNB - UE misalignment due to ambiguous HARQ feedback. The value represents the number of radio frames. Value "infinity" means that the SCell is never deactivated by sCellDeactivationTimereNB.
TDD specific comment: This timer controls the deactivation of Secondary Cell for Carrier Aggregation configured UEs. The timer behaves in the same way as the SCell deactivation timer defined in TS 36.321, but result is explicit SCell deactivation by MAC CE instead of implicit SCell deactivation in order to avoid eNB – UE misalignment due to ambiguous HARQ feedback. The value represents the number of radio frames. Value "infinity" means that the SCell is never deactivated by sCellDeactivationTimereNB.

enum.name: EOaMSCellpCellHARQFdbkUsage
enum.comment: The parameter selects how the ambiguous HARQ feedback of UE with an active SCell related to DL transmission is interpreted for the purpose of controlling DRX Inactivity Timer. If set to conservative, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is interpreted as DTX for the purpose of controlling the timer. If set to aggressive, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is interpreted as NACK for the purpose of controlling the timer. It is expected that the aggressive setting will favor the UE throughput of UEs with an active SCell. It is expected that the conservative setting will favor cell throughput.

enum.name: EOaMTxPathFailureMode
enum.comment: Controls the handling of TX path failures. If set to "keepCellInService" a cell remains enabled as as long as at least one TX path carrying PSS/SSS is operating. If set to "disableCell" a cell is disabled if at least one TX path is not operable. Note that changing the mode requires "BTS restart". If txPathFailureMode is configured to 'keepCellInService' the cell will be kept in service in following configurations for a TX path failure: - dlMimoMode is configured to: "TXDiv", "4-way TXDiv", "Dynamic Open Loop MIMO", "Closed Loop Mimo", "Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)" and - for FSMr2 and FSMr3: syncSigTxMode is configured to "TxDix" and at least one TX path is still operable while actOtdoa is set to "false" or (actOtdoa is set to "true" and actPrsTxDiv set to "true") or - for FSMr3: syncSigTxMode equals "SingleTx" and the TX path which transmits the synchronization signal (PSS/SSS) is operable eNB will automatically check for each cell if these conditions are fulfilled. If not, the cell will be disabled.

enum.name: EOaMWaitTimeEstCtrlX2Lnk
enum.comment: For each establishment attempt of an eNB Controlled X2-link, the eNB shall wait until a certain time before repetition of the establishment attempt. The contribution of the eNB RNL to this wait time is given by 'waitTimeEstCtrlX2Lnk'. Note: To obtain the total wait time the additional contribution from eNB TNL given by 'MaxTimeSctpSetup' has to be added.

enum.name: EOaMX2PrdRevalWaitTmr

If 'x2PrdRevalWaitTmr' is set to '0', then no re-validation is triggered. Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same NR has expired.

enum.name: EOaMActModulationSchemeUL
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: This parameter switch on/off the differnt Ul modulation schemes. When set to "16QAMHighMCS" MCS21-MCS24 are enabled and the UL AMC proposes to the UL scheduler to use the higher 16-QAM MCS, if radio conditions allow. Precondition for the feature is that UE is a Cat.1 to Cat.4 device. Cat.5 devices, which would support real 64-QAM modulation, will be as well provided with codecs up to MCS24 (when the appropiated configuration of this parameter is given); however the assumption is that Cat.5 UEs acts as Cat.1 to Cat.4 devices and utilize16-QAMmodulation in UL. because of the setting to 'false' enable64qamPusch" parameter (broadcasted in SIB2). MCS (MCS21-MCS24) for UL AMC may be used only when this parameter is set to "16QAMHighMCS". With the coonfiguration "16QAM" only the codec up to MCS20 are enable. "QPSK" configuration allows utilization only up to MCS10
TDD specific comment: This parameter switch on/off the different Ul modulation schemes. When set to "16QAMHighMCS" the 16 QAM high MCS for UL AMC (MCS21 - MCS24) are enabled and the UL AMC proposes to the UL scheduler to use the higher 16-QAM MCS, if radio conditions allow for it. For all UEs the maximum MCS is up to MCS24 and for MCS21-MCS24 the modulation scheme is 16QAM. When set to "64QAM", for UE CAT5&8 64QAM is supported. For UE CAT5&CAT8, the maximum MCS is up to MCS28 and for MCS21-MCS28 the modulation scheme is 64QAM. For other category UEs, the maximum MCS is up to MCS20. When set to "64QAMand16QAMHighMCS", for UE CAT5&8 the maximum MCS is up to MCS28 and for MCS21-MCS28 the modulation scheme is 64QAM. For other category UEs, the maximum MCS is up to MCS24 and for MCS21-MCS24 the modulation scheme is 16QAM. When actModulationSchemeUl is set to "64QAM" or "64QAMand16QAMHighMCS", the information element "enable64QAM" for PUSCH in SIB2 gets value "true". Otherwise the value send is "false".

enum.name: EOaMActRepeaterMode
enum.comment: Defines mode of the the radio module or RIU unit. The "actRepeaterMode" parameter value Coupled needs to be used for coupled mode cells (R type configuration), value Dedicated for dedicated mode cells (cell have resources only from RIU unit) and value None for all other cells (cells do not have resources from RIU unit). Possible modes are None, Dedicated and Coupled. The Coupled is supported only with Configuration Type R. The RIU is able to work either in Dedicated or Coupled mode also in case a RF unit is chained via it. Super cell configurations are not released in conjunction with Repeater Interface Units.

enum.name: EOaMActUlLnkAdp
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Activates Uplink Link Adaptation and defines Link Adaptation mode When set to "off" no Uplink link Adaptation function is active at all. When set to "eUlLa" the extended Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated. When set to "fUlLa" the new Fast Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated. The other choice "slowAmcOllaATB" allows to set to active all the 3 old components of the UL LA function as it was up to RL20.
TDD specific comment: Activates Uplink Link Adaptation and defines Link Adaptation mode When set to "off" no Uplink link Adaptation function is active at all. When set to "eUlLa" the extended Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated. When set to "fUlLa" the new Fast Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated. The other choice "slowAmcOllaATB" allows to set to active all the 3 old components of the UL LA function as it was up to RL15.

enum.name: EOaMApplyOutOfSyncState
enum.comment: Determines which UEs shall be actively sent to UL out-of-sync state provided that bearer combination and applied DRX profile allows for this. extendedDrxOnly: only UEs being configured with extended settings for the long DRX cycle, i.e. long DRX cycle durations larger than 80ms allDrx: all UEs being configured for DRX provided that applied DRX profile allows allUEs: all UEs independently of DRX configuration provided that bearer combination allows.

enum.name: EOaMCellBarred
enum.comment: The cell barred flag indicates if the cell status is barred or not. A barred cell is a cell that a UE is not allowed to camp on, not even for emergency calls. If a cell on which a UE is currently camped becomes barred, a cell reselection is triggered.

enum.name: EOaMCellResourceSharingMode
enum.comment: The parameter activates the feature LTE1382 'Cell resource groups' and selects the resource sharing mode. The feature allows pre-reservation of cell resources in admission control per PLMN group.

enum.name: EOaMCellSrPeriod
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Define the admitted Scheduling Request periodicity in the cell, once the scheduling request reporting has been set to enable This parameter is part of sr-ConfigIndex Parameter . See TS 36.213 [23,10.1]. Operator define periodicity and system define an allocation offset in time,; these two lelements combined define the above mentioned sr-ConfigIndex In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: if riEnable is set to 'true' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is false.
TDD specific comment: Define the admitted Scheduling Request periodicity in the cell, once the scheduling request reproting has been set to enable This parameter is part of sr-ConfigIndex Parameter . See TS 36.213 [23,10.1]. Operator define periodicity and system define an allocation offset in time; these two lelements combined define the above mentioned sr-ConfigIndex

enum.name: EOaMCellType
enum.comment: This parameter allows the operator to specify the size of an LTE cell. This parameter is used for preparing the UE History IE during an outgoing handover, according to LTE1768. It will be considered if the LTE1140: Intra-frequency load balancing feature is activated for deriving the corresponding CellBeta coeffcient .

enum.name: EOaMCqiAperMode
enum.comment: Corresponds to cqi-ReportingModeAperiodic of 3GPP-36.213. CQI format indicator for aperiodic reporting on PUSCH. The operator can choose one of the 2 family modes available, the MIMO algorithm embedded in RRM chooses the effective mode based on the UE capabilities and the family mode chosen by the operator and forwards this to UE; FTB1 selects the reporting mode 2.x, FTB2 selects the reporting mode 3.x; x is determined by the MIMO algorithm internal in eNB.

enum.name: EOaMCqiPerNp
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Sets the CQI Reporting Periodicity Np for CQI reporting. Range is now extended up to include the 80ms periodicity option. For each UE, the RRC algorithm calculate and add to this parameter a specific NOffset,CQI, depending on the UE offset allocation within the chosen periodicity determining the iCQI/PMI index value to be sent to UE. EXAMPLE: by default value of 20ms only iCQI/PMI index values among 17 and 36 will be allocated by CQI/PMI allocation algorithm. In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected: (1) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '2' - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp (2) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '1' - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2 eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.
TDD specific comment: The parameter defines the periodicity of periodic CQI / PMI feedback on PUCCH or PUSCH.

enum.name: EOaMDSrTransMax
enum.comment: This is the maximum number of the allowed dedicated Scheduling Requests. Once this limit is exceeded, UE releases all PUCCH resources. The value 4n corresponds to 4 transmissions, 8n corresponds to 8 transmissions and so on. Indirectly provides the UE-specific maximum time within which the UE must receive a valid uplink grant for a new transmission on UL-SCH. If this time expires, the UE releases PUCCH resources and no longer performs a dedicated Scheduling Request, but instead performs a random access Scheduling Request. This time is calculated by cell Scheduling Request periodicity * dedicated SR transmission maximum.

enum.name: EOaMDefPagCyc
enum.comment: The default paging cycle defines the cell-specific paging DRX cycle duration. It also determines the maximum paging DRX duration applicable in the cell. Referred to as ' T ' in TS 36.304. Value rf32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, rf64 corresponds to 64 radio frames and so on.

enum.name: EOaMDlChBwFdd
enum.comment: Downlink channel bandwidth defines the DL bandwidth for the eNode-B transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks. The downlink channel bandwidth mapping to number of Physical Resource Blocks is: 1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBS 3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBS 5.0 MHz = 25 DL PRBS 10.0 MHz = 50 DL PRBS 15.0 MHz = 75 DL PRBS 20.0 MHz = 100 DL PRBS Following configuration rules need to be considered: FSMD: maximum downlink channel bandwidth is 10 MHz if more than 2 cells are configured. FSME: maximum downlink channel bandwidth is 10 MHz if more than 3 cells are configured. Cell bandwidth 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz: - is only supported with FSMF - is not supported with 4 TX/RX configuration - is not supported with WCDMA RF sharing - all LNCEL instances of the eNB must be configured with the same bandwidth. Cell bandwidth 1.4 MHz: - is not supported with GSM RF sharing In case feature 'SuperCell' is activated (parameter LNCEL-actSuperCell set to 'true') the bandwidth usage is limited to 10MHz.

enum-member.comment: Original enumeration name in PDDB source is: '1.4 MHz'. It contains non-alphanumerical characters.

enum.name: EOaMDlChBwTdd
enum.comment: Channel Bandwidth defines the Downlink and Uplink bandwidth for the eNode-B transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks which is transmitted in the MIB. The Channel Bandwidth mapping to Number of Physical Resource Blocks is: 1.4 MHz = 6 PRB; 3.0 MHz = 15 PRB; 5.0 MHz = 25 PRB; 10.0 MHz = 50 PRB; 15.0 MHz = 75 PRB; 20.0 MHz = 100 PRB.

enum.name: EOaMDlInterferenceModulation
enum.comment: The dlInterferenceModulation parameter defines modulation scheme to be used for generated downlink interference. That is, for a non-existing UE the downlink interference is transmitted.

enum.name: EOaMDlMimoMode
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Cell specific downlink transmission/mimo mode The used DL mimo mode for each physical channel is the following: SingleTx: Single Stream Downlink: All downlink physical channels are transmitted using this mode; TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for two antennas using Transmission Mode 2. 4-way TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for four TX antennas using Transmission Mode 2. Please note that "4-way TXDiv" must not be configured in dual band configurations. Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Dual Stream MIMO with spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity; If dlMimoMode is set to "Dynamic Open Loop MIMO", mimoOlCqiThD, mimoOlCqiThU, mimoOlRiThD, mimoOlRiThU are relevant. Default values will be used if no dedicated values are configured. Closed Loop Mimo: Dynamic Closed Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. Closed Loop MIMO (4x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x2: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. In case dlMimoMode is set to "Dynamic Open Loop MIMO" or "Closed Loop Mimo" it is recommended to set riEnable to value 'true' to enable dynamic switching between dual stream MIMO spatial multiplexing and single stream transmission. If dlMimoMode is set to "SingleTX", dlpcMimoComp is not applicable. The default value is used implicitly.
TDD specific comment: Parameter to select the static DL MIMO mode for each physical channel and to enable the UE specific dynamic open loop as well as closed loop MIMO Mode control Algorithm. Cell specific downlink transmission/mimo mode The used DL mimo mode for each physical channel is the following: SingleTx: Single Stream Downlink: All downlink physical channels are transmitted using this mode. TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for two antennas using Transmission Mode 2. Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Dual Stream MIMO with spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. Single Stream Beamforming: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using Single Stream Beamforming depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. Dual Stream Beamforming: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using Dual Stream Beamforming depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. Closed Loop MIMO (4x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. Closed Loop MIMO (8x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO8x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity. 4-way TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for four antennas using Transmission Mode 2.

It is recommended to stay with the default value 'PRBs with PSS or SSS and PBCH used' if dlChBw is set to '3 MHz'. Value "not used" mean that partial PRBs are not used.
TDD specific comment: Determines whether PRBs partly allocated for transmission of Primary (PSS) and Secondary synchronization Signals (SSS) and Physical Broadcasting Channel (BPCH) should be used in dynamic scheduling. Value "not used" mean that partial PRBs are not used.

enum.name: EOaMMbrSelector

In case of using DL carrier aggregation for an UE this selector is ignored and in any case the standardized limits (3GPP 36.306) are used for max. number of transport block bits per TTI in DL.

enum.name: EOaMMeasQuantityCSFBUtra

The quantities used to evaluate the triggering condition for the event. cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD. cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD. This parameter refers to event B1 for CSFB to WCDMA.

enum.name: EOaMPagingNb
enum.comment: Paging nB defines the number of possible paging occasions per radio frame, i.e. the density of paging occasions. This parameter is used to calculate the number of paging occasions within one paging DRX duration, which in turn is used to calculate the paging occasion.

enum.name: EOaMPdcchAggDefUe
enum.comment: The parameter defines default aggregation for UE to be used in PDCCH Link Adaptation when enableAmcPdcch has been disabled or when enableAmcPdcch has been enabled and there is no valid Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) available due to an expiry of the timer determining CQI remembering.

enum.name: EOaMPeriodicCqiFeedbackType
enum.comment: Parameter determines if Wideband CQI or UE_selected subband CQI report mode for periodic CQI reporting on PUCCH or PUSCH should be used. If periodicCqiFeedbackType is set to UE_selected subband CQI this means that UEs supporting subband CQI (prooved via check of FGI) use it and UEs which do not support subband CQI will use wideband CQI. Note for the case where periodic subband CQI reporting is enabled together with DRX functionality (actDrx): It may not be possible to synchronize DRX start offset such that the wideband CQI report is received during the DRX OnDuration (due to periodicities) and that may cause small performance degradation in DL whenever fresh wideband channel quality information cannot be get in time. It is up to an operator whether to prevent activation of periodic subband CQI reporting and DRX in parallel because of this restriction.

enum.name: EOaMPhichDur
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Indicates the duration of PHICH. When phichDur is set to value (Normal), PHICH is transmitted in the first OFDMA symbol, and when phichDur is set to value (Extended), PHICH is transmitted in first three OFDMA symbols. phichDur is transmitted in system information as information is cell specific, and all UEs need to know whether to receive PHICH from 1 or 3 symbols. phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signalled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3. For futher info see Table 6.9.3-1 in TS 36.211. Hint for cells with bandwidth 1.4 MHz: A slightly improved PDCCH and PHICH performance could be achieved if extended PHICH is configured. Rationale: with phichDur set to 1 (meaning "extended PHICH Duration") the PHICH REs are distributed over 3 OFDMA symbols, so both time diversity for PHICH and better distribution of PHICH excess power used as a source for PDCCH power boost can be achieved.
TDD specific comment: Indicates the duration of PHICH. When phichDur is set to value (Normal), PHICH is transmitted in the first OFDMA symbol, and when phichDur is set to value (Extended), PHICH is transmitted in first three OFDMA symbols. phichDur is transmitted in system information as information is cell specific, and all UEs need to know whether to receive PHICH from 1 or 3 symbols. phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signalled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3. For futher info see Table 6.9.3-1 in TS 36.211.

enum.name: EOaMPhichRes
enum.comment: The Physical Hybrid ARQ Indicatior Channel (PHICH) carries the hybrid-ARQ ACK/NAK. Multiple PHICHs mapped to the same set of resource elements constitute a PHICH group and the PHICH resource parameter defines the number of PHICH groups.

enum.name: EOaMPrimPlmnCellres
enum.comment: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for operator use. Cells reserved for operator use are treated as barred by 'normal' UEs without a USIM with AC 11 or 15 inserted. UEs with AC 11 or 15 USIM inserted are specific operator UEs and thus allowed to camp on and access such cells. The default value is not reserved.

enum.name: EOaMPrsConfigurationIndex
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Determines the periodicity and offset of the PRS occasions for FDD 151-157: 160ms period 471-477: 320ms period 1111-1117: 640ms period 2391-2397: 1280ms period The periodicity and offset can be computed according to 3GPP TS 36.211 Rel9
TDD specific comment: Determines the periodicity and offset of the PRS occasions for TDD. 153-159: 160ms period 473-479: 320ms period 1113-1119: 640ms period 2393-2399: 1280ms period The periodicity and offset can be computed according to 3GPP TS 36.211 Rel9. Note: - when PRS periodicity is 160ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex(subframes) - when PRS periodicity is 320ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 160(subframes) - when PRS periodicity is 640ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 480(subframes) - when PRS periodicity is 1280ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 1120(subframes)

enum.name: EOaMQHyst
enum.comment: The Qhyst parameter provides the hysteresis value in dB for ranking criteria in the cell reselection procedure. The parameter is used to minimize pingpong.

enum.name: EOaMRaContResoT
enum.comment: The maximum content resolution timer parameter defines the maximum amount of time allowed for contention resolution.

enum.name: EOaMRaMsgPoffGrB
enum.comment: Path loss threshold in dB required for selecting one of the two groups of Random Access preambles. The UE will only use preambles from group B if it needs to send a large Msg3 AND its measured path loss is less than Pmax - PREAMBLE_INITIAL_RECEIVED_TARGET_POWER - DELTA_PREAMBLE_MSG3 - messagePowerOffsetGroupB (see 36.321 ch 5.1.2)

enum-member.name: EOaMRaMsgPoffGrB_Infinity
enum-member.comment: Original enumeration name in PDDB source is: '-infinity'. It contains non-alphanumerical characters.

enum.name: EOaMRaNondedPreamb
enum.comment: This parameter determines the total number of non-dedicated RA preambles that a UE can select from (i.e. for contention based RA). The minimum cannot be zero.

enum.name: EOaMRaPreGrASize
enum.comment: Defines the size of the Random Access preambles Group A.

enum.name: EOaMRaRespWinSize
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in TTIs.
TDD specific comment: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in TTIs. IMPORTANT NOTE: Preamble format 0: If the UL/DL configuration is 1 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 5. If the UL/DL configuration is 2 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4. Preamble format 1: If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4. Preamble format 2: If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4. Preamble format 4: If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 7 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 3. If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 6. If the UL/DL configuration is 2 and the special subframe configuration is 7 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 3. If the UL/DL configuration is 2 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 5.

enum.name: EOaMRaSmallVolUl
enum.comment: Defines the data volume to be used for small size Random Access message 3 in case of UL or DL data arrival.

enum.name: EOaMRiPerM
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Multiplier M for defining periodic RI feedback reporting period. It defines the multiplier for the cqiPerNp which results in the periodicity for RI periodic reports. RI periodicity = cqiPerNp * riPerM. When riPerM is equal to 0 (M=1) the parameter riPerOffset must be set to -1 (CQI and Ri are adjiacent) while when riPerM is set to 1 (M=2) the parameter riPerOffset must set to 0 (in this case CQI and RI alternate).
TDD specific comment: Multiplier M for defining periodic RI feedback reporting period. It defines the multiplier for the cqiPerNp which results in the periodicity for RI periodic reports. RI periodicity = cqiPerNp * riPerM. When riPerM is equal to 0 (M=1) the parameter riPerOffset must be set to -1 (CQI and Ri are adjiacent) while when riPerM is set to 1 (M=2) the parameter riPerOffset must set to 0 (in this case CQI and RI alternate).

enum.name: EOaMRttCsfbType
enum.comment: Defines the 1xCSFB type which shall be used in the cell. If set to forbidden, 1xCSFB is not allowed; if set to R81xCsfbEnforced, R8 1xCSFB with redirection shall be enforced; if set to R9e1xCsfb, R9 enhanced 1x Circuit Switched Fallback (e1xCSFB) will be attempted.

enum.name: EOaMSiWindowLen
enum.comment: Defines the common System Information scheduling window. The parameter SI Window Length defines the common System Information scheduling window for all SIs.

enum.name: EOaMSyncSigTxMode
enum.comment: The parameter determines whether Primary and Secondary Synchronization Signals (PSS, SSS) are transmitted into a cell via one antenna port (SingeTx) or via all antenna ports using TX diversity with Precoding Vector Switching (PVS). In case of 2 or 4 antenna port configuration is done in a flexible way based on the antenna configuration.

enum.name: EOaMT300
enum.comment: Timer T300 supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure. Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionRequest Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionSetup or RRCConnectionReject message, cell re-selection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers At expiry: Perform the actions as specified in 36.331, 5.3.3.6

enum.name: EOaMT301
enum.comment: Timer T301 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure. Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE

enum.name: EOaMT304InterRAT
enum.comment: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target WCDMA system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)

enum.name: EOaMT304InterRATGsm
enum.comment: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target GSM system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall) Despite this timer is transparently provided by GERAN Target system its value is needed in LTE to calculate TS1RELOCOverall

enum.name: EOaMT304IntraLte
enum.comment: Timer T304 supervises the successful completion of a handover or cell change.

enum.name: EOaMT304eNaccGsm
enum.comment: 3GPP defined Timer T304 (used for RRC Re-Establishment) for the case of eNACC to GSM This timer value is passed to the UE in an RRC: MobilityFromEUTRANCommand message and is used by the UE to identify CCO Failure

enum.name: EOaMT310

enum.name: EOaMT311

enum.name: EOaMUlChBw
enum.comment: Uplink channel bandwidth defines the UL bandwidth for the eNB transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks. The uplink channel bandwidth mapping to number of Physical Resource Blocks is: 1.4 MHz = 6 UL PRBS 3.0 MHz = 15 UL PRBS 5.0 MHz = 25 UL PRBS 10.0 MHz = 50 UL PRBS 15.0 MHz = 75 UL PRBS 20.0 MHz = 100 UL PRBS Maximum 10 MHz uplink channel bandwidth may be used with single FSMD to configure more than 2 cells or with single FSME to configure more than 3 cells. 1.4 MHz and 3.0 MHz uplink channel bandwidth is only supported on FSMF. enum.comment:

For optimal performance of the IRC mode it is recommended to deploy phase synchronization via GPS. IRC reception is supported on FSM Rel3 only. enum.name: EOaMUlsFdPrbAssignAlg
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Scheduler Type for FD scheduler Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in frequency domain for the scheduler in UL - The "RoundRobinFD" scheduler assigns the physical resources equally fair to the UEs selected by the TD scheduler until the PRBs are sufficient for the service or the physical resources of the cell are exhaust - The "ExhaustiveFD" scheduler assigns in the priority sequence defined by the TD scheduler as many physical resources as possible to the UEs until the number of PRBs are sufficient for the service or the resources of the cell are exhaust - The "MixedFD" scheduler is a joint FD scheduler which assigns the PRBs for SRB and GBR bearers by the exhaustive FD scheduler and the PRBs for the nonGBR bearers by the Round Robin FD scheduler to the UEs
TDD specific comment: Scheduler Type for FD scheduler Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in frequency domain for the scheduler in UL - The Round Robin FD scheduler assigns the physical resources equally fair to the UEs selected by the TD scheduler until the PRBs are sufficient for the service or the physical resources of the cell are exhaust - The FD Exhaustive FD scheduler assigns in the priority sequence defined by the TD scheduler as many physical resources as possible to the UEs until the number of PRBs are sufficient for the service or the resources of the cell are exhaust - The Mixed FD scheduler is a joint FD scheduler which assigns the PRBs for SRB and GBR bearers by the exhaustive FD scheduler and the PRBs for the nonGBR bearers by the Round Robin FD scheduler to the UEs

enum.name: EOaMUlsSchedMethod
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in the cell for the UL branch. Selects the method for the scheduling of the UEs in UL. Three methods can be chosen - the channel unaware UL scheduler, the interference aware UL scheduler and the channel aware UL scheduler.
TDD specific comment: Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in the cell for the UL branch. Selects the method for the scheduling of the UEs in UL. Two methods can be chosen - the channel unaware UL scheduler and the channel aware UL scheduler.

enum.name: EOaMDlInterferenceSpatialMode
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the spatial mode for the downlink interference. If dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTX' then one element of the structure must be present with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'SingleTx'. If dlMimoMode is set to 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' , 'Closed Loop Mimo' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' then one element of the structure must be present with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'TXDiv'. If dlMimoMode is set to 'Single Stream Beamforming' or 'Dual Stream Beamforming' then both elements of the structure must be present, one with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'TXDiv' and the other with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'Single Stream Beamforming'.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDlSectorBFWeightProfName
enum.comment: This parameter identifies the name of the downlink sector beamforming weight profile. There are two types of the downlink sector beamforming weight profiles. One is "predefined profile" and another is "customized profile". "predefined profile" means the downlink sector beamforming weights shall be set as the predefined values per the specific antenna type(according to antenna spec). "customized profile" means the operator can set the downlink sector beamforming weights via O&M interface. Each profile name maps to the downlink sector beamforming weight of the specific antenna type(predefined profile) or the customized sector beamforming weight profile.

enum.name: EOaMDlsFdAlg
enum.comment: Parameter to choose between different available algorithms for frequency domain scheduling. Available algorithms are TTA: fair allocation property based on ratio of relative to wideband channel quality PFsch: proportional fair allocation property based on ratio of immediate to average scheduled channel quality MaxCI: Maximum C/I based sub-band channel quality

enum.name: EOaMDlsNgap
enum.comment: Parameter defines the gap value used in the interleaving function which maps VRBs to PRBs when using Distributed VRB mapping.

enum.name: EOaMDlsSchedType
enum.comment: Parameter to choose between different available scheduler types

enum.name: EOaMFilterCoefficientCSFBPccpchRscp
enum.comment: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA-WCDMA CSFB Cpich-RSCP Specifies the filtering coefficient used for PCCPCH-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA TD-SCDMA.

enum.name: EOaMFilterCoefficientPccpchRscp
enum.comment: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA TD-SCDMA PCCPCH-RSCP Specifies the filtering coefficient used for PCCPCH-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA TD-SCDMA

enum.name: EOaMProhibitTimerTmSwitch
enum.comment: Defines the period of time between to transmission mode switches for the same UE.

enum.name: EOaMSCellTmSettingWithBf
enum.comment: This parameter will impact the transmission mode determination for UEs that use the cell as SCell and may be configured with transmission mode using SRS based beamforming. When set to ‘fixedTm3WithBf’, the transmission mode of those UEs is fixed at TM3; when set to ‘followDlMimoMode’, those UEs are handled as if they are using the cell as PCell.

enum.name: EOaMSrsBwConf
enum.comment: Defines together with the channel bandwidth (chBw) and the srsBandwidthNonBf (srs bandwidth for non beamforming users) or srsBandwidthBf (srs bandwidth for beamforming users) the bandwidth of one srs symbol. Please refer to table 5.5.3.2-1 to 5.5.3.2-4 in 3GPP TS36.211 for different system bandwidth. If dlMimoMode is set to a beamforming mode ("Single Stream Beamforming" or "Dual Stream Beamforming") , than srsBandwidthForNonBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for UEs which rrc transmission mode is set to tm0 to tm4. srsBandwidthForBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for UEs which rrc transmission mode is set to tm7 or tm8. If dlMimoMode is set to a non beamforming mode ("SingleTX", "TXDiv", "4-way TXDiv", "Dynamic Open Loop MIMO", "Closed Loop Mimo" or "Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)"), than srsBandwidthForNonBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for all UEs.

enum.name: EOaMSrsDuration
enum.comment: Defines the Ue transmission duration for srs. Only indefinite duration is supported.

enum.name: EOaMSrsHoppingBw
enum.comment: Defines the srs hopping bandwidth. If srsHoppingBw >= srsBandwidthforNonBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is disabled. If srsHoppingBw < srsBandwidthforNonBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is enabled. If srsHoppingBw >= srsBandwidthforBf than for beamforming users frequency hopping is disabled. If srsHoppingBw < srsBandwidthforBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is enabled.

enum.name: EOaMSrsSubfrConf
enum.comment: Defines the cell specific srs subframe configuration as specified in 3GPP TS36.211 table 5.5.3.3-2.

enum.name: EOaMT304InterRatTd
enum.comment: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target TD-SCDMA system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)

enum.name: EOaMTimeChInfoValid
enum.comment: Time period during which channel information is valid timeChInfoValid indicates that the maximum time during which the measurement channel information is valid. If timeChInfoValid is set to 0, the measurement channel information is always invalid. If timeChInforValid is set to infinite, the measurement channel information is always valid.

enum.name: EOaMCellIndOff
enum.comment: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of home eNB cells for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving or Neighbor Carrier Measurement Object CIO values for macro eNodeB(s) always have higher priority than those for home eNBs as far as the PCI of the macro eNB is not in a home eNB PCI range. CIO is only included in the measurement object if there is sufficient space.

enum.name: EOaMB2TimeToTriggerGERANMeas
enum.comment: Duration for which the RSRP based event B2 must be valid Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

enum.name: EOaMLnhogBandIndicatorGERAN
enum.comment: Indicates how to interpret the ARFCN of the BCCH carrier The IE BandIndicatorGERAN indicates how to interpret an associated GERAN carrier ARFCN, see TS 45.005 [20]. More specifically, the IE indicates the GERAN frequency band in case the ARFCN value can concern either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with one of these bands, the indicator is not relevant.

struct.name: SOaMLnhogNccperm
struct.comment: Network (PLMN) Colour Code This parameter restricts the permitted Network Colour Code (NCC) for connected mode mobility. Using default settings, no network is permitted. Field encoded as a bit map, where bit N is set to "0" if a BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is not permitted for monitoring and set to "1" if the BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is permitted for monitoring; N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the leading bit of the bit string.

enum.name: EOaMReportIntervalGERAN
enum.comment: The RSRP based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP

enum.name: EOaMB2TimeToTriggerHrpdMeas
enum.comment: Time during which specific criteria for the RSRP&Pstr based measurement event B2 needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

enum.name: EOaMReportIntervalHrpd
enum.comment: The RSRP&Pstr based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP&Pstr based event. Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

enum.name: EOaMA3ReportIntervalRsrpInterFreq
enum.comment: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRP is met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

enum.name: EOaMA3ReportIntervalRsrqInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMA3TimeToTriggerRsrpInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMA3TimeToTriggerRsrqInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMA5ReportIntervalInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMA5TimeToTriggerInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMMeasQuantInterFreq

enum.name: EOaMLnhowB1TimeToTriggerCSFBUtraMeas
enum.comment: Duration for which the RSRP based event B1 must be valid. For further important notice see the Additional Description. Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Important Note: Since the B1 event for the purpose of CSFB shall be reported by the UE as fast as possible not the full range of up to 5120 ms for TTT shall be applicable. enum.name: EOaMLNMMEadministrativeState
enum.comment: Administrative state of the LNMME S1 link. This parameter is used to lock and unlock the LNMME S1 link. Locking LNMME means closing the SCTP association between eNB and MME. All impacted UEs in RRC connected mode will be released. Unlocking LNMME triggers SCTP association establishment and S1AP Setup procedure. If feature 'S1 Flex' is not activated only the S1 link of LNMME instance 0 will be supported.

enum.name: EOaMHandoverAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls handover blacklisting. The instance of LNREL and the related cell relationship, defined by ECGI, identifies the specific cell to cell relation. The parameter allows HO for this neighbor relation, only S1 HO or no HO at all. The blacklisting applies in addition to blacklisting via the LNCEL parameter blacklistHoL. The meaning is as follows: 'allowed' means that any S1 or X2 outgoing handover is allowed. 'onlyS1' means that outgoiing handover via S1 is allowed but not via X2. 'forbidden' means that no outgoing S1 or X2 handover is triggered.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelNrControl
enum.comment: The parameter coordinates the access to parameter handoverAllowed, i.e. whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNREL and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct

enum.name: EOaMNrStatus
enum.comment: Indicates the status of the neighbor relation. unavailable: Indicates that the neighbor relation is not considered for HO (for example because neighbor cell information is not available). available: Indicates that the neighbor relation is considered for HO if not blacklisted, that is if handoverAllowed is not set to Forbidden. The nrStatus of a blacklisted neighbor relation may be nevertheless Available. This indicates that all information for HO is available and HO would be in principle possible if blacklisting would be released.

enum.name: EOaMENACCAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether Network Assisted Cell Change to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelgNrControl
enum.comment: The parameter coordinates the access to mobility-feature whitelist parameters (type: *Allowed), that is whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNRELG and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct Optimizer Features. NetAct ANR features consider this setting accordingly. The Operator might consider the setting. The parameter is for NetAct usage only. It is not evaluated by eNB.

enum.name: EOaMRedirWithSysInfoAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether the related neighbor cell is a candidate for providing system information in case of UE redirection to GERAN. If system information is not configured in the related LNADJG object at least the frequency of the cell will be provided in the redirection information.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelgSrvccAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelwCsfbPsHoAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether CSFB with PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelwNrControl
enum.comment: The parameter coordinates the access to mobility-feature whitelist parameters (type: *Allowed), that is whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNRELW and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct Optimizer Features. NetAct ANR features consider this setting accordingly. The Operator might consider the setting. The parameter is for NetAct usage only. It is not evaluated by eNB.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelwPsHoAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelwSrvccAllowed
enum.comment: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

enum.name: EOaMLnrelxBandClass
enum.comment: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) band class of this 1xRTT neighbor cell. The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].

enum.name: EOaME1xCsfbAllowed
enum.comment: Define whether the CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell could be used for 1xRTT measure configuration for e1xCSFB.

enum.name: EOaMMhaConnection
enum.comment: Defines the connection type for MHA/LNA.

enum.name: EOaMLnaNumber
enum.comment: The parameter for MHA telling LNA number inside one MHA. For Non AISG MHAs is used -1 (not defined).

enum.name: EOaMMhaType
enum.comment: Defines the type of the MHA. The supported MHA types are: WMHA, WMHB, WMHC, WMHD, MDTA, MDPA, MDGA, MDDA, FLJA, DTMAFV1, DTMAFV3, DTMAFV4, DTMARETFV1, DTMARETFV2, DTMARETFV3, DTMARETFV4, SDTMARETFV1, SDTMARETFV2, SDTMARETFV3, TMAFV1, TMAFV3, TMAFV4, TMARETFV1, FLHA, FLMA, FLNA and Other.

enum.name: EOaMMhaScannedAntennaInterface
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines which antenna interface is scanned. Expected value: RMODx-ANTx and empty string where RMODx: 1...12 and ANTx: 1...6 It depends on radio module type which antennas are capable for scanning/AISG device detection.
TDD specific comment: Defines which antenna interface is scanned. Expected value: RMODx-ANTx and empty string where RMODx: 1...12 and ANTx: 1...8 It depends on radio module type which antennas are capable for scanning / AISG device detection.

struct.name: SOaMTmaSubunitType
struct.comment: TMA Subunit type

enum.name: EOaMWmhConnector
enum.comment: This parameter defines the MHA connector regarding WMHC and TMARET MHA types. The options are BTS1 (Pass-through) and BTS2 (Power) for WMHC, NODEB0 and NODEB1 for TMARET MHA types. If other than WMHC or TMARET MHA types are used, then the wmhConnector parameter value is None

enum.name: EOaMModredAddGsmSIToRedirMsg
enum.comment: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message. GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

enum.name: EOaMModredRedirBandCdma
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 band class. It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT. The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

enum.name: EOaMModredRedirGeranBandIndicator
enum.comment: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers. For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning. This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran. The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

enum.name: EOaMModredRedirRAT
enum.comment: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected. The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

enum.name: EOaMMoredAddGsmSIToRedirMsg
enum.comment: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message. GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

enum.name: EOaMMoredRedirBandCdma
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 band class. It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT.

enum.name: EOaMMoredRedirGeranBandIndicator
enum.comment: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers. For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning. This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran.

enum.name: EOaMMoredRedirRAT
enum.comment: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected.

enum.name: EOaMSharedRfTechnologies
enum.comment: This parameter indicates the partner technologies which share the same RF equipment. The system will set this parameter automatically based on RF sharing configuration defined to the BTS.

enum.name: EOaMTraceRrcMsgCategory
enum.comment: If traceRrcMsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceRrcUeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced. If traceRrcMsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceRrcNonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of n on-UE specific messages to be traced. If traceRrcMsgCategory = all then the both lists are present.

enum.name: EOaMTraceRrcSetting
enum.comment: This parameter indicates if all RRC messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of RRC messages as defined in parameter traceRrcMsgCategory (specific), or RRC not traced at all (none).

enum.name: EOaMTraceS1MsgCategory
enum.comment: If traceS1MsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceS1UeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced. If traceS1MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceS1NonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of non-UE specific messages to be traced. If traceS1MsgCategory = all then the both lists are present.

enum.name: EOaMTraceS1Setting
enum.comment: This parameter indicates if all S1 messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of S1 messages as defined in parameter traceS1MsgCategory (specific), or S1 not traced at all (none).

enum.name: EOaMTraceX2MsgCategory
enum.comment: If traceX2MsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceX2UeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced. If traceX2MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceX2NonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of non-UE specific messages to be traced. If traceX2MsgCategory = all then the both lists are present.

enum.name: EOaMTraceX2Setting
enum.comment: This parameter indicates if all X2 messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of X2 messages as defined in parameter traceX2MsgCategory (specific), or X2 not traced at all (none).

enum.name: EOaMRedrtAddGsmSIToRedirMsg
enum.comment: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message. GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

enum.name: EOaMRedrtRedirBandCdma
enum.comment: This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000-HRPD or redirRAT=cdma2000-1xRTT. Specifies the cdma2000 band class.

enum.name: EOaMRedrtRedirGeranBandIndicator
enum.comment: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers. For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning. This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran.

enum.name: EOaMRedrtRedirRat
enum.comment: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected.

enum.name: EOaMRetDeviceType
enum.comment: Defines the RET device type as a single-antenna RET device or a multi-antenna RET device Defines the RET device type as a single-antenna RET device or a multi-antenna RET device. A RET device controlling a single antenna will have one RET managed object instance whose RET device type is "SingleAntennaDevice". A RET device controlling multiple antennas will have multiple RET managed object instances, one for each controlled antenna, whose RET device type is "MultiAntennaDevice"

TDD specific comment: Defines which antenna interface is scanned. Expected value: RMODx-ANTx and empty string where RMODx: 1...12 and ANTx: 1...8 It depends on radio module type which antennas are capable for scanning / AISG device detection.

enum.name: EOaMRmodClimateControlProfiling
enum.comment: Climate control Profiling parameter. Fan speed will be controlled according to module temperature and desired BTS fan profile. - Low Noise: Minimised noise for low and moderate ambient temperatures - Optimized Cooling: Maximised unit MTBF (long life) by running fans with maximum speed already in moderate ambient temperatures - Linear: An intermediate profile which increases fan speed linearly as temperature increase. It is possible to select fan control profiles independently for each module in the BTS. If user does not want to define fan profiling or module does not support fan profiles, the BTS manager will not set a value to SCF. Parameter values are: "Optimized Cooling", "Linear" and "Low Noise". Default value is "Optimized Cooling". BTS property Fan.Control.Profiles.Supported is defined if module supports Fan control profiles (low noise, linear, Optimized cooling). RF variants from Rel. 2.x onwards and FSM3r3 with fans shall have "TRUE" value. RF variants without fans or older than Rel. 2.x shall have "FALSE" value.

enum.name: EOaMRmodLinkSpeed
enum.comment: This linkSpeed parameter defines the RP3-01 link speed between radio modules for master mode ports. This parameter can be set to all radio module variants but "6Gbps" option can be taken into use by BTS only for radio modules which have HW support for that speed. Note that normally default value "Auto" is optimal selection for all configurations, but some case for example optical network performance or SFP selection reasons there is needed to define fixed link speed. Parameter values for RP3-01 link speed: - 3Gbps: When this value is configured, BTS enables the RP3-01 link speed at 4x line rate and always remain at that speed. BTS does not check the SFP capability against the requested line rate, but relies on the user defined configuration. - 6Gbps: When this value is configured, BTS enables the RP3-01 link speed at 8x line rate and always remain at that speed. BTSOM does not check the SFP capability against the requested line rate, but relies on the user defined configuration. - Auto: When this value is configured, BTS first establishes RP3-01 link speed at 4x line rate and checks the HW capability on both modules. If the HWs allow, BTS take into use the RP3-01 link speed at 8x line rate.
