member.name: systemInfoListGeran
member.comment: This parameter contains the GERAN Systeminformation which is used when sending a UE to GSM by eNACC or UE Context Release with redirect. At least one list entry must be configured if SystemInformationType has the value “si” or “psi”. The parameter is meaningless if: - LTE498: RIM for GSM feature is activated AND - the PLMN of the cell is not blacklisted for RIM AND - parameter "gTargetRac" is configured Constant value maxGERAN-SI is defined in 3GPP TS36.331 section 6.4 The 23 octet 3GPP parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet two character must be configured, with a minimum length of one octet.

member.name: btsResetRequest
member.comment: Reset request for BTS. Whenever a (delta-)plan modifiying or setting this parameter is downloaded, BTS will reset automatically. This parameter is not intended for use by operator, but will be used by NetAct to perform automatic troubleshooting actions, which require a reset of the BTS. The value of the parameter as such is not relevant. However, at each new reset request a different value should be selected. One way to make sure that the new parameter value is different from the last one is to use the current time stamp. Using this scheme will also document the time at which the reset decision was taken. However, any other scheme which makes sure the parameter value changes is also possible.

member.name: enbName
member.comment: This is a human-readable name for the eNB. It corresponds to the eNB name according to 3GPP 36.413. The character set is restricted to Printable string according to 3GPP with following supported character: lower case letters 'a' through 'z', upper case letters 'A' through 'Z', the digits '0' through '9' and the characters ' = ( ) + , - . / : ? and space.

member.name: cellResetRequest
member.comment: Reset request for Cell Will be downloaded with current timestamp to indicated reset request, new request will receive new timestamp and therfeore cause parameter change. Cell reset will be exceuted automatically, since parameter change requires cell lock/unlock. String is in human readable format, e.g. Cell reset requested : YYYYMMDD hhnnss where YYYYMMDD hhnnss is timestamp.

member.name: hrpdSectorID
member.comment: This parameter contains the HRPD Sector ID used for HRPD handover preparation/execution and defined as specified in 3GPP2 C.S0024-A. It is used to populate the CDMA2000 sector ID (128 bits) using hexadecimal characters. The format of Sector ID equals the format of an IPv6 address acc. to RFC4291. However it is up to operator whether real IPv6 addresses are used.

struct.name: SOaMAlToggSuppList
struct.comment: The alarms are suppressed based on the toggling alarm parameters. The toggling alarm parameters contain the amount of alarms in time (time and amount values ) for setting the toggling alarm condition and clearance duration time when the toggling alarm is no longer toggling (alarm either active or cleared). If the alarm is active, it is set active after toggling alarm is cleared.

typedef.name: TOaMForeignNidReg
typedef.comment: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) Network Identification (NID) roamer registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. Value TRUE is to enable foreign NID roamers for autonomous registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

typedef.name: TOaMForeignSidReg
typedef.comment: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) System Identification (SID) roamer registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. Value TRUE is to enable foreign SID roamers for autonomous registration. typedef.name: TOaMHomeReg
typedef.comment: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) home registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the homeRegIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.

The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

member.name: idleLBHrpdCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of CDMA HRPD band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

typedef.name: TOaMCrgprPlmnGroupShareListPlmnGroupId

typedef.name: TOaMCrgprPlmnGroupShare
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Specifies the share of the cell resource group on a percentage basis.
TDD specific comment: Specifies the share of the cell resource group on a percentage basis. Because TDD has less DL and UL TTIs per frame, so in order to have enough chances to be scheduled, TDD's value range is smaller than FDD. Lower bound 25% is decided based on uplink scheduling. There are 4 UL TTIs per frame, it is expected that each CRG will be scheduled at least once per frame for both downlink and uplink, so CRG share is set to start from 25%. Then upper bound is 100%-25%=75%.

struct.name: SOaMResourceList
struct.comment:
FDD specific comment: The resource list specifies the antenna line resources allocated for the given local cell. TX and RX resources can freely be assign to local cells. The functionality is guaranteed only for officially supported and tested configurations. There will be no error handling when unofficial configurations are used. HW dependencies: FSMr3: Only 2 RX or 4 RX resources can be assigned to one LCELL. FSMr2: Only in R type configuration four antenna lines can be assigned to one LCELL. Sector Configuration Types A, G, and I use 2 antIds per radio module. Sector Configuration Type H uses antennas from 2 radio modules,1 per radio module. Sector Configuration Type P uses 3 antennas from 2 radio modules. Sector Configuration Type R uses 4 antennas from RIU and radio module, 2 antennas per radio module. Sector Configuration Types D, E, J and M use 4 antIds per radio module. Sector Configuration Types K and N use 4 antennas from 2 radio modules, 2 antIds per radio module. Notes: In RIU coupled mode configuration (RIU chained with Radio modules and same LNCEL is radiated from all modules) local cells need to be commissioned to the chained radio modules and RIU modules. In this case R-type configuration must be used and 4 antlIds must be configured to the resourceList. In case a RIU module is detected by the eNB, 4 RX reception is not supported in LNCELs the RIU is associated.
TDD specific comment: The resource list specifies the antenna line resources allocated for the given local cell. Sector Configuration Types A and I are using 2 antIds per radio module. Sector Configuration Types F is using 1 antId per radio module. Sector Configuration Type N uses antennas from 2 radio modules, 2 per radio module. Sector Configuration Types M and O are using 4 antIds per radio module. Sector Configuration Types L is using 8 antIds per radio module.

typedef.name: TOaMIdleTimeThresLteNR
typedef.comment: The eNB may autonomously remove a LTE NR, if the LTE NR is not used for handover for at least the time 'idleTimeThresLteNR'. Notes: * LTE NRs which are 'reserved by operator' are not autonomously removed by eNB * The eNB checks once per hour if a LTE NR has to be removed Note: It is recommended to chose 'idleTimeThresLteNR' to be smaller than 'idleTimeThresX2' to avoid that one eNB may autonomously close an X2 link and the peer eNB re-esatblishes the X2 link again, because autonomous removal of associated unused Neighbour Relations did not yet occur.

typedef.name: TOaMIdleTimeThresNbeNB
typedef.comment: If for at least the time “idleTimeThresNbeNB” an enbControlled NbeNB no NR and no X2 link is available, then the eNB removes the LNADJ/ LNADJL objects associated with the NbeNB Notes: * Neighbour eNBs and Neighbour Cells which are associated with an oamControlled LNADJ object are not autonomouosly removed by eNB * The eNB checks once per hour if a LTE NR has to be removed

typedef.name: TOaMIdleTimeThresX2
typedef.comment: If for an enbControlled X2 link no LTE Neighbour Relation exists and if for at least the time “idleTimeThresX2” no X2 handover is received, then the eNB autonomously closes the X2 link. Notes: * oamControlled X2 links are not autonomouosly closed by eNB * The eNB checks once per hour if a X2 link has to be closed. Note: It is recommended to chose 'idleTimeThresX2' to be larger than 'idleTimeThresLteNR' to avoid that one eNB may autonomously close an X2 link and the peer eNB re-esatblishes the X2 link again, because autonomous removal of associated unused Neighbour Relations did not yet occur.

struct.name: SOaMAnrIdleTimeThresLte
struct.comment: This structure includes the 'idle time threshold' values used by eNB for autonomous removal of LTE Neighbour resources

struct.name: SOaMBlacklistedGsmPlmnsForRim
struct.comment: List of GERAN PLMN IDs which are to be blacklisted in terms of RIM. No RIM associations will be established for GERAN cells belonging to one of the blacklisted PLMN IDs. If this parameter is omitted, all GERAN neighbor cells will be RIM-enabled provided that the routing area code is configured in each neighbor cell with the "gTargetRac" parameter.

member.name: enbId

If ‘enbId’ is not provided then the associated ‘Global eNB Id’ is a ‘partially specified Global eNB Id’, i.e.: All ‘Global eNB Ids’ with a PLMN ID which is identical to the associated 'X2 Blacklisted PLMN ID' are considered as members of the 'Global eNB Id X2-link Blacklist'.

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsQciTab1Dscp
typedef.comment: This parameter configures the DSCP (Differentiated Services Code Point) value associated with the QCI. The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB. List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal): BE (=0), AF11 (=10), AF12 (=12), AF13 (=14), AF21 (=18), AF22 (=20), AF23 (=22), AF31 (=26), AF32 (=28), AF33 (=30), AF41 (=34), AF42 (=36), AF43 (=38), EF (=46)

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsQciTab1EnforceTtiBundling
typedef.comment: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination. List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal): BE (=0), AF11 (=10), AF12 (=12), AF13 (=14), AF21 (=18), AF22 (=20), AF23 (=22), AF31 (=26), AF32 (=28), AF33 (=30), AF41 (=34), AF42 (=36), AF43 (=38), EF (=46)

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsQciTab8EnforceTtiBundling
typedef.comment: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination. If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

member.name: l2OHFactorDl
member.comment: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2. eNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR DL/100. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

member.name: l2OHFactorUl
member.comment: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2. eNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

enum.comment: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according to [36.321]

member.name: maxGbrDl
member.comment: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction. eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI3 for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

member.name: maxGbrUl
member.comment: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction. eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI3 for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsQciTabOperatorPdcpProfIdx
typedef.comment: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile. If the RLC mode is set to "RLC_AM", this parameter has to set in the range {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}. If the RLC mode is set to "RLC_UM", this parameter has to be set in range {102, 103, 104}.

member.name: prio
member.comment: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203. This parameter is used for GBR congestion handling and is ignored for nonGBR bearers.

enum.comment: This parameter specifies the parameter pollPDU of [36.331] The parameter Poll PDU defines the number of RLC PDUs that are sent on a logical channel before the RLC polling bit is set.

typedef.name: TOaMLnbtsRlcProf1RlcProfileId
typedef.comment: Identity of the RLC profile

enum.name: EOaMLnbtsRlcProf1TPollRetr
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331] This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice of the timerReorder.

enum.name: EOaMLnbtsRlcProf1TProhib
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331] This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU

enum.name: EOaMLnbtsRlcProf1TReord
enum.comment: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331] This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

typedef.name: TOaMPhysCellId
typedef.comment: Physical cell identifier for which the system information applies.

member.name: sysInfo
member.comment:
FDD specific comment: WCDMA system information which is included in the RRC Connection Release message. The parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet two character must be configured, with a minimum length of one octet. The octet string has to be defined according to TS25.331 section 10.2.48a.
TDD specific comment: WCDMA systeminformation which shall be included in the RRC Connection Release message. The parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet two character must be configured, with a minimum length of one octet. The octet string has to be defined according to TS25.331 section 10.2.48a.

struct.name: SOaMSystemInformationListWCDMA
struct.comment:
FDD specific comment: The configured WCDMA system information is sent to the UE with the RRC Connection Release message in all kinds of redirection to WCDMA. The setting applies for all LTE cells of the eNB.
TDD specific comment: The configured WCDMA system information is sent to the UE with the RRC Connection Release message in all kinds of redirection to WCDMA The setting applies for all LTE cells of the eNB.

member.name: calibrationAntennaCarrier
member.comment: Indicate which antenna Carrier is used to carry the calibration streams (calibration training sequence in RX calibration and loopbacked sample streams in TX calibration). For TxCalibration,PHY should know which antenna carrier to receive.For RxCalibration,PHY should know which antenna carrier to send. For NSN OBSAI RRU, this parameter shall be '7'. For CPRI RRU(FZFD,FZFA,FZFF), this parameter shall be '1'.

member.name: calibrationParametersId
member.comment: This parameter indicates one instance of calibration parameters set.Each instance of calibration parameters set maps to one type of RRU. 1: TD-Tech RRU 2: Axis 8 pipe RRU 3: NSN 8 pipe RRU 4: NSN 4 pipe RRU 5: NSN BC 8 pipe RRU

member.name: calibrationPeriod
member.comment: Period of calibration procedure. Number of 10 ms frames. Details of parameter value are HW specific. Allowed values should be powers of 2 e.g. 1, 2, 4, 8,16…4096.

member.name: calibrationSetId0
member.comment: Calibration set Index 0 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId1
member.comment: Calibration set Index 1 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId2
member.comment: Calibration set Index 2 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId3
member.comment: Calibration set Index 3 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId4
member.comment: Calibration set Index 4 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId5
member.comment: Calibration set Index 5 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId6
member.comment: Calibration set Index 6 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: calibrationSetId7
member.comment: Calibration set Index 7 - Identifies A Set Of Calibration set

member.name: rxCalSwitchingDuration
member.comment: Defined duration in time between downlink special subframe GP boundary and Rx Calibration in unit of universal time, 1 universal time = 1/1.2288GHz

member.name: txCalSwitchingDuration
member.comment: Defined duration in time between downlink special subframe GP boundary and Tx Calibration in unit of universal time, 1 universal time = 1/1.2288GHz

struct.name: SOaMCalibrationParameters
struct.comment: Calibration parameter

typedef.name: TOaMAntennaBitMap
typedef.comment: AntennaBitMap encoded as a bitmap, where bit Nb is set to "0" if an antenna path with Np = N-1 is not permit to calibration, and set to "1" if the antenna path with Np = N-1 is permitted to calibration; N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the Least Significant Bit of the bit string. Np = 0 to 7; is the antenna path index.

typedef.name: TOaMCalFrameOffset
typedef.comment: Indicate when it take place with regard to start of calibration period.

enum.name: EOaMCalRxTxFlag
enum.comment: To indicate this calibrationSet is for Rx calibration or Tx calibration. The value "not valid" means this set will not be used.

typedef.name: TOaMCalibrationSetID
typedef.comment: Calibration Set indentification

enum.name: EOaMHalfFrameIndication
enum.comment: Half frame indication, the valid number should 1,6. Note:For radio frame structure type 2 the uplink-downlink configuration 3,4,5, only subframe 1 is valid.

struct.name: SOaMCalibrationSet
struct.comment: Denoting calibration configuration set 0

typedef.name: TOaMBeamIdOfWeight
typedef.comment: Identifies the beam for the downlink interference of the cell.

typedef.name: TOaMImagPartofWeighforAnt0
typedef.comment:

struct.name: SOaMLncelAcBarCsfbOcAcBarAC
struct.comment: Access class barring list (5 bit) for originating calls. Access class barring list (5 bit) for originating calls for AC 11-15 (leftmost bit is for AC 11, the second bit in the list is for AC 12, and so on...). The default is no access class barred.

enum.name: EOaMLncelAcBarCsfbOcAcBarTime
enum.comment: Defines the access class barring time. The access class barring time defines the time that the access barring check remains unsuccessful while the UE is not performing an emergency call. In this case, the UE starts timer T303 using this parameter. Timer value in minutes.

enum.name: EOaMBlacklistTopo
enum.comment: This parameter is introduced to allow blacklisting for X2-Handover only other HO variants are still allowed If set to "all" the respective entry in blacklistHoL is valid for all kinds of Handover Topology. If set to "onlyX2", handover to the respective entry in blacklistHoL shall only be excluded as targets for X2-based handover but may still be used as target for S1 based handover. This parameter is only evaluated for inter eNodeB target cells which can be used as target for X2-Handover as well as for S1-Handover

struct.comment: Profile 1 of DRX configuration parameters. Profile for disabling DRX.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxInactivityT
enum.comment: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX. The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission. If drxLongCycle is set to '160ms', drxInactivityT should be set to '200'(ms) otherwise UEs may go out-of-synch when DRX profile is applied for a longer period of time.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxLongCycle
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Configures the long DRX cycle. It is recommended to use carefully the 40 ms value, as so far tested UEs are not able to do ReportCGI measurement with this cycle size. The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.
TDD specific comment: Configures the long DRX cycle. It is recommended to carefully use the 40 ms value, as so far tested UEs are not able to do ReportCGI measurement with this cycle size. The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxOnDuratT
enum.comment: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX. The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxProfileIndex
enum.comment: DRX profile index. Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

typedef.name: TOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxProfilePriority
typedef.comment: DRX profile priority. Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established. Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

enum.name: EOaMLncelDrxProfile101DrxRetransT
enum.comment:
FDD specific comment: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX. The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.
TDD specific comment: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX for TDD. The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

struct.name: SOaMDrxProfile101

typedef.name: TOaMPreRegLoadBalFactor
typedef.comment: Each eHRPD sector-ID which is configured for preregistration is associated with this loadbalancing factor to allow for loadbalancing according to a weighted round robin mechanism when selecting the sector-ID of the eHRPD-AN for Pre-Registration

member.name: sectorID
member.comment: This Parameter contains the HRPD Sector ID as specified in 3GPP2 C.S0024-A. It is used to populate the CDMA2000 sector ID (128 bits) using hexadecimal characters. The format of Sector ID equals the format of an IPv6 address but without colons. However it is up to Operator whether real IPv6 addresses are used.

struct.name: SOaMEHrpdSectList
struct.comment: This Structure contains a list of eHRPD Sector-IDs which shall be used to address eHRPD-AN when tunneling cdma2000 HRPD PDU for Pre-Registration with eHRPD. Each Sector-ID is associated with a loadbalancing factor to allow loadbalancing between multiple eHRPD-AN

typedef.name: TOaMLncelAltitude
typedef.comment: Altitude in meters (coded value) Relation between coded Altitude N and range of absolute altitudes a (a >= 0 meters) it encodes is the following: for 0 <= N <= 2^15-2: N <= a < N+1 for N = 2^15-1: a >= 2^15-1 According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute altitudes a in metres

typedef.name: TOaMConfidence
typedef.comment: Confidence by which the position is known to be within the shape description expressed as a percentage Confidence = 0 means no information available

typedef.name: TOaMDegreesOfLatitude
typedef.comment: Latitude in degrees (coded value) Relation between coded Degrees of latitude N and range of absolute latitudes X (0° <= X <= 90°) it encodes is the following: for 0 <= N <= 2^23-2: N <= 2^23/90*X < N+1 for N = 2^23-1: N <= 2^23/90*X <= N+1 According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute latitudes X in degrees

typedef.name: TOaMDegreesOfLongitude
typedef.comment: Longitude in degrees (coded value) Relation between coded Degrees of longitude N and range of absolute longitudes X (-180° <= X < +180°) it encodes is the following: N <= 2^24/360*X < N+1 N is coded in 2's complement binary on 24 bits. According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute longitudes X in degrees

enum.name: EOaMDirectionOfAltitude
enum.comment: Represents height above resp. depth below WGS84 ellipsoid surface

enum.name: EOaMLatitudeSign
enum.comment: Distinguishes between north and south latitude

typedef.name: TOaMOrientationOfMajorAxis
typedef.comment: Orientation of major axis of uncertainty ellipsoid measured clockwise from north

typedef.name: TOaMUncertaintyAltitude
typedef.comment: Uncertainty of altitude Relation between coded Uncertainty altitude K and absolute uncertainty of altitude h (0 <= h <= 990.5 metres) it encodes is the following: h = 45*(1.025^K-1)

typedef.name: TOaMUncertaintySemiMajor
typedef.comment: Semi-major of uncertainty ellipsoid Relation between coded Uncertainty semi-major K and absolute semi-major uncertainty r (0 <= r <= 1800 metres) it encodes is the following: r = 10*(1.1^K-1)

typedef.name: TOaMUncertaintySemiMinor
typedef.comment: Semi-minor of uncertainty ellipsoid Relation between coded Uncertainty semi-minor K and absolute semi-minor uncertainty r (0 <= r <= 1800 metres) it encodes is the following: r = 10*(1.1^K-1)

struct.name: SOaMEutranAccessPointPosition
struct.comment: Identifies the geographical position of the transmit antenna for positioning purposes. It is expressed as ellipsoid point with altitude and uncertainty ellipsoid according to TS 23.032 The position is reported within the LPPa OTDOA Information Exchange procedure if requested by E-SMLC. In case of multiple transmit antennas, a geographical mean value should be calculated as "logical antenna"

enum.name: EOaMCellReserve
enum.comment: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for operator use. Cells reserved for operator use are treated as barred by 'normal' UEs without a USIM with AC 11 or 15 inserted. UEs with AC 11 or 15 USIM inserted are specific operator UEs and thus allowed to camp on and access such cells. The default value is not reserved.

struct.name: SOaMFurtherPlmnIdL
struct.comment: These are further PLMN IDs of the cell. The parameter indicates which operators' (PLMNID) networks are available from the cell. These PLMN identities have a cell scope. The primary PLMN ID has to be provided separately for the eNB.

typedef.name: TOaMTC2KRelocOverallHrpd
typedef.comment: This timer value is used for eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target HRPD system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. eNodeB internally use this value to calculate the supervision timer for the eHRPD optimized Handover Execution Phase (TC2KRelocOverall).

typedef.name: TOaMTC2KRelocPrepHrpd
typedef.comment: This timer value defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits for the Downlink CDMA2000 Tunneling message from MME after forwarding the dedicatedInfoCDMA2000-HRPD PDU in UplinkHandoverPreparationTransfer message (received from UE) to MME.

typedef.name: TOaMTUlHoPrepTransferHrpd
typedef.comment: The timer value defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits to receive an UlHandoverPreparationTransfer message from UE after sending a HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest message to the UE.

struct.name: SOaMHrpdTimers
struct.comment: Defines the timers used to control mobility to CDMA2000 HRPD

typedef.name: TOaMIFLBBearCheckTimer
typedef.comment: Timer is started when S1AP sends back Initial Context Setup Response. After Timer expiration it is checked whether or not the UE has a QCI1 bearer. The value 31 indicates that QCI1 (VOIP) bearer are not excluded from the Inter Frequency Load Balancing. Note that when QCI1 check is not performed, there is 1s wait timer before start Load Balancing. In LTE1387 UEs with QCI1 (VOIP) bearer are excluded from the Inter Frequency Load Balancing. As the bearer establishment takes some time, SW has to wait before making a check.

typedef.name: TOaMIFLBHighLoadGBRDL
typedef.comment: High Load for usage of GBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction. High Load is the treshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing. If iFLBHighLoadGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadPdcch are set to 100%, the cell will never enter active Inter Frequency Load Balancing state.

typedef.name: TOaMIFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL

typedef.name: TOaMSpid

Virtual SPID is used for mapping with value ((MNC+255) mod 256) + 1

member.name: spidLast
member.comment: Last SPID value if a range of SPID values shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile. 3GPP 36.300 defines the following SPID range: Values 1-128 are Operator specific SPIDs Values 129-256 are Reference SPID values Reference SPIDs have the following meaning: SPID 256 High prio to eUTRA, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to GERAN SPID 255 High prio to UTRAN, Medium prio to GERAN, Low prio to eUTRA SPID 254 High prio to GERAN, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to eUTRA If LNBTS-moProfileSelect is set to "plmn" then MOPR selection is based on MNC included in UE Serving PLMN ID. Virtual SPID is used for mapping with value ((MNC+255) mod 256) + 1

struct.name: SOaMPrsMutingInfo
struct.comment: The prsMutingInfo is a bit string consisting of 16 bit. Only the first prsMutingInfoPatternLen bits will be taken into account starting from prsMutingInfoBit1. This means the first prsMutingInfoPatternLen bits of the prsMutingInfo bit string will determine the PRS Muting Info pattern with a given periodicity. Details of the description can be found in TS36.355. Muting configuration allows to increase the reuse of the PRS signal. PRS of individual cells can be muted in order to increase hearability of cells with the same frequency reuse.

enum.name: EOaMPrsMutingInfoPatternLen
enum.comment: The prsMutingInfoPatternLen determines how many PRS Muting Info Bits are used to describe PRS muting sequence. The sequence starts from the prsMutingInfoBit1 and it corresponds to the first positioning occasion, prsMutingInfoBit2 corresponds to second positioning occasion and so on.

struct.name: SOaMPrsMuting

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwMaxRbUl
typedef.comment: Defines the maximum number of PRBs which may be assigned to a UE scheduled in UL when restricted PRB assignment in uplink is enabled. Note that the actual amount of PRBs in UL allocation must be of the form 2^i*3^j*5^k where i, j and k are non-negative integers, so effectively the value will be rounded down to the next value complying with the rule. Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are: - if ulChBw is set to '1.4 MHz':6 - if ulChBw is set to '3 MHz': 15 - if ulChBw is set to '5 MHz': 25 - if ulChBw is set to '10 MHz': 50 - if ulChBw is set to '15 MHz': 75 - if ulChBw is set to '20 MHz':100

typedef.name: TOaMRedBwMinRbUl
typedef.comment: Defines the minimum number of PRBs which may be assigned to a UE scheduled in UL when restricted PRB assignment in uplink is enabled. However, a lower number of PRBs is allowed if the transport block size with this number of PRBs and the MCS selected by AMC would exceed the UE capabilities. Note that the actual amount of PRBs in UL allocation must be of the form 2^i*3^j*5^k where i, j and k are non-negative integers, so effectively the value will be rounded up to the next value complying with the rule.

struct.name: SOaMRedBwRbUlConfig
struct.comment: Defines the maximum and minimum number of PRBs which may be assigned to a UE scheduled in UL when restricted PRB assignment in uplink is enabled.

enum.name: EOaMA1ReportInterval
enum.comment: For the RSRP based A1 event of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (InterFreq) Measurements the UE performs periodical reporting with this indicated interval The UE is configured to report this A1 event in an infinite way when this parameter is set, otherwise A1 event will be only reported once.

enum.name: EOaMA2TimeToTriggerMobRsrq
enum.comment: Time to trigger for A2-RSRQ. Duration for which the event A2-RSRQ must be valid, such that mobility measurements with measurement gaps are activated.

typedef.name: TOaMHysThreshold2MobRsrq
typedef.comment:
Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for mobility measurements activation. Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2-RSRQ triggered reporting condition. The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.331: IE value = value [dB] * 2
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold2MobRsrq
typedef.comment:
Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving value < threshold2MobRsrq then mobility measurements with measurement gaps are activated. The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133: - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB) - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold2aRsrq
typedef.comment:
Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (Inter-Freq) measurements. The RSRP based A1 event reports also the RSRQ value which is compared with this threshold in eNB. When RSRP of serving cell becomes better than threshold2a the UE sends the A1 event. If the reported RSRQ of that A1 event of serving cell is also better than this configured threshold2aRsrq in eNB then InterFreq and InterRAT measurements are de-activated. This check is done at each time the A1 report is received in eNB until either the RSRQ value fits or the leaving condition for this A1 event is fullfilled. The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133: - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB) - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

struct.name: SOaMRsrqMobilityParams
struct.comment: Structure containing the RSRQ parameters for mobility triggers It is recommended that parameters of parent structure "RSRQ redirection parameters" are also set.

enum.name: EOaMA2TimeToTriggerRedirectRsrq
enum.comment: Time to trigger for A2-RSRQ. Duration for which the event A2-RSRQ must be valid, such that redirect is raised.

typedef.name: TOaMHysThreshold4Rsrq
typedef.comment:
Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for redirection trigger. Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2-RSRQ triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMThreshold4Rsrq
typedef.comment:
Threshold for RSRQ of intra-frequency serving cell. If RSRQ of serving value < Th4Rsrq then re-direct is triggered. The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133: - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB) - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

struct.name: SOaMRsrqRedirectParams
struct.comment: Structure containing the RSRQ parameters for redirection.

typedef.name: TOaMP0NomPuschIAw
typedef.comment: P0 setting that is broadcast in SIB2 if interference-aware UL-PC is activated. ulpcAlpha must be set to "alpha 1" for interference-aware UL-PC.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcCEBalanceIAw
typedef.comment:
Controls Target SINR in interference-aware UL-PC: provides a tilt in the balancing between Target SINR in cell-center and Target SINR at cell-edge. Target SINR determines the max. throughput, therefore higher values increase cell-center throughput at the cost of cell-edge throughput, and vice versa.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcMinQualIAw
typedef.comment:
Minimum quality measure for interference-aware UL-PC. Target SINR for UEs in poor conditions cannot go below a limit defined by this parameter even if they generate higher UL interference. Defines a minimum quality level in linear scale that is a multiplier to a reference SINR calculated from ulpcRefPwrIAw and the UE's UL signal plus noise.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcMinWaitForPc
typedef.comment: Minimum number of TTIs (ms) that must pass before another UL power decision is made for a UE.

typedef.name: TOaMUlpcRefPwrIAw
typedef.comment:
Controls Target SINR in interference-aware UL-PC: provides an equal shift of Target SINR for all UEs in the cell, regardless of their pathloss ratios.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMCsiRsSubfrConf
typedef.comment: Defines the cell specific CSI-RS subframe configuration 0-4: 5ms period 5-14: 10ms period 15-34: 20ms period 35-74: 40ms period 75-154: 80ms period Note: when CSI-RS periodicity is 5ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf(subframes) when CSI-RS periodicity is 10ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 5(subframes) when CSI-RS periodicity is 20ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 15(subframes) when CSI-RS periodicity is 40ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 35(subframes) when CSI-RS periodicity is 80ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 75(subframes).

enum.name: EOaMDepConfBeamformingType
enum.comment: Defines the beamforming type for which srsBandwidth and srsUePeriodicity are valid. Two elements of srsDlMimoModeDepConf with same beamformingType are not allowed.

enum.name: EOaMDepConfSrsBandwidth
enum.comment: Defines together with srsBwConf (srs bandwidth configuration) the bandwidth for srs for non beamforming or beamforming configured UEs . Please refer to table 5.5.3.2-1 to 5.5.3.2-4 in 3GPP TS36.211. This depends on the value of LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType. If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'nonBeamforming', then srsBandwidth defines the bandwidth of one SRS symbol for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm1 to tm4. If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'beamforming', then srsBandwidth defines the bandwidth of one SRS symbol for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm7 or tm8.

enum.name: EOaMDepConfSrsUePeriodicity
enum.comment: Defines the UE periodicity for srs in which the UE will provide srs to the eNB. If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'nonBeamforming' then this parameter defines the periodicity for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm1 to tm4. If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'beamforming' then this parameter defines the periodicity for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm7 or tm8.

struct.name: SOaMSrsDlMimoModeDepConf
struct.comment: SRS configuration parameter specific for non beamforming and optional beamforming users. If dlMimoMode is set to a non beamforming mode ('SingleTX', 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 'Closed Loop Mimo' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)'), then one structure element is mandatory for the configuration for non beamforming users (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming'). If dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' and actTmSwitch is set to false, then one structure element is mandatory for the configuration for non beamforming users (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming'). If dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' and actTmSwitch is set to true, then the structure must contain 2 elements, one for non beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming') and one for beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'beamforming') configuration. If dlMimoMode is set to a beamforming mode ('Single Stream Beamforming' or 'Dual Stream Beamforming'), then the structure must contain 2 elements, one for non beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming') and one for beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'beamforming') configuration. In case of carrier aggregation, dlMimoMode/actTmSwitch setting under both P-LNCEL and S-LNCEL shall be considered.

typedef.name: TOaMCandSubCellUlSinrOffset
typedef.comment:
Defines the maximum UL SINR offset to serving for candidate sub-cell selection. If the SINR gap between serving sub-cell and a second sub-cell is less than this offset the second sub-cell can be selected as candidate sub-cell.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMRemCandSubCellUlSinrHys
typedef.comment:
Defines the UL SINR hysteresis on top of UL SINR offset for removing candidate sub-cell. If the SINR gap between serving sub-cell and current candidate sub-cell is larger than candSubCellUlSINROffset plus this parameter this candidate sub-cell will be changed to measurement sub-cell.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMRepCandSubCellUlSinrHys
typedef.comment:
Defines the UL SINR hysteresis to replace candidate sub-cell by a measurement sub-cell. If one measurement sub-cell's SINR is larger than current candidate sub-cell' this measurement sub-cell will replace current candidate sub-cell as new candidate sub-cell.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMSubCellSwitchUlSinrHys
typedef.comment:
The parameter defines the UL SINR hysteresis for sub-cell switch.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMSubCellUlSinrAvgT
typedef.comment: The parameter defines the time length as the filter coefficient for averaging UL UE SINR per RRH on SRS, PUSCH and PUCCH for sub-cell switch.

struct.name: SOaMSuperCellParSet
struct.comment: Parameter set for Super Cell feature to maintain the serving and candidate sub-cell selection.

typedef.name: TOaMTm8MuMimoCorrThd
typedef.comment:
The correlation threshold below which two TM8 MU-MIMO candidate can be paired.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

typedef.name: TOaMTm8MuMimoCqiThd
typedef.comment:
The CQI threshold above which the TM8 BF UE can be selected as TM8 MU-MIMO candidate. This TM8 MU-MIMO candidate must also be rank 1 UE.
The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

struct.name: SOaMTm8MuMimoParSet

typedef.name: TOaMUlMuMimoOrthThreshold

The value provided at the interface is internal value. If the external value is required, you must compute it by using the DIVISOR in your code!

enum.name: EOaMModimpCdmaHrpdBdCl
enum.comment: CDMA2000 HRPD band class value used for Idle Mode mobility. The UE performs only Load Balancing cell reselection for bands already configured for Idle Mobility (in CDFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other bands than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such bands.

member.name: idleLBHrpdCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of CDMA HRPD Band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user. When not specified the weight is considered as 0.

typedef.comment: ARFCN value which is used as reference to a GERAN measurement object (LNHOG).

struct.name: SOaMModprRefFreqListNaccGeran
struct.comment: ENACC mobility to GERAN is restricted to the target frequencies configured in refFreqListNaccGeran. The frequency values are used as references to GERAN measurement objects (LNHOG). If feature LTE490 'Selective Mobility Profiles' is enabled by setting the LNBTS parameter actSelMobPrf to 'true' the restriction applies to UEs if no SPID value is provided or if no mobility profile is assigned to the SPID value. If feature LTE490 is deactivated the restriction applies to all UEs. All LNHOG objects of a cell, which contain at least the reference ARFCN value in arfcnValueListGERAN are selected for UE measurement configuration. If the same ARFCN value would be configured in more than one LNHOG instance of a cell, only the first found LNHOG object is considered. No NACC to GERAN mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted. The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

typedef.comment: UTRA-FDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility The UE performs only Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

struct.name: SOaMMoimpUtrFddCarFrqL
struct.comment: List of UTRA-FDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message

member.name: idleLBUtraTddCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of UTRA TDD Carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user. When not specified the weight is considered as 0.

typedef.name: TOaMMoimpUtrTddCarFrq
typedef.comment: UTRA-TDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. It does not make sense to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

struct.name: SOaMMoimpUtrTddCarFrqL
struct.comment: List of UTRA-TDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message

SMOD1-IF4 and SMOD1-IF5 are needed later also with SMr3 indoor version. IF6 in release 3 outdoor version system module is the multiplexed interface RP3/GE.
TDD specific comment: Defines Radio module (RM) connection to the system module. In RF-sharing this is a connection to the master technology FSM. For FSM and FSP this parameter shall be set to "None". member.name: unitName
member.comment: Defines the name of the unit or module in the BTS. This parameter is used in the offline commissioning mode. The following values will be defined: FSM, FSP (FBBx) and FR. The exact module or unit type is defined in the variant parameter.

typedef.name: TOaMUnitNumber
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the number of the module (radio module or system module)in the BTS. Defines the number of the module in chain (radio module or system module) in the BTS. The first radio module connected to each RF interface of system module gets unitNumber with value "1", the second radio module connected to each RF interface of system module gets unitNumber with value "2" and so on. The first baseband extension module (FSP) gets unitNumber value “2” and the second baseband extension module (FSP) gets unitNumber value “3”. Master system module gets unitNumber 1 and first extension system module gets unit number 2 an so on. Parameter is used in offline mode commissioning in BTS Site Manager and in prevalidation in NetAct.
TDD specific comment: Defines the number of the module (radio module or system module) in the BTS. Defines the number of the module in chain (radio module or system module) in the BTS. The first radio module connected to each RF interface of system module gets unitNumber with value "1", the second radio module connected to each RF interface of system module gets unitNumber with value "2" and so on. The first baseband extension module (FSP) gets unitNumber value “2” and the second baseband extension module (FSP) gets unitNumber value “3”. Master system module gets unitNumber 1 and first extension system module gets unit number 2 an so on. Parameter is used in offline mode commissioning in BTS Site Manager and in prevalidation in NetAct.

member.name: variant
member.comment: Defines the variant of the unit or module. This parameter is used in the offline commissioning mode. In the case of FSMD, D is used; in the case of FRGF, GF is used. In the case of baseband extension module: FSPE (FBBA), E is used and FSPH (FBBB), H is used. Defines the name of the module (radio module or system module) in the BTS. Example: variant for FRGF is GF. Example: variant for FSMD is D. Parameter is used in offline mode commissioning in BTS Site Manager and in prevalidation in NetAct.

struct.name: SOaMUnitList
struct.comment: The list defines the unit information for offline mode commissioning in BTS Site Manager and for prevalidation in NetAct. unitList must contain radio modules, system modules and optional baseband extension modules (FSMr3) from BTS site HW configuration. Example HW configuration with FSMD1 and FRGF1: FRGF 1 with product code: 471483A. prodCode = 471483A, unitName = FR, unitNumber = 1, variant = GF and FSMD 1 with product code: 471402A. prodCode = 471402A, unitName = FSM, unitNumber = 1, variant = D. All parameters in unitList are mandatory. prodCode must get known product code value supported. unitName gets always value FR for radio modules even if radio modules would be named differently than FRxx. unitName gets always value FSM for system modules even if system modules would be named differently than FSMx. unitName gets always value FSP for baseband extension modules even if named differently than FSPx.Variant gets always unit variant value. Only radio modules, system modules and baseband extension modules (FSMr3) are supported and used in unitList.

typedef.name: TOaMTraceId
typedef.comment: Trace ID identifies a cell trace session. In combination with PLMN ID, the identifier becomes unique. Trace ID is part of Trace Reference contained in E-UTRAN Trace ID. E-UTRAN Trace ID is unique id identifying a trace session. E-UTRAN Trace ID is made up of Trace Reference and Trace Recording Session Reference. Trace Reference is globally unique and is 6 Octect length comprising of: MCC+MNC+Trace ID. MCC+MNC is of 3 Octet length Trace ID is of 3 Octet length E-UTRAN Trace ID is one of the trace parameters received for a trace session.

typedef.name: TOaMSmodLinkId
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: Defines the RP3 port link in system module to which the Radio Module is connected (direct or in chain). In single LTE mode RP3 ports 1-5 (FSMr2) or 1-6 (FSMr3) can be used for radio modules. In RF sharing configurations with FSMr2; RP3 ports 1,2,3 and 5 can be used for radios. Port #4 is for system module sync. In RF sharing configurations with FSMr3; RP3 ports 1,2 and 3 can be used for radios. Port #6 is for system module sync. In RF chaining configurations with FSMr2; RP3 port 1-3 can be used for RF chains. In RF chaining configurations with FSMr3; RP3 port 1-3 and 6 can be used for RF chains.
TDD specific comment: Defines the RP3 port link in system module to which the Radio Module is connected (direct or in chain). In single LTE mode all RP3 ports 1-5 can be used for radio modules. In RF sharing configurations RP3 ports 1,2,3 and 5 can be used for radios and port #4 is for system modules sync. In RF chaining configurations RP3 port 1-3 can be used for RF chains.

enum.name: EOaMSmodLinkSpeed
enum.comment: This linkSpeed parameter defines used the RP3-01 link speed between system module and first radio module. This parameter can be set to all FSM variants but "6Gbps" option can be taken into use by BTS only for FSMr3 HW. Note that normally default value "Auto" is optimal selection for all configurations, but some case for example optical network performance or SFP selection reasons there is needed to define fixed link speed. Parameter values for RP3-01 link speed: - 3Gbps: When this value is configured, BTS enables the RP3-01 link speed at 4x line rate and always remain at that speed. BTS does not check the SFP capability against the requested line rate, but relies on the user defined configuration. - 6Gbps: When this value is configured, BTS enables the RP3-01 link speed at 8x line rate and always remain at that speed. BTSOM does not check the SFP capability against the requested line rate, but relies on the user defined configuration. - Auto: When this value is configured, BTS first establishes RP3-01 link speed at 4x line rate and checks the HW capability on both modules. If the HWs allow, BTS take into use the RP3-01 link speed at 8x line rate.

typedef.name: TOaMRadioMaster
typedef.comment:
FDD specific comment: This radioMaster parameter defines the BTS system module that controls O&M tasks in RF sharing. With value "true" this parameter defines a system module that controls radio SW updates, antenna line device parameters, and common radio parameters in case of single technology dedicated RF-module or master mode when RF-sharing feature is used.
TDD specific comment: With value "true" this parameter defines a system module that controls radio SW updates, antenna line device parameters, and common radio parameters in case of single technology dedicated RF-module or master mode when RF-sharing feature is used.

struct.name: SOaMLinkList
struct.comment:
FDD specific comment: The parameter linkList must be configured mainly in RF sharing configurations, where the configuration of the RP3 links for the radio modules depends on the shared RF technologies. If there is a need to change RP3-01 link speed then the linkList need to be defined also. In case of RF sharing, in the peer technology SMOD instance the linkSpeed parameter is not applicable but the default value must still be used. For LTE-2G RF sharing configuration: If the RP3 link contains a shared radio module, LTE must be configured as radio master technology (that is radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true' while in 2G SMOD the radioMaster must be configured to 'false'). If the RP3 link contains a not shared radio module, LTE is the radio master for the radio module (that is radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true'). For LTE-3G RF sharing configuration: If the RP3 link contains a shared radio module, 3G must be configured as radio master technology (that is radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'false' while in 3G SMOD radioMaster must be configured to 'true'). If the RP3 link contains a not share radio module, LTE is the radio master for the radio module (that is radioMaster in LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true'). LTE only configuration when linkSpeed is defined: LTE is the radio master for the radio module (that is radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true').
TDD specific comment: The parameter linkList must be configured only in RF sharing configurations, where the configuration of the RP3 links for the radio modules depends on the shared RF technologies. For LTE-2G RF sharing configuration the configuration need to be done as below: If the RP3 link contains a shared radio module, LTE must be configured as radio master technology (i.e. radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true' while in 2G SMOD the radioMaster must be configured to 'false'). If the RP3 link contains a not shared radio module, LTE is the radio master for the radio module (i.e. radioMaster in the LTE SMOD must be configured to 'true').

member.name: idleLBUtranFddCelResWeight
member.comment: Weight factor of UTRA-FDD carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing. When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.
